nd Cake','<br>\n','Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; add sugar and beating well. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating until combined.<br><br>Combine flour and salt; gradually add to butter mixture, beating&nbsp; at low speed just until blended after each addition.&nbsp; Stir in vanilla .<br><br>&nbsp;Pour batter into a grease and floured 10 inch&nbsp; Bundt pan. Bake at 300 oF&nbsp; for 1 hour and 40min. or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. <br><br>&nbsp;Cool in&nbsp; pan over a wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pan.<br>\n',10,0,0,0,0,18,13,7,9,13,9,115,'4','2014-04-25 08:40:35',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(46,'Sparkling Punch','<br>\n','Stir together pineapple juice and pink lemonade concentrate.and strawberry daiquiri<br>&nbsp;Thawed, cover and chill for one hour. <br><br>Stir in ginger ale just before serving. garnish with lemon slices.<br><br><br><br><br>\n',20,0,0,0,0,12,13,7,8,11,7,8,'','2014-05-21 09:29:41',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(42,'Crispy Chicken Strips','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 425oF. <br>Stir together crushed crackers, pecans, paprika, salt and pepper.<br><br>Whisk egg white just until foamy. Place a wire rack coated with cooking spray in a parchment paper lined 15 x 10 inch jelly-roll pan<br><br>Dredge chicken strips in flour; dip in egg white, and dredge in saltine mixture.<br><br>Lightly coat chicken on each side with cooking spray; arrange chicken on wire rack. <br><br>Bake for 18 -20 minutes or until golden brown, turning once after 12 minutes.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,41,13,8,9,16,9,35,'../files/recipes/crispy chicken strips.JPG','2014-05-12 16:11:20',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(61,'Jezebel Sauce','<br>\n','<br>Mix all ingredients in a medium bowl.<br><br>Pour over cream cheese, over ham or pork,&nbsp; or over saltine crackers.<br>\n',0,0,0,0,0,20,13,8,8,3,9,10,'','2014-03-16 17:19:39',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(63,'Bacon Onion Dip','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In medium bowl stir together all ingredients.&nbsp;Cover and chill until ready to serve.<div><br>Yield 1 3/4 cups<br>\n</div>\n	\n	',20,0,0,1,0,42,13,9,8,3,6,10,'../files/recipes/onion deep.JPG','2014-05-21 04:05:33','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(44,'Taco Salad','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Mix the first 3 items in a&nbsp; mixing bowl.<br><br>&nbsp;Spread a layer of the mixture on&nbsp; a plate.<br>&nbsp;Then cut up the lettuce, tomatoes and green onions and place each one on top of the mixture.<br><br>&nbsp;Then add the shredded cheese as the top layer. It is now ready to eat.\n	\n	',15,0,0,0,0,4,8,7,8,10,9,15,'../files/recipes/taco salad.JPG','2014-02-06 17:08:48','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(14,'Gorilla Bread','	\n		<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-45a2e2f0-82cf-00e5-47a7-aa44c764fd8a\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">It is not really known how this recipe came to be, or how it got to be this famous, with a name like gorilla bread, which many classify as silly; the truth is that this recipe has a great deal of popularity and that everyone who tries it is fascinated by its flavor.</span></p><br><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"></span><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Many prepare it for breakfast, to side a cup of coffee, more conservative others, eat it as a dessert after dinner, and some follow the likings of famous like President Jimmy Carter, who absolutely loved it, it is certain though, that this dessert occupies a precious place in the American pastry. Sometimes, even in the most famous cookbooks they come with a warning of Absolutely delicious.</span></p><br><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"></span><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Gorilla bread is simply exceptional as a dessert, both the original recipe and its variants with chocolate and toffee sauce, and others have great popularity, and besides the great caloric input, we need to also take in the important potassium input that the walnuts which it is prepared with give us. In conclusion, we could only take seriously the warning that they give us.</span></span>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat the oven 350 oF<br>Spray a bundt pan with nonstick cooking spray .<br><br>Mix the granulate sugar and cinnamon in a saucepan. Melt the butter and brown sugar over low heat, stirring well, set aside.<br><br>Sprinkle each crescent triangle with 1/2&nbsp; teaspoon of cinnamon sugar. <br><br>Place a slice of cream cheese in the center of each triangle, roll as to make&nbsp; the&nbsp; crescent rolls. Sprinkle 1/2 cup of the nuts into the bottom of the pan. Place half of the prepared biscuits in the pan. Sprinkle with cinnamon sugar, pour half of the melted mixture over the biscuits, and sprinkle on 1/2 cup of nuts.<br>&nbsp; <br>Layer the second can of prepared crescents on top, sprinkle with the remaining cinnamon sugar, pour the remaining butter mixture over the biscuits, and sprinkle with the remaining 1/2 cup of nuts.<br><br>Bake for 30 minutes.<br>Remove from the oven and cool for 10 minutes. Place a plate on&nbsp; top and invert.<br>\n	\n	',10,0,0,0,0,25,13,9,9,13,9,45,'../files/recipes/gorillabread.jpg','2014-05-07 11:39:38','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2013-11-13 13:00:03'),(49,'Parsley Potatoes','<br>\n','Peel a strip of skin from around the middle of each potato, and place potatoes in cold water. Set aside. <br><br>Heat a large skillet over medium-high heat; add oil, saute onion and&nbsp;chopped&nbsp;garlic for 5 mins or until tender. Add chicken broth and 3/4 cup parsley chopped, mix well and put in a boil.<br><br>Place potatoes in a single layer in skillet. Return to a boil; reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 10 mins or until potatoes are tender.<br><br>Remove potatoes with a slotted&nbsp; spoon to serving bowl, add pepper to skillet, stir. Pour sauce over potatoes. Sprinkle with remaining parsley chopped.<br><br>You can replace parsley with basil leaves.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,37,7,7,6,14,9,20,'../files/recipes/Parslied potatoes.JPG','2014-04-30 21:32:05',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(68,'Rum Cake','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF and greased 8 inch round pan.<br><br>Cream butter and brown sugar in a large bowl , add&nbsp; honey, eggs, water and rum. mix well, pour flour sifted over the creamed mixture and beat until all ingredients are combined,&nbsp; pour the batter into pan.<br><br>Bake for 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.<br>Let cake cool&nbsp; on wire rack.<br><br>To serve invert the cake onto a platter, sift confectioner sugar on top.<br>\n',10,0,0,0,0,23,13,9,9,13,8,40,'','2014-06-05 18:35:43',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(66,'Biscuits','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 425oF<br><br>Place paper baking cups in muffin pans, and coat with cooking spray , set aside.<br><br>In a medium bowl stir together all ingredients&nbsp; with an electric mixer until creamy,<br><br>spoon batter into pans immediately,&nbsp; filling cups two-thirds full.<br><br>Bake for 10- 15 minutes. Cool on wire racks.<br><br><br>\n',18,0,0,0,0,46,7,7,9,14,9,15,'../files/recipes/biscuit.JPG','2014-05-17 00:41:56',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(45,'Yogurt Herb Dip','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In a small bowl combine yogurt, basil, oil and thyme. Mix well.<br><br>Season to taste with plenty&nbsp; of vegetables.<br><br>May also be used as a potato topping or salad dressing.<br>\n	\n	',12,0,0,0,0,7,13,7,8,3,6,5,'../files/recipes/yogurt herb deep.JPG','2014-02-28 02:21:02','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(43,'Cheesy Chicken Rice','<br>\n','Season chicken with garlic, pepper lemon&nbsp; before.&nbsp; Stir in soup water, rice, vegetables and onion power in a 12 x 8\" shallow baking dish. <br>Top with&nbsp; chicken and cover.<br><br>Bake at 375oF&nbsp; for 45 min.&nbsp; or until done.<br><br>Top with cheese, and put in oven until melt.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,28,13,8,9,4,5,50,'../files/recipes/cheesy chicken rice.JPG','2014-05-28 17:20:34',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(47,'White Sangria','<br>\n','Combine wine, brandy and orange peel in large pitcher, chill until cool.<br><br>Just before serving, add soda and ice. <br><br>stir to mix and pour into wine glasses. <br><br>add additional ice and peach pieces to each drink serve.<br>\n',20,0,0,0,0,16,9,9,7,11,6,15,'','2014-05-08 10:39:58',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(58,'Cheese Herb Dressing','','	\n		Combine cream cheese and vinegar in a small bowl, stirring until smooth.&nbsp;&nbsp;Add yogurt, parsley, chives, celery seeds, and salt; stir well. Stir in pimiento, drained.&nbsp;Serve with salad greens, yield 1 cup.<br>\n	\n	',25,0,0,0,0,15,13,7,8,3,6,6,'../files/recipes/cheese herb dressing.JPG','2014-05-17 16:00:46','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(57,'Festival Slaw','<br>\n','Combine cabbage, red cabbage, carrot, onion, cashews and pineapple in a medium bowl, toss gently.<br><br>Combine vinegar and remaining ingredients; stir well.&nbsp; Add to cabbage mixture, and toss gently. Cover and chill thoroughly.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,15,13,7,8,10,9,10,'../files/recipes/col slow.JPG','2014-04-22 02:08:33',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(55,'Chunky Meat and Fruit Salad','<br>\n','In small bowl combine 2 cups plain&nbsp; yogurt low fat, 2 tbsp mustard, 1/4 cup honey&nbsp; and 1/4 tsp cinnamon and nutmeg. and chill.<br><br>Cut 1/2 inch honey ham and turkey breast, cut celery and red apple, cored. <br>In medium bowl combine ham, turkey, grapes, celery and apple. Gently toss with chill dressing.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,15,13,8,8,10,9,15,'','2014-04-25 19:03:44',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(64,'Banana Cupcakes','<br>\n','Preheat&nbsp; oven at 350oF<br>Beat&nbsp; butter, softened, at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy; gradually add sugar, beating well. <br><br>Add eggs, banana mashed and vanilla, beating until blended. <br><br>Add flour to banana mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour; beat at low speed until blended after each&nbsp; addition.<br><br>Place paper baking cups in muffin pans, and coat with cooking spray; spoon batter into pans, filling cups two-thirds full..<br><br>Bake for 17 minutes. Remove cupcakes from pans immediately, and cool on wire racks. Spread with frosting, if desired.<br>\n',8,0,0,1,0,48,13,8,9,15,9,30,'../files/recipes/cupcakes.JPG','2014-05-03 00:09:06',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(51,'Mash Potatoes Cheese','<br>\n','Peel potatoes, cut in half and place in a pot, cover with water and bring to a boil&nbsp; with salt, about 20 minutes or until tender, drain and return to pot.<br><br>&nbsp;Mash&nbsp; potatoes with masher. Add sour cream and cheese, when cheese is melted add chives and pepper to taste.\n',6,0,0,0,0,23,7,7,6,14,9,25,'../files/recipes/Mashed potatoes and cheese.jpg','2014-05-11 14:26:28',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(53,'Shrimp Balls','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Chop or grind shrimp peeled and deveined, onion and garlic.<br><br>&nbsp;Add bread crumbs, egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.&nbsp; Form into 1\" balls. Roll balls in flour.<br>&nbsp;<br>Chill for at least 1 hour. Heat oil in fry all.Deep fry balls a few at a time until golden brown.<br><br>Drain in basket. Repeat.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,67,7,9,6,9,9,95,'../files/recipes/shrimp balls.JPG','2014-05-21 01:22:51','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(52,'Chicken and Broccoli Macaroni','<br>\n','Prepare macaroni according&nbsp; to package directions in 3 qt saucepan. Add broccoli during last 4 min. of cooking time.<br><br>Drain macaroni and broccoli well in colander.<br><br>Heat butter in skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until well browned, stirring often. Stir soup, milk, cheese, pepper and&nbsp; macaroni mixture into skillet.<br>\n<div><br></div><div>Cook until mixture is hot and bubbling.</div>\n',4,0,0,2,0,41,10,8,6,4,9,30,'../files/recipes/chicken and brocoly macarroni.jpg','2014-05-10 08:41:39',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(50,'Chick Pea Salad','<br>\n','In a medium colander drain and rinse the chick pea. <br><br>Remove to serving bowl.<br><br>Add red and green pepper , onion chopped, vinegar,&nbsp; olive oil , salt and pepper to taste.<br>Mix well.\n',4,0,0,0,0,17,7,7,8,10,9,10,'../files/recipes/chick pea salad.JPG','2014-04-30 16:03:07',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(56,'Spinach Salad','<br>\n','Combine torn fresh spinach,&nbsp; chopped red apple, golden raisins, and almonds in a large bowl; toss gently. <br><br>&nbsp;Combine apple juice and remaining ingredients in a small jar, cover tightly , and shake vigorously.<br><br>&nbsp;Pour over spinach mixture, and toss gently.\n',6,0,0,1,0,49,13,8,8,10,9,20,'../files/recipes/spinach salad.JPG','2014-05-21 22:15:25',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(54,'Chicken Hula','<br>\n','Rub chicken with garlic, sprinkle with salt.<br><br>Broil or grill chicken until cooked through (about 10 min. Drain pineapple juice into large saucepan, combine with honey, lime juice, soy sauce and cornstarch. Cook stirring, until thickened, add pineapple slices, heat through.<br><br>&nbsp;Serve pineapple and sauce with chicken. <br><br>Sprinkle with lime peel.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,22,13,8,6,16,9,25,'../files/recipes/Chicken hula.jpg','2014-04-03 19:00:03',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(62,'Nut Balls','<br>\n','Preheat the oven to 350oF.<br><br>&nbsp;In a mixing bowl,cream butter. Add honey and beat until light and fluffy. Blend in vanilla, add flour, salt, walnuts, mix well.<br><br>&nbsp;Shape level teaspoons into balls. Place on greased cookie sheets.<br><br>&nbsp;Bake for 15 or 20 minutes.Cool on wire racks, but&nbsp; while still warm, roll in confectioner sugar&nbsp; Cool thoroughly, then roll a second time in confectioner sugar.<br>\n',12,0,0,0,0,31,13,9,9,12,9,50,'','2014-05-27 04:50:49',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(35,'Light fruity Pie','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Dissolve gelatin completely in 2/3 cup boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes. Add ice cubes and stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2-3 minutes. Remove any unmelted ice.<br><br>Using wire whisk,&nbsp; blend in whipped topping; then whip until smooth.<br><br>Fold in fruit. Chill, if necessary,&nbsp; until mixture will mound.&nbsp; Spoon into crust. and chill 3 hours&nbsp; or until set. <br><br>Garnish, if desired.<br><br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,12,13,8,8,15,9,5,'../files/recipes/light fruit pie.JPG','2014-05-17 09:27:20','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(19,'Almond Legend Cake','<div><div>From immemorial times the almond is considered a symbol of love, wealth and happiness. Believed connected with the Greek culture, the legend tells Princess Phyllis was turned into an almond tree by the Gods, after she die of sadness, waiting for her loved Demophon returns to marry her. Perhaps because the legend, almonds are currently presented at weddings, festivals and special events as a symbol of prosperity and union.</div><div><br></div><div>The almondsâ€™ pleasant aroma and unusual taste makes them one of the most consumed seed, with high popularity in the world of international pastry. The Almond Legend Cake delights our palate by combining the sweetness with the lighter, bitter flavor of the almond oil. The sugared cover is made in synonymous of the deeper love and the almond inside represents the eternal spirit of youthful impetuosity.</div><div><br></div><div>Prepare the Almond Legend Cake following the advice given: one single almond seed should be included intact. Odds numbers symbolize fortune and luck. When the cake is divided, the person who gets the Almond will be blessed with great joy and happiness.</div></div>\n','Generously grease a bundt. Gently press 1/2 cup chapped <b>almonds </b>in botton and half-way up sides of pan, in large bowl at low speed mix all ingredients less whole almond, apricot preserve and 3 tsp orange juice. Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Stir in whole almond. Carefully pour batter into prepared pan. Bake at 350 oF for 35 - 45 minutes. <br><br>Cool in pan for 10 minutes invert onto serving plate. In small bowl, combine the apricot preserve and remaining orange juice, blend well. Spoon over warm <b>cake</b> and cool to receive a delightful Almond Legend Cake.\n',12,0,0,5,0,1064,13,8,9,14,7,75,'../files/recipes/almond legend cake.jpg','2014-06-07 22:46:48','',1,1,1,1,1,0,'2013-11-20 13:00:02'),(25,'Healthy Flan','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 350oF. <br><br>Heat sugar in small heavy-duty saucepan over medium-low&nbsp; heat, stirring constantly, for 3-4 minutes or until dissolved and caramel colored. Pour onto bottom of 9 inch round cake pan; quickly swirl around bottom to coat, set aside.<br><br>Place egg white, condensed milk, vanilla and water in blender, cover.Blend for 5 seconds<br><br>Pour into prepared pan; cover lightly with foil. Place pan in large roasting pan fill roasting pan with warm water to about 1 inch depth. Bake for 50 minutes or until knife&nbsp; inserted near center comes out clean.<br><br>Remove flan from water. Cool on wire rack. Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.<br><br>To serve, run knife around&nbsp; edge of pan. Invert serving plate over pan. Turn over, shake gently to release.<br><br>This is a healthy dessert for persons with high cholesterol.<br>\n	\n	',8,0,0,0,0,211,7,8,9,13,9,55,'../files/recipes/my healthy flan.jpg','2014-05-29 02:01:06','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(48,'Walnut Cream','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		<span id=\"result_box\" class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\"></span><span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\"></span></span><span id=\"result_box\" class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\"></span><span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">In a</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">large bowl</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">beat butter</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">until</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">soft.</span><br><br> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">Gradually add sugar</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">until a</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">smooth</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">mixture</span><span class=\"\" title=\"Click for alternate translations\">.</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">Stir</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">in</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">grated</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">nuts</span><span class=\"\" title=\"Click for alternate translations\">.</span><br><br>&nbsp;<span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">Can be</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">substituted for</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">hazelnuts</span> <span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\">or almonds</span></span>.<br><span id=\"result_box\" class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\"></span><span title=\"Click for alternate translations\" class=\"hps\"></span></span>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,11,13,7,8,14,6,10,'','2014-03-16 12:28:48','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(70,'Traditional Flan','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF.<br><br>Heat sugar in small, heavy-duty saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring constantely, for 3 to 4 minutes or until dissolved and caramel-colored. Pour onto bottom of 9 inch round cake pan; quickly swirl around bottom to coat.<br><br>Place evaporated milk, condensed milk, eggs and vanilla in blender, cover. Blend for 5 seconds. Pour into prepared pan; cover lightly with foil. Place pan in large roasting pan; fill roasting pan with warm water to about&nbsp; 1 inch depth.<br><br>Bake for 50 minutes or until wooden pick&nbsp; inserted center comes out clean. Remove flan from water. Cool on wire rack.<br><br>Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.<br><br>To serve, run small spatula around edge of&nbsp; pan. Invert&nbsp; serving plate over pan. Turn over; shake&nbsp; gently to release.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,14,7,9,9,13,5,55,'../files/recipes/traditional flan.JPG','2014-05-05 19:17:23',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(71,'St. Patrick Spinach Salad','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Pan fry&nbsp; slices bacon until crisp, drain on paper towel&nbsp; and&nbsp; bit. Reserving about 3 tbsp&nbsp; drippings in skillet.<br><br>Add vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper to taste. Heat 30 seconds to warm.<br><br>Meanwhile, halve grapes. In bowl toss spinach and grapes with the warm dressing to coat.<br><br>Serve&nbsp; with&nbsp; bacon bit, cheese&nbsp; and pecans<br><br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,7,7,7,8,10,10,20,'../files/recipes/St. Patrick Spinach Salad.JPG','2014-04-14 10:40:57','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(72,'Tuna Sandwich','<br>\n','Mash&nbsp; and stir cream cheese with&nbsp; chili sauce and spread on the inside of 2 halved and split pita bread.<br><br>Drain tuna and add to a bowl, flake with a fork and mix with thawed vegetables mix.<br><br>Spoon into pita halves.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,22,7,7,8,10,9,15,'','2014-05-17 23:13:31',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(18,'Coconut Cake','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF - Grease an flour three 9 inch round cake, set pans aside.<br><br>In large bowl, with mixer on medium speed,&nbsp; beat butter until creamy. Add sugar and continue beating 6 minutes or until light and fluffy.<br><br>Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after&nbsp; each addition<br><br>Add flour and milk alternately to butter mixture, beginning and ending with flour, add vanilla and beat until just mixed, divide batter equally among prepared pans.Level batter in each pan by holding pan 3-4 inches above counter,then dropping it flat onto counter several times to release air bubbles and produce more level cake layers.<br>Bake 30 -35 minutes until toothpick inserted of layers come out clean.<br><br>While cake is baking,&nbsp; prepare coconut filling in medium bowl with spoon, stir together sugar, sour cream, milk, 1/2 cup coconut until well blended.<br><br>Cool layers on wire 10 minutes , with small knife, loosen layers from sides of pan and invert onto work surface. Using handle and wooden spoon, poke holes in layers 1 inch&nbsp; apart,&nbsp; until each layer is poked all over. Spread one-third of filling on each layer. Place 1 layer on cake plate, top with&nbsp; second, then third layer, (hold stacked layers with&nbsp; skewers (together ) to prevent cake from shifting. Cover and refrigerate 1 hour or up to 3 days to absorb filling, when ready to assemble cake, prepare 7 minutes frosting.<br><br>FROSTING<br>4 cup sugar&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>1 cup&nbsp; water<br>4 eggs whites<br>8 drops lemon<br>1/8&nbsp; tsp&nbsp; salt<br>1/4 tsp cream of tartar<br><br>In a saucepan&nbsp; combine&nbsp; water, sugar, lemon, let it boil for 7 minutes.<br>While&nbsp; beat the eggs white until stiff, add salt, cream of tartar and vanilla, when the&nbsp; syrup list&nbsp; so hot is added slowly to the meringue beat this constantly&nbsp; until desired consistency , strong consistency is proved when&nbsp; there are marks on the surface&nbsp; of a fork to pass through it.<br><br>Use frosting to frost top&nbsp; and side of cool cake, sprinkle cake with remaining coconut and garnish with strawberries.<br>\n',20,0,0,0,0,18,13,8,9,13,8,150,'../files/recipes/jemmycoconoutcake.jpg','2014-04-03 17:06:33',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(74,'Broccoli Soup','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In a large saucepan, mix chicken broth,&nbsp; onion, broccoli, garlic powder. Bring to a boil. <br>reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes, or until vegetables are soft.<br><br>Pour mixture into a food processor. Pulse until smooth,approximately&nbsp; 1 minute. Reserve in a bowl. <br><br>In the original saucepan,&nbsp; melt butter, whisk in flour, salt, and a little pepper until a thick paste forms.. Add milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.<br><br>&nbsp;Add cheese; stir until it dissolves.<br><br>Pour in broccoli mixture and cook&nbsp; until blended. If necessary,&nbsp; add more&nbsp; chicken&nbsp; broth to thin. Season with additional salt and pepper. And serve with bread for&nbsp; dipping.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,17,13,8,6,14,9,15,'../files/recipes/brocoly soup.JPG','2014-06-05 16:56:45','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(75,'Frosting 7 Minutes','<br>\n','In a sauce pan combine water, sugar and lemon, let it boil for 7 minutes.<br><br>While beat the eggs white until stiff, add salt, cream of tartar and vanilla, When the syrup list, so hot is added slowly to the meringue, beat this constantly until desired consistency.&nbsp; <br><br>Strong consistency is proved when there are marks on the surface of a fork to pass&nbsp; through it.<br><br>Use frosting to frost top and side of cool cake 9 inch&nbsp; round cake.<br>\n',16,0,0,0,0,12,7,7,6,14,6,7,'','2014-03-21 23:18:49',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(76,'Chocoflan','<br>\n','<div>Heat the oven to 375 oF. Grease a bundt pan. Mix the milk, 4 ounces of cream cheese, 4 eggs, vanilla and sugar in a blender; blend for 5 seconds and put aside. At medium speed, with an electric mixer, beat the chocolate cake mix, water, oil and three eggs; beat well. Add sour cream and repeat.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>First pour the chocolate cake mixture into the greased bundt pan and then pour the first mixture (previously set aside) &nbsp;slowly over the chocolate cake layer. Place the bundt pan inside a 13x9x2 pan &nbsp;and add water until the pan is half filled. Bake for 1 hour and 30 minutes.</div>',0,0,0,0,0,196,13,8,9,13,8,105,'../files/recipes/chocoflan.jpg','2014-06-01 22:25:45',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(362,'Cuban Congri Rice','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Wash beans and soak them in water for an hour. Cook beans in the same soaking water until tender, about 2 hours. (In pressure cooker cook them for 15 minutes).<br><br>In a skillet saute meat pork chopped in the little pieces, remove it, and if necessary add oil until 2 tbs of fat in it. Saute onion, garlic, oregano, black pepper and green pepper.<br><br>Put beans with water, rice and salt in the rice cooker, add the sauce from the skillet and cook.<br><br>When the rice is done wait 15 minutes, uncover and stir from bottom.<br><br>When you serve stir in the fried meat pork and stir again from below to mix.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,3,0,412,7,8,6,7,9,65,'../files/recipes/congri rice.JPG','2014-06-04 17:22:37','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(204,'Ziti Pasta','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 375 oF&nbsp; spray a 9\" x 13\" baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.<br><br>Cook a noodle as directed on package, omit salt and drain in colander.<br><br>Put the marinade, tomatoes and cream cheese diced in the same pot and cook&nbsp; over medium heat until cheese is melted and well blended. Stir frequently. Put the noodles in the pot and mix well.<br><br>Combine sour cream and mozzarella cheese, set aside. Pour the half of noodles in the baking pan. Arrange sour cream - cheese mixture, cover with the remaining noodle and top with mozzarella and parmesan cheese.<br><br>Bake 20 minutes or until cheese is melted.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,15,13,9,9,4,8,45,'../files/recipes/zity pasta.JPG','2014-05-14 18:14:45',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(111,'Doughnuts','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In a medium bowl sift flour, baking powder,salt, nutmeg and cinnamon.<br><br>Beat eggs with sugar and melted butter. Add this mixture to the dry ingredients alternately with milk.<br><br>On a flat surface roll out the dough with a rolling pin until you have a quarter inch thick.Cut the doughnuts.<br><br>Deep fry them in oil hot about 3 minutes. When you throw in the oil sink to the bottom and&nbsp; then rise. Turn it over so they are browned on both sides. Drain on paper towel.<br><br>At fry do not put many at a time,&nbsp; only those that can fry the other side but no on top of each other.<br>\n	\n	',24,0,0,0,0,14,13,9,6,15,9,30,'../files/recipes/donut.JPG','2014-06-05 22:16:24','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(121,'Raspberry Chocolate Smoothie','<br>\n','Blend all ingredients together in food processor .<br><br>Serve cool.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,16,13,8,8,11,9,5,'','2014-05-21 04:09:41',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(77,'Rice with Cheese','<br>\n','<div id=\"gt-res-content\" class=\"almost_half_cell\"><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"zoom:1\"><span id=\"result_box\" class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\">Preheat oven to 350oF Coat a 9 x 13 inch pan with cooking spray.</span></span></div><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"zoom:1\"><span class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\"><br></span></span></div><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"zoom:1\"><span class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\">Cut cheese in rectangle no to wide, and cut the green chilis the same way, make a sandwich with two slices of cheese and one slice of chili in the midle.</span></span></div><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"zoom:1\"><span class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\"><br></span></span></div><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"zoom:1\"><span class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\">Chop onions and jalapeno in small pieces, crush galic, saute all this in a casserole with butter. Add washed rice, salt and chicken broth, bring to boil in medium heat stirring constantelly until dry.</span></span></div><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"zoom:1\"><span class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\"><br></span></span></div><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"zoom:1\"><span class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\">Pour into prepared baking dish half the rice, put all sandwish over the rice. Cover with remaining rice and pour slowly whipping cream.</span></span></div><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"zoom:1\"><span class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\"><br></span></span></div><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"zoom:1\"><span class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><span class=\"hps\">Bake 45 minutes.</span></span></div><div dir=\"ltr\" style=\"zoom:1\"><span class=\"\" lang=\"en\"><br><br><br><br><br><br></span></div></div>\n',6,0,1,5,0,52,13,7,9,7,8,80,'../files/recipes/Rice with Cheese Slide.JPG','2014-05-21 01:27:06',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(295,'Beef Casserole','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 400oF. Coat 2 quart baking dish with cooking spray. Heat large nonstick skillet over medium high. Add beef &nbsp;and onion, cook, stirring often, until beef is browned, 5 &nbsp;or 7minutes. Stir in soup and 1/2 cup water; cook until bubbly.<div>Transfer to baking dish; top with potatoes, cheese and breadcrumbs.</div><div><br></div><div>Bake until beef mixture is bubbly and topping is golden, 12 or 15 minutes.</div><div><br></div><div>Let stand 10 minutes before serving.</div>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,19,13,8,9,6,9,45,'../files/recipes/beef casserole.JPG','2014-05-25 11:20:53','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(78,'Walnut Cheesecake Brownies','<br>\n','Prepare brownie mix as package directs. Spread half of batter evenly in greased 9\" round cake pan. reserve remaining batter.&nbsp;In 1 quart&nbsp; bowl, beat cream cheese with eggs and sugar until smooth.. Mix in 1 cup of the walnuts; pour over brownie batter in pan.<br><br>Gently&nbsp; dollop with remaining batter to nearly&nbsp; cover cheese&nbsp; mixture.&nbsp;Sprinkle top with remaining walnuts.&nbsp;Bake&nbsp; at 350oF&nbsp; for 55 - 60 minutes.&nbsp;Serve warm or at room temperature.<br>\n',10,0,0,1,0,45,13,9,9,15,9,60,'../files/recipes/brownies.JPG','2014-05-22 04:30:31',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(81,'Pecan Tarts','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350 oF.<div><br></div><div>Crust: cream cheese, margarine, flour and cream together, divide dough into 2 balls and separate each ball into 12 small balls, press dough into small cupcake.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Filling: eggs, sugar, margarine, salt and vanilla. Mix together fill crust with pecan pieces and fill with filling.</div><div><br></div><div>Bake for 15 minutes.&nbsp;</div>\n',6,0,0,0,0,11,16,8,9,12,9,20,'','2014-05-15 06:56:23',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(82,'Mint Cashew','<br>\n','Melt chocolate chips, milk and butter in a&nbsp; double boiler, stir until chocolate is melted,do not boil.<br><br>Remove from heat, and add peppermint essence to taste, then add coarsely chopped cashews. <br><br>Pour&nbsp; into foil-lined 8 x 10 inch pan, and refrigerate until firm. Lift from pan, remove foil, cut into squares.<br><br>Store in airtight container in fridge.<br>\n',10,0,0,0,0,10,13,8,6,15,9,12,'','2014-04-14 13:43:38',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(83,'Calas','<br>\n','In medium bowl mix together the dry ingredients,&nbsp; beat together&nbsp; the rice and eggs. Add the dry ingredients to the rice and eggs. When thoroughly mixed,&nbsp; allow to stand for 15 minutes. Now drop by spoonfuls into deep, hot fat and fry until brown on both sides. Drain on a paper towel.<br><br>Then sprinkle with powered sugar.<br><br>Must be served hot.<br>\n',8,0,0,2,0,80,13,8,8,12,9,10,'../files/recipes/calas.JPG','2014-06-03 03:57:45',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(84,'Spicy Rice','<br>\n','Chop a onion very finely and mince&nbsp; the garlic. In a frying pan, melt butter and over a low heat, saute the onions and garlic for 3 - 4 minutes. Put the rice in a Food Steamer and add the necessary amount of chicken broth. Add poultry seasoning&nbsp; and pour the contents of the frying pan into the rice pot, cover and press the switch.<br><br>While the rice is cooking, mince 4 scallions and when the chime rings, remove the lid and stir in the scallions.<br><br>Serve warm.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,24,13,7,8,7,9,25,'../files/recipes/spice rice.JPG','2014-05-27 07:00:51',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(85,'Croquettes','<br>\n','Heat butter and saute chopped onion slightly, add flour, salt and pepper diluted in milk . Cook the sauce over low heat stirring constantly until it is thick double cream and see the bottom of the pot to move the cream with the spoon.<br><br>Lower it from heat, add the cook wine and ham, toss well.<br><br>Pour batter into a shallow dish and cool well.<br><br>Take the dough by spoonfuls, give form patties and wrap them in beaten egg and bread crumbs.<br><br>Fry until golden brown.<br><br>If you want to make chicken or meat&nbsp; croquettes, you can use this recipe, instead of ham, use mass of meat or chicken, but must be cooked and ground before&nbsp; adding the creamy.<br>\n',10,0,0,0,0,35,7,8,6,12,9,20,'../files/recipes/croketas.jpg','2014-05-09 05:31:33',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(86,'Monkey Bread','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 350 oF<br><br>Melt butter in large sauce pan, meanswhile, add all ingredients except&nbsp; bread. <br><br>Stir all together take off stove. Add bread cut into golf ball size and mix all together and pour into 9 x 11 pan or bundt pan.<br><br>Bake for 30 - 40 minutes <br><br><br>\n	\n	',16,0,0,0,0,12,13,9,9,15,9,15,'../files/recipes/monkey bread.JPG','2014-05-24 12:51:34','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(87,'Pumpkin Bread','<br>\n','Preheat oven at 350oF&nbsp; - Greased&nbsp; 2 pans 9 x5 x3<br><br>In medium bowl mix together flour, baking powder, salt&nbsp; and oats, set aside.<br><br>In a big bowl beat eggs at medium speed with an electric mixer, add pumpkin,&nbsp; sugar, milk, water and oil, mix well.<br><br>Add flour mixture, beating at low speed until blended. Stir in chopped walnut.<br><br>Pour batter into&nbsp; two&nbsp; pans&nbsp; and bake for 70 minutes<br>\n',10,0,0,0,0,19,13,8,9,14,3,90,'../files/recipes/pumpkin bread.jpg','2014-02-12 22:51:05',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(88,'Eclair Cake','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Arrange&nbsp; 1/3 of the crackers&nbsp; on bottom of 13x9 inch baking pan, breaking crackers to fit, if necessary.<br><br>Pour milk into large&nbsp; bowl. Add pudding mixes. Beat&nbsp; with wire whisk 2 minutes. <br>gently stir in whipped topping. Spread 1/2 of the pudding mixture over crackers. Place 1/2&nbsp; of the remaining crackers over pudding;&nbsp; top with remaining pudding mixture and&nbsp; crackers.<br><br>Remove top and foil from frosting container. Microwave frosting in container on High 1 minute or until pourable. Spread&nbsp; evenly over crackers.<br><br>Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.&nbsp; Cut into squares to serve.<br><br>Garnish with strawberries.<br>\n	\n	',18,0,0,0,0,16,13,8,8,13,6,20,'../files/recipes/eclear cake.JPG','2014-04-27 16:56:55','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(107,'Cornbread','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF.&nbsp;&nbsp; Greased loaf pan a&nbsp; 9 x 5 x 3 , set aside.<br><br>In a medium bowl combine all ingredients, pour into greased pan.<br><br>Bake for 24 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean,&nbsp; cool in pan on wire racks, remove from pan and cool completely.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,20,7,8,9,14,9,25,'../files/recipes/corn bread.JPG','2014-06-05 01:37:51',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(109,'Cuban Empanadas','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In a big bowl sift flour, salt and sugar,&nbsp; add cold butter, work it with 2 knife or your fingertips until is like a fine crumb,&nbsp; in the center of dough add beating egg&nbsp; and cook wine. Mix well in circle form<br><br>Roll dough into pieces and extend with a rolling pin on a surface with a little flour until thin, and a circle form. In the middle of circle put the filling you want (guava, coconut, ground meet, ground ham, etc). <br><br>Seal the edges with a fork or a dough press set.&nbsp; And fry in hot oil until browned.<br>\n	\n	',10,0,0,0,0,24,7,8,8,12,6,20,'../files/recipes/cuban empanadas.JPG','2014-05-29 21:30:08','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(90,'Pasta with Beef','<br>\n','Heat 2 tablespoons oil in a medium skillet over medium heat; add beef. Cook, stirring &nbsp;until beef is cooked through. Remove from skillet and drain on paper towels.<br><br>Heat remaining oil in same skillet; Begin heating water for pasta. Add carrot to skillet, cook, stirring, for 4 minutes. Add broccoli and garlic to skillet, cook, stirring, for 2 minutes longer.<br><br>Cook pasta according to package directions.&nbsp; While pasta cooking, add beef broth, basil and cheese to skillet. Stir to combine. Return beef to skillet. Reduce heat and simmer for 4 minutes. Drain pasta. Place in a large serving bowl Top with beef and vegetable mixture.<br><br>Serve immediately.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,21,7,7,6,4,9,15,'../files/recipes/pasta with beef.JPG','2014-06-01 21:50:29',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(91,'Chocolate Cheese Pie','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Heat oven to 350&nbsp; oF<br><br>In large mixer bowl combine cream cheese and sugar, beat&nbsp; well. <br><br>Blend in cocoa, scraping sides of bowl and beaters frequently. Add eggs and vanilla; blend well. Blend in whipping cream.<br><br>Pour into crust.&nbsp; Bake 35 or 40 minutes.<br><br>Center will be soft but will set upon cooling.<br><br>Cool to room temperature. Cover and chill several hours or overnight.<br><br>Garnish with pie filling .<br>\n	\n	',8,0,0,0,0,15,13,8,9,15,9,20,'../files/recipes/chocolate pay.JPG','2014-04-16 01:43:19','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(127,'Boston Cream Pie','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350 oF &nbsp;- Grease a 9 inch round cake pan.<br><br>Beat together 3 egg yolks and 1 teaspoon vanilla at medium speed until blended. Beat in 1/4 cup of sugar until very thick and pale, set aside.<br><br>Using clean, dry beaters, beat together 3 egg whites and pinch of salt at medium speed until very soft peaks form. Gradually beat in remaining sugar until stiff, but not dry, peaks form.<br><br>Fold yolk mixture into egg whites. Sift 3/4 cup flour over mixture; fold in gently.&nbsp; Do not over mix. Pour batter into prepared pan.<br><br>Bake cake for 25 minutes or until top springs back when lightly pressed.<br><br>Loosen cake by running a metal spatula around sides of pan. Invert cake onto a wire rack. Remove pan, leaving waxed paper on cake. Turn cake right-side up. Cool completely on rack.<br><br>Meanwhile, prepare filling. In a saucepan, mix together 1/2 cup sugar and 1/4 cup flour. Gradually whisk in milk, then 6 egg yolks, 2 teaspoon vanilla and pinch of salt. Bring to a boil for 1 minute, whisking constantly. Strain through a fine sieve into a bowl. Press plastic wrap on surface. Chill for 30 minutes.<br><br>Using a serrated knife, cut cake horizontally in half. Carefully remove waxed paper. Place bottom layer on a serving plate. Spread evenly with filling. Top with remaining cake layer.<br><br>To prepare glaze, in a saucepan, bring remaining sugar, corn syrup and water to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar has dissolved. Remove from heat. Add chocolate; let stand for 1 minute, Whisk until smooth. Gradually pour glaze over cake, allowing it to drip down sides. Let stand until glaze sets.<br><br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,27,13,8,9,13,8,85,'','2014-04-30 04:50:58',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(93,'Butter Pecan Square','<br>\n','Preheat&nbsp; oven to 350 oF.&nbsp; Grease square pan, 8x8x2 or 9x9x2 inches.<br><br>In small mixer&nbsp; bowl cream butter, egg,&nbsp; sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy. Blend in flour.<br><br>Stir in 1 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup pecans.&nbsp; Spread into prepared pan.<br><br>Bake 25 - 30 minutes or until lightly browned. Remove from oven. Immediately&nbsp; sprinkle with remaining chips.<br><br>Let stand 5 - 10 minutes or until chips soften;&nbsp; spread evenly.<br><br>Immediately sprinkle with remaining pecans; press gently onto chocolate.<br><br>Cool completely. Cut into squares.<br>\n',16,0,0,0,0,10,13,8,9,15,9,15,'','2014-03-18 03:48:22',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(100,'Marble Cheesecake','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 325 0F<br><br>In a small bowl,&nbsp; combine crumbs and butter. Mix well. Press into bottom of a 8 inc springform pan. Wrap outside of pan with heavy-duty foil. Set aside.<br><br>In a large mixing bowl, using an electric mixer set on medium speed, beat cream cheese and sugar for 2 minutes. Beat in sour&nbsp; cream, flour, and vanilla. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.<br><br>Transfer 1 1/2 cups of batter to a small bowl. Stir in chocolate. Spread half of vanilla batter over crust.&nbsp; Top with half of chocolate batter. Spoon remaining vanilla batter over chocolate batter. Top with remaining chocolate batter.<br><br>Using a knife, gently swirl batters together. Place pan in a shallow roasting pan; add enough boiling water to come half way up sides of springform pan. Bake until just set, about 1 hour 15 minutes.<br><br>Place pan on a wire rack and cool to room temperature.<br><br>Cover and chill for 4 hours.<br>\n',16,0,0,0,0,10,13,8,9,13,9,75,'','2014-03-31 02:36:23',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(98,'French Toast','<br>\n','In a shallow&nbsp; bowl, using a wire whisk,&nbsp; beat the egg and egg white until foamy. Add the milk, vanilla, cinnamon, and nutmeg. Beat well , set aside.<br><br>Preheat oven to 200 oF.<br><br>Lightly spray a large nonstick skillet with vegatable cooking spray; heat over medium heat. Dip 4 of the bread slices into the egg mixture, turning to coat and draining excess back into the dish.<br><br>Place bread slices in prepared skillet.&nbsp; Cook until golden brown,&nbsp; turning once, about 1-2 minutes per side. <br><br>Transfer cooked slices to a plate; keep&nbsp; warm in oven. Dip remaining&nbsp; slices in egg mixture; cook as directed. Spray skillet with vegetable cooking spray as needed.<br><br>Divide french toast among serving plates. Sprinkle lightly with cinnamon sugar and top with maple syrup.<br><br>Serve immediately.<br><br>Any type of bread works well in this recipe.<br><br><br><br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,28,16,9,6,14,9,10,'../files/recipes/french toast.jpg','2014-05-16 05:26:23','',0,0,1,0,0,0,NULL),(97,'Turtle Cheesecake','<br>','Place&nbsp; caramels and evaporated milk in a heavy saucepan.&nbsp; heat over medium low heat, stirring continually, until&nbsp; smooth, about 5 minutes.&nbsp; Stir&nbsp; in 1/2 cup&nbsp; chopped pecans. Pour into piecrust.<br><br>Combine cream cheese, sour cream and milk in a blender. Process until smooth. <br>add pudding mix; process for about 30 seconds longer.<br><br>Pour pudding mixture over caramel layer, covering evenly. Chill, loosely&nbsp; covered, until set, about 15 minutes.<br><br>Drizzle&nbsp; fudge topping over pudding layer in a decorative pattern. Sprinkle top of cake with remaining pecans. <br><br>Chill,&nbsp; loosely covered, until serving time.<br><br><br>',12,0,0,0,0,19,13,9,6,13,9,30,'','2014-05-19 15:31:29',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(99,'Cocoa Frosting','<br>\n','In small mixer bowl combine all ingredients; beat to spreading consistency.<br><br>About 1 cup frosting.<br>\n',1,0,0,0,0,7,13,9,8,14,9,5,'','2014-03-16 05:18:54',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(101,'Honeyluscious Chicken','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 400 oF<br><br>Combine mustard and honey in a small bowl. Stir in dill and orange peel.<br><br>Line a baking sheet with foil. Place chicken, skin-side down, on prepared pan. Brush sauce on top of chicken; coat well.<br><br>Turn chicken over. gently pull back skin and brush meat with sauce. <br>gently pull skin back over sauce.<br><br>Brush skin with remaining sauce. Bake until juices run clear when thickest portion of meat is pierced with a knife,&nbsp; about 45 minutes.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,23,11,8,9,16,9,35,'../files/recipes/Honeyluscious chicken.jpg','2014-03-31 01:55:18',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(102,'Chocolate Snack','<br>\n','Heat oven to 350 oF.&nbsp; <br><br>Grease&nbsp; and flour square pan, 8x8x2 inches. In small mixing bowl&nbsp; combine flour, sugar, cocoa,&nbsp; and salt. Add water, oil, vinegar and vanilla; beat until smooth.<br><br>Pour into prepared pan.&nbsp;&nbsp; Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.<br><br>Bake 35 - 40 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. <br><br>Cool in pan on wire rack. Cut into squares .<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,10,13,9,9,15,9,15,'','2014-04-04 13:21:00',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(104,'Earthquake Cake','	\n		<span id=\"docs-internal-guid-2d726892-82ce-c7b1-1de9-14eb481088ff\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Almost like an earthquake this cake emerged from the oven heat a winter night, all expected to see a beautiful cake almost flat, when suddenly the dough began to sprout up hollows doing dual effects of color on the surface.</span></p><br><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"></span><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Very well resembles an earthquake of fantasy in a land of chocolate and marshmallows, there appeared his name, but left the question of taste, needless to say that has nothing to do with the appearance, nor the bitterness that leaves a natural disaster; is a nice blend of chocolate combined with grated coconut and pecans with an indescribable sweet taste.</span></p><br><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\"></span><span style=\"font-size: 15px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;\">The Earthquake Cake is a simple recipe with a bold combination of flavors, suitable for any night of desserts or party guests simple bold tastes, is a proposal out of classism and a new design of the pastry.</span></span>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 350 oF.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Grease one 9 x 13 pan, set aside.<br><br>Spread pecans and coconut on the bottom of pan. In medium bowl prepare cake mix as directed on package and pour into pan.<br><br>Melt together cream cheese, butter and sugar and pour&nbsp; on top of cake batter.<br><br>Bake for 1 hour or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.<br>\n	\n	',20,0,0,2,0,120,13,8,9,13,9,5,'../files/recipes/earthquake cake.JPG','2014-06-06 09:34:45','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2013-11-27 13:00:04'),(105,'Pumpkin Cake Roll','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 375oF&nbsp; - Grease&nbsp; 15 x 10 inch jelly-roll pan; line with wax paper. Grease and flour paper. Sprinkle towel with powdered sugar.<br><br>Combine flour, cinnamon and salt in small bowl.&nbsp; Beat eggs and sugar in large mixer bowl until thick. Beat in pumpkin.&nbsp; Stir in flour mixture. Spread evenly into pan. Sprinkle with nuts.<br><br>Bake for 15 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Immediately loosen&nbsp; and turn&nbsp; cake onto prepared towel. Carefully peel off paper.&nbsp; Roll up cake and towel, starting with narrow end.&nbsp; Cool in wire rack.<br><br>Beat&nbsp; cream cheese, 1 cup powered sugar, butter and vanilla in small mixer bowl until smooth.&nbsp; Carefully unroll cake, remove towel. Spread cream cheese mixture over cake. Roll cake. Wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate at least one hour.<br><br>Sprinkle with powdered&nbsp; sugar&nbsp; before serving.<br>\n	\n	',10,0,0,0,0,5,13,9,9,13,3,35,'../files/recipes/pumpking cake roll.JPG','2014-03-26 00:50:03','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(106,'Heavenly Cake','<br>\n','<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\n  <o:RelyOnVML></o:RelyOnVML>\n  <o:AllowPNG></o:AllowPNG>\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:WordDocument>\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\n  <w:TrackMoves></w:TrackMoves>\n  <w:TrackFormatting></w:TrackF