w Roman\";\n	mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;\n	mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;}\n</style>\n<![endif]-->\n\n\n\n\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",\"serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">Preheat oven to 350 oF&nbsp; and grease 3 round&nbsp; 8 inch pan.<br style=\"mso-special-character:line-break\">\nPrepare cake mix in medium bowl as\ndirect on package and pour into pans, bake&nbsp; for 25 minutes or .until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire racks 10 minutes, remove from pans. Cool completely on wire rack. <br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; line-height: normal;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",\"serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">Combine pudding mix powder with\npineapple in medium bowl. Gently stir in whipped topping.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;line-height:\nnormal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;line-height:115%;font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",\"serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" roman\";mso-ansi-language:en-us;mso-fareast-language:=\"\" en-us;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa\"=\"\">Spread this mixture between cake layers and top.\nChill in the refrigerator at least 1 hour before serving. Garnish with strawberries <br></span></p>\n',12,0,0,0,0,17,13,9,9,13,7,45,'','2014-05-05 19:42:16',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(112,'Dobosh Tropical','	\n		<div>Very often, the most exquisite recipes, have taken the name their creators, an example of this is the most famous Hungarian cake, made-up in 1884 by famous confectioner Jozsef C. Dobosh. It is a special cake containing five thin layers of spongy dough, between there spread with butter chocolate creams filling, and finished with a cover of soft of caramel.</div><div><br></div><div>The cake was first introduced in the National General Exhibition of Budapest in 1885 and acquired its reputation because its presence at this event, and tried by Franz Joseph I, Emperor of Austria and Elisabeth of Wittelsbach, Empress Consort, known as Sissi. After touring Europe and the West Indies through migration, preparing the cake was adapting to new ways and conditions of cooking, without losing its essential nature.</div><div><br></div><div>Nitza Villapol, the Cuban cooking teacher, published in 1981, nearly a century of being created the original recipe, a variation that allowed us to savor this delicacy from a new perspective and called it, Dobosh Tropical, keeping the name its creator and master introducing the difference of the tropics, it does claim to the residents and visitors, by the consumption of cold foods and quick to do.</div><div><br></div><div>We present a new variant of the original recipe: The Tropical Dobosh, created by Nitza in 1980. In this desert, she replaced the spongy dough by cookies dipped in fresh milk, and finished with a caramel cover, as Dobosh made hundred years ago.</div><div><br></div><div>We offer a desert to easy and quick preparation. You can enjoy this recipe with friends at a party or just hanging out, without getting tired.</div>\n	\n	','	\n		Coat bottom and sides of a 9 inch springform pan&nbsp; with clear wrap.<br><br>In a medium bowl&nbsp; cream the butter, add sugar gradually until a very soft cream, add one by one the eggs and then vanilla.<br><br>Placing a first layer of cookies in milk slightly wet. Each layer should be about 10 cookies.<br><br>Divide into 6 parts cream and place a cookies on the first part.&nbsp; Repeat until you have 7 layers of cookies and&nbsp; 6 layers of cream.<br><br>Squeeze a bit of clear wrap so that the cream is firm in the cookies.&nbsp; Freeze&nbsp; until firm, almost&nbsp; 2 hours. Then unmold it and takes&nbsp; up clear wrap.<br>\n	\n	',10,0,0,0,0,140,13,9,8,13,6,15,'../files/recipes/dobosh.JPG','2014-05-29 12:25:38','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2013-12-04 13:00:02'),(113,'Cheese Fritter or Bunuelos','<br>\n','In a big bowl sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt. Add cheese and beaten eggs.<br><br>Mix well all together and make number 8 shape.<br><br>Fry in hot oil until golden.&nbsp; <br><br>Serve with syrup.<br>\n',10,0,0,0,0,51,7,9,8,15,9,25,'../files/recipes/bizcochos.JPG','2014-05-11 11:33:44',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(114,'Vizcaina Cod','<br>\n','Soak the cod 10 hours before usage. Change water and cool until tender, remove from water and shred into large pieces.<br><br>In a flat pan in the bottom place the potatoes cut in slices, cover with cod, onions rings, crushed garlic, green peppers strips, water,&nbsp; cooking wine, oil and tomatoes sauce, leave it on medium heat until potatoes are cooked.<br><br>Serve with fried bread and garnish with red peppers.<br>\n',8,0,0,1,0,64,7,8,6,8,9,60,'../files/recipes/Vizcaina cod.JPG','2014-05-29 01:22:26',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(115,'Black Beans','<br>\n','Wash beans and soak it in a pressure cooker for 1 hour,&nbsp; put them to cook in same water until tender, about 20 minute. In a skillet heat vegetal oil saute ground onion, garlic and pepper.<br><br>Add a cup of beans in the skillet and mash well. Pour into the casserole with remaining beans. Add salt, black pepper, oregano, cumin, bay leaf and sugar.<br><br>Boil 20 minutes over low heat, add vinegar and cook wine and let uncovered&nbsp; until a medium thickened.<br><br>Just before serving add olive oil.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,45,7,7,3,14,9,60,'../files/recipes/black beans.jpg','2014-05-22 03:07:51',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(116,'Honey Buttercream Frosting','<br>\n','With an electric mixer, beat softened butter, honey and cream cheese in a large bowl until smooth. Gradually add in powdered&nbsp; sugar, beating until mixture is smooth and creamy. If necessary,&nbsp; add milk, 1 teaspoon at a time, until mixture is spreading consistency.<br>\n',10,0,0,0,0,148,13,9,8,3,6,5,'','2014-05-21 23:20:33',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(117,'Onion Rings','	\n		Onion<br>luminous flask,<br>petal by petal<br>your beauty was formed,<br>glass flakes will increased<br>and secrecy of the dark earth<br>is your belly of dew ....<br><br>Neruda. <br>Ode to the Onion, 1954.<br><br>The poets have sung for generations; the people, since immemorial time, have satisfied their hunger with it, She have played a major role in Egyptian mummification, she&nbsp; ornament the gardens of Pompeii, she is&nbsp; inscribed in hieroglyphics, and continues present through&nbsp; centuries in the international gastronomy.&nbsp; Whom could speak, only about the onion.<br><br>She, as simple and beautiful, full of medicinal properties, appetite stimulant, and one of the main spices in the kitchen, with its unique flavor appears in countless dishes. <br>Native from Asia and disseminated throughout the world is part of a host of recipes. <br>We present it today fried, grilled, raw, as a condiment, in salads, because we want share with us the taste of French onions, whoâ€™s only secret is to cut into wide strips before breading it. <br><br>Like to taste them!<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br>\n	\n	','	\n		Cut onions into rings 1/2 inch slices , and separate&nbsp; into rings. Set aside.<br><br>Pass the onions rings in milk and flour.<br><br>Fry in hot oil until golden brown<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,1,0,33,7,8,6,14,9,15,'../files/recipes/onion rings.JPG','2014-06-08 19:34:36','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2013-12-11 13:00:01'),(118,'Chocolate and Raspberry Bars','<br>\n','Heat oven to 375oF<br><br>Sift four, cocoa, baking soda and salt into a bowl.<br><br>In an electric mixer on medium-high, Beat butter in bowl until creamy. Add sugars, beat until fluffy. Beat in egg. Add vanilla.<br><br>On low speed, beat in flour mixture. Fold in chips. Spread batter into 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.<br><br>Bake for 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack.<br><br>Spread bar with frosting. Stir jam&nbsp; in small cup until smooth. Spoon into small plastic bag; snip small corner. Pipe jam in straight lines lengthwise over top of&nbsp; frosting. Draw sharp knife crosswise through lines, alternating direction. Refrigerate to set. Cut into bars.<br>\n',36,0,0,0,0,12,13,9,9,15,9,20,'','2014-05-26 19:10:49',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(119,'Chicken Wraps','<br>\n','In a big bowl combine coleslow mix, sliced medium red pepper, green onions and cilantro in a food processor;cover and process with several on/of pulses until finely chopped.<br><br>Transfer to slaw mixture, cooked chicken tender and teriyaki sauce to a large skillet. Cook and stir over medium heat until heated through.<br><br>Spoon slow mixture and chicken onto 8 bib lettuce leaves, roll up.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,13,13,8,8,5,9,20,'','2014-04-30 16:18:02',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(124,'Pineapple Chicken Stir Fry','<br>\n','Drain pineapple, reserve 1/4 cup juice. Stir together, in small bowl reserve juice, water, 1/3 soy sauce, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, red pepper and minced garlic; set aside.<br><br>Combine in medium bowl chicken with remaining cornstarch and soy sauce. Heat oil in wok or non-stick large skillet over medium-high heat.Add chicken and stir-fry 5 minutes or until lightly browned.Add broccoli florets, red pepper chunks,carrot thinly sliced diagonally stir-fry 5 minutes or until just tender. Add reserved soy sauce mixture;&nbsp; cook, stirring,until sauce boils and thickens.Stir in pineapple chunks and heat through.<br><br>Serve over <a href=\"http://recipescookbook.org/recipe/white-rice\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">white rice</a>.<br><br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,13,13,7,6,14,9,30,'../files/recipes/pinaple chicken stir fried.JPG','2014-05-14 17:06:42',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(120,'Tres Leches Cake','<br>\n','<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\n  <o:RelyOnVML></o:RelyOnVML>\n  <o:AllowPNG></o:AllowPNG>\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\n</xml><!