-alt:auto;\nline-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",\"serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">Frosting:</span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"mso-margin-top-alt:auto;mso-margin-bottom-alt:auto;\nline-height:normal\"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:\" times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\",\"serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" roman\"\"=\"\">At medium speed beat cream, sugar,\nespresso and whiskey until stiff peaks form. Using serrated knife horizontal\ncut 1 cake layer in half. Place 1 half-layer on cake plate; spread with 1&nbsp; cup\nfrosting. Top with uncut cake layer; spread with 1 1/4 cups frosting. Top with remaining\nhalf-layer; spread top and side with remaining frosting. Sprinkle with sugar\ncrystal, if desired.</span></p>\n',16,0,0,0,0,37,13,7,9,13,10,20,'../files/recipes/Chocolate Cake.JPG','2014-05-14 22:35:56',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(143,'Rustic Lasagna','<br>\n','Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions but do not add salt.<br><br>While noodles are cooking, preheat oven to 350ÂºF. Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking dish with vegetable cooking spray; set aside.<br><br>In a small bowl, combine tomato sauce, garlic and oregano. Mix well. In a medium bowl, combine broccoli, carrot, ricotta, and parmesan. Mix we<br><br>Drain noodles in a colander.&nbsp; Spread 1/2 cup of tomato sauce in bottom of prepared dish. Place 3 noodles on top of tomato sauce. Spread half of broccoli mixture over noodles. Spoon 1/2 cup of tomato sauce over broccoli; place 3 noodles on top. <br>spread with remaining broccoli mixture; top with 1/2&nbsp; cup of tomato sauce.<br><br>Top with remaining noodles and tomato sauce; sprinkle mozzarella over top. Bake until bubbling, about 45 minutes. Place on a wire rack and cool for about 15 minutes; cut into squares.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,29,10,8,9,4,9,75,'../files/recipes/lassagna rustica.JPG','2014-06-03 12:29:35',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(144,'Fried Eggplant','<br>\n','Peel eggplant, cut into thin slices. Soak the slices for 10 minutes in salted water.<br><br>Dip eggplant slices in beaten eggs and bread crumbs. <br><br>Fry in hot oil until browned.<br>\n',15,0,1,0,0,18,7,8,6,14,9,20,'../files/recipes/fried eggplant.jpg','2014-05-20 04:53:38',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(145,'Juice Punch','<br>\n','In a punch bowl stir juice&nbsp; fruit and ginger ale. Add dry ice<br>\n',15,0,0,0,0,11,7,9,8,11,4,5,'','2014-04-18 09:10:19',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(146,'Orange Punch','<br>\n','Make ice with juice on a plastic mold.<br><br>In a punch bowl stir juice fruit,&nbsp; ginger ale and orange fruit.<br><br><br>Add ice. Enjoy<br><br><br>\n',15,0,0,0,0,11,7,9,8,11,6,10,'','2014-05-08 22:12:50',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(147,'Pico de Gallo Sauce','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Finely chop tomatoes, onion; snip fresh cilantro and seeded and finely chop.serrano chile pepper.<br><br>In a medium bowl combine tomatoes, onion, cilantro, serrano chile pepper and a dash sugar. Cover, chill several hours.<br><br>...serve like dip with tortilla chips, carrot and celery sticks<br>\n	\n	',15,0,0,0,0,10,8,7,8,3,6,10,'../files/recipes/pico de gallo.jpg','2014-02-11 03:43:27','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(148,'Puppy Chow','<br>\n','Pour cereal into large bowl, set aside.<br><br>In 1-quart microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips, peanut butter and margarine Microwave on HIGH 1 to 11/2 minutes or until smooth, stirring after 1 minute. Stir in vanilla.<br><br>Pour chocolate mixture over cereals, stirring until all pieces are evenly coated. Pour cereal mixture into a large, resealable bag with powdered sugar. Seal securely, and shake until all pieces are well coated.<br>&nbsp;<br>Spread on waxed paper to cool.<br><br>Makes 9 cups<br>.<br>\n',15,0,0,0,0,10,13,7,2,15,6,10,'../files/recipes/puppy chow.JPG','2014-04-15 23:25:32',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(149,'Cheese Straws','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 375oF<br><br>Sift flour and baking powder into a bowl. Cut in butter and cheese as for pie crust, using a pastry blender or two knives.<br><br>Add water and mix well.<br><br>Forms straws on ungreased&nbsp; cookie sheets, Cut into desired lengths.<br><br>Bake 8 - l0 minutes.&nbsp; Cool in pan on wire racks.<br><br><br><br><br>\n',30,0,0,0,0,13,13,9,9,12,6,10,'','2014-03-16 05:08:56',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(150,'Pineapple Salad','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In a salad bowl mix 2 handfuls spinach, sliced cucumber, tidbits pineapple, cooked shrimp and cashews<br><br>Toss well with olive oil, cider vinegar and salt.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,11,9,8,8,10,9,10,'../files/recipes/pinapple salad.JPG','2014-04-25 02:08:32','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(151,'Pizza Salad','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In a salad bowl combine baby arugula, cherry tomatoes, cheese, sliced mushrooms, sliced red and green pepper and sliced black olives.<br><br>Toss well with olive oil and cider vinegar. Enjoy.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,12,13,8,8,10,9,10,'../files/recipes/pizza salad.JPG','2014-04-27 14:56:58','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(152,'Turkey Burgers','<br>\n','Heat barbecue grill to medium. Tear bread in small pieces into a medium bowl. Add milk and soak about 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Shape into four 1-in-thick patties.<br><br>Coat patties with nonstick cooking spray. Grill 15 minutes, turning once, until a thermometer inserted in center registers to 165oF<br><br><br>Serve with lettuce, tomatoes and onion.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,12,13,8,5,14,9,25,'','2014-05-28 15:00:37',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(162,'Sauce Wrap','<br>','<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\n  <o:RelyOnVML></o:RelyOnVML>\n  <o:AllowPNG></o:AllowPNG>\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:WordDocument>\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\n  <w:TrackMoves></w:TrackMoves>\n  <w:TrackFormatting></w:TrackFormatting>\n  <w:PunctuationKerning></w:PunctuationKerning>\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas></w:ValidateAgainstSchemas>\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid