ctions.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"> Combine ricotta, 1 1/2 cups mozzarella, seasoning, salt and pepper;\nreserve. <br></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">Coat nonstick skillet with cooking spray; place over medium heat. Add\ngarlic; cook until softened, 2 minutes. Stir in both jars of sauce, crumbles, vinegar\nand 1 tbs Parmesan. Cook, stirring, until heated through; removes from heat.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\">\nCoat13\"x9\" baking dish with cooking spray. Spread 1/2 cup sauce\nmixture over bottom of dish. Top with 3 noodles, 1 1/2 cups cheese mixture and 1 1/2\ncups sauce mixture;<span style=\"mso-spacerun:yes\">&nbsp; </span>repeat layers two\nmore times. Top with remaining noodles. Spread with remaining sauce mixture. Coat\nsheet of foil with cooking spray; place over lasagna, coated side down.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"> Bake 30\nminutes or until beginning to bubble. Uncover; sprinkle with remaining\nmozzarella and Parmesan. Bake until cheese melts, 10 minutes.</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"> Let stand 10\nminutes before cutting</p>\n',8,0,0,0,0,15,10,8,9,4,9,110,'../files/recipes/Less Fat Mealty Lasagna.jpg','2014-05-15 01:34:18',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(137,'Shrimp Tortellini Marinada','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Cook tortellini following package directions.<br><br>Cut&nbsp; tomatoes into halves. Preheat large saute pan on medium high 3 minutes. Place oil in pan, then add shrimp, cook 2 minutes or just until shrimp turn pink. Stir marinara sauce into shrimp, then stir in remaining ingredients and cook until thoroughly. heated.<br><br>Drain tortellini,, and stir into marinara sauce.<br><br>Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,10,10,8,6,4,9,25,'','2014-04-06 07:47:26','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(138,'Pizza Stick','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In a skillet heat up tortilla.In a heated tortilla place 1 slices of cheese,&nbsp; 3 slices pepperoni and a teaspoon sauce.About 1 1/2 inches from the bottom edge of the tortilla. <br><br>Fold the bottom of the tortilla over the fillings, then fold insides to close off edges, continue rolling tortilla, dampen final edge and press to seal.<br><br>Fry in heated oil until golden and crispy.<br><br>Serve with additional sauce for dipping.<br>\n	\n	',10,1,1,0,0,7,7,8,6,14,9,15,'../files/recipes/pizza sticks.JPG','2014-05-05 15:12:16','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(142,'New Chocolate  Frosting','<br>','Melt butter in a 4qt. pan on low heat.Add in the cocoa and mix on medium speed. Slowly add in sugar and milk ( alternating between them) while mixing on medium speed. Add in the coffee, then the vanilla. Mix on fast speed until smooth. Spread on cake while frosting is still&nbsp; warm.<br>',8,0,0,0,0,16,13,7,6,13,9,10,'','2014-03-17 16:08:50',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(139,'Party Mix','<br>\n','In large microwave-safe bowl on High&nbsp; melt margarine. Stir in seasonings. Gradually add cereals, nuts, pretzels and bagel chips; stir to coat evenly.<br><br>Microwave on High 5 - 6 minutes, stirring thoroughly with rubber spatula every 2 minutes. While stirring, make sure to scrape sides and bottom of bowl. Spread on absorbent paper to cool.&nbsp; <br><br>Store in airtight container.<br>\n',30,0,0,0,0,11,13,9,2,12,6,70,'../files/recipes/party mix.JPG','2014-06-02 19:26:17',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(140,'Phillip Potatoes','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF<br><br>Break up potatoes, but do not thaw completely. Combine soup, sour cream, cheese, onion, salt and pepper, stir in potatoes mix.<br><br>Put in a greased 9\" x 13\" baking dish.<br><br>Stir together melted butter and crushed cereal and arrange over potatoes mix.<br><br>Bake 50 minutes or until bubbly and potatoes are tender.<br>\n',10,0,1,1,0,27,13,8,9,14,5,75,'../files/recipes/phillips potatoes.JPG','2014-05-21 00:51:57',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(141,'Layered Salad with Terragon Dressing','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In bowl whisk oil, sour cream, vinegar, shallots, sugar, tarragon, salt and pepper until combined; cover and refrigerate. Heat dry skillet over medium heat. Add pecans;cook,stirring,until lightly browned, 3-4 minutes. Remove from skillet; reserve. Toss salad greens with chicory.Transfer 6 cups greens to large bowl. Top with beets, blue&nbsp; cheese, carrots and remaining greens. Drizzle with dressing. sprinkle with pecans just before serving<br>\n	\n	',8,0,0,0,0,7,13,7,6,10,9,30,'','2014-03-15 10:36:58','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(155,'Spring Stew','<br>\n','In a medium-size saucepan, heat oil over medium-high heat.Add celery,carrot,red pepper and scallions and cook, stirring,5 minutes. Add potato,salt,pepper and thyme.Cook an additional 2 minutes.<br>Stir in 2 cups of the milk and 1/2&nbsp; cup of water. Cover and bring to a simmer. Reduce heat to medium low and simmer for 12 minutes or until vegetables are tender.<br>Once vegetables are softener, stir in corn and crab-meat. <br>In small dish,stir the remaining tablespoon milk into the cornstarch. Add to pot,stirring,cook 3 minutes or until thickened. Cool slightly, then serve.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,8,13,7,6,14,5,20,'../files/recipes/Spring Stew.JPG','2014-03-16 14:48:33',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(156,'Fresh Pineapple Sundaes','<br>\n','Twist crown from pineapple. Cut pineapple lengthwise in quarters. Cut fruit from shell. Core and cut pineapple into chunks. Divide among eight 1 cup souffle or dessert bowls.<br>In blender, mix milk and dry pudding,40 seconds (or beat together until blended). Transfer to a bowl and chill 10 minutes.Spoon evenly over pineapple. Top with nuts and coconut.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,18,13,7,7,4,9,10,'','2014-04-13 09:40:08',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(157,'Squash Rice Pilaf','<br>\n','Cook rice.<br>Meanwhile, in a large nonstick skillet melt butter over medium heat.Add garlic&nbsp; and coriander; cook, stirring occasionally, 1 minute. Add leek, zucchini, squash, salt and pepper; cook stirring occasionally, until softened, 3-4 minutes. Add orange juice; cook 30 seconds. Stir in rice,zest and parsley; heat through, about 1 minute. transfer to serving bowl.<br><br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,13,13,7,6,7,9,25,'','2014-06-04 09:29:57',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(158,'Spinach and Walnut Salad','<br>\n','In small bowl combine vinegar, juice, soy sauce, salt and pepper; gradually whisk in oil. Stir in parsley and shallot finely chopped. In bowl toss spinach&nbsp; with onion thinly sliced. Peeled and cut into segments an orange and cut tomato into thin wedges. <br><br>Arrange orange and tomato over spinach; sprinkle&nbsp; with walnuts. Stir dressing; drizzle over salad and&nbsp; gently toss.<br>\n',6,0,0,1,0,53,13,7,8,10,9,20,'../files/recipes/Spinach and Walnut Salad.JPG','2014-05-22 04:35:56',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(159,'Chocolate Swirl Cheesecake','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF -- Coat 9 inch spring-form pan with cooking spray. Wrap outside, including bottom of pan, with heavy-duty foil.<br><br>Crust: in blender process cookies until finely ground. Transfer to bowl;combine with butter. Press into bottom and&nbsp; 1/2&nbsp; inch up side of pan. Bake 10 minutes; set aside on rack.<br><br>Cake: At high speed beat cheese and sugar until smooth. Reduce speed to low;&nbsp; beat in egg substitute, sour cream and vanilla.Increase speed to medium high; beat 5 minutes. In bowl stir cocoa into water until smooth, stir in 1 1/2 cups batter until combined. Pour half of remaining plain batter into crust. By spoonfuls drop half of chocolate mixture onto batter in pan. Top with remaining plain batter and spoonfuls of chocolate mixture. Pull knife through batter to create swirls. Place pan in roasting pan; fill roasting pan with hot water halfway up side of spring-form pan. <br><br>Bake 1 hour or until center is set. Remove from water; remove foil. Run knife around edge of cake. Cool on rack 1 1/2 hours; refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Remove side of pan; transfer to serving plate.<br>\n',16,0,0,0,0,13,13,8,9,13,6,90,'','2014-05-08 20:06:06',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(160,'Crispy Chicken Breast','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF.&nbsp; Coat 13 x 9inch baking dish with cooking spray, set aside.<br><br>Crush cornflakes cereal and place in shallow dish or pan, set aside. In medium mixing bowl, beat egg and milk slightly. Add flour, salt and pepper. Mix until smooth. Dip chicken in batter. Coat with cereal. Place in single layer, in shallow baking dish. Drizzle with butter.<br><br>Bake about 1 hour or until chicken is tender, no longer pink and juices run clear. Do not cover pan or turn chicken while baking. Serve hot<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,18,16,8,9,16,9,90,'../files/recipes/crispy chicken breast.jpg','2014-05-22 00:07:11',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(161,'Easter Basket Cupcake','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF. Line muffin cups (2 1/2&nbsp; inches diameter) with paper bake cups.<br><br>Stir together sugar,flour,cocoa, baking powder and salt in large bowl. Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla; beat on medium speed of electric mixer 2 minutes. Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin). Fill muffin cups 2/3 full with batter.<br><br>Bake 22 -25 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely.<br><br>To make baskets, frost each cupcake with vanilla frosting. Immediately make nest on top of each cupcake with tinted coconut; place assorted candy in nests.<br><br>For handle, insert wooden pick in each end of strawberry twists; press down into each side cupcake, bending to form handle.<br><br>To tint coconut combine several drops green food color with 3/4 teaspoon water; add to 1- 1/2 cups coconut. Stir until evenly tinted. <br><br><br>\n',30,0,0,0,0,11,16,9,9,15,5,50,'../files/recipes/Easter basket cupcakes.jpg','2014-05-26 23:00:55',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(163,'Italian Wedding Soup','<br>\n','In pot, heat 1 tbs oil over medium-high heat. Add onion, Italian seasoning, 1/2 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper;cook, stirring,&nbsp;until onion is tender, 2-3 minutes. Add meatballs; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned, 3-4 minutes. Add broth and 2 cups of water;bring to a boil. Add pasta and cook until tender, 10 minutes.Stir in spinach and cook until heated through,1-2 minutes. If desired,serve topped with shredded parmesan cheese.\n',4,0,0,0,0,13,10,9,6,4,9,30,'../files/recipes/italian wedding soup.JPG','2014-05-16 07:17:51',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(164,'Easter Pie','<br>\n','In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy;gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth. Add cold water and pudding mix; on low speed, beat until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spoon 1/2 of filling into pie crust. Place chocolate eggs evenly over filling. Top with remaining filling.<div><br></div><div>Chill 3 hours. &nbsp;Garnish as desired.</div><div><br></div><div>Refrigerate leftovers.</div><div><br></div><div>For young children, use holiday marshmallow candies or other soft candies.</div>\n',8,0,0,0,0,9,13,8,8,13,5,10,'../files/recipes/easter pie.jpg','2014-04-21 02:38:08',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(165,'Potato Salad','<br>\n','Cut potatoes in cubed and cook&nbsp; in lightly salted water with lemon juice for 15 minutes or until just tender; drain.<br><br>Cook eggs until hard and cut in slice onion and eggs; diced green pepper and pimiento. <br><br>In large serving bowl, combine cold potatoes and remaining ingredients. Toss gently.<br><br>Refrigerate to chill.&nbsp; Enjoy<br><br><br>I use low calorie mayonnaise.<br><br><br><br>\n',10,0,0,0,0,19,7,8,6,10,9,20,'../files/recipes/potato salad.jpeg','2014-05-24 01:36:24',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(166,'Vegetarian Enchilada Bake','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF.&nbsp;<div>Coat 13\"x9\" baking dish and large nonstick skillet with cooking spray. Heat skillet medium-high heat. <br><br><br></div><div>Add diced pepper; cook until lightly browned and excess liquid has evaporated, 10 minutes. Stir in crumbles, corn and 3/4cup sauce;cook until heated through 1-2 minutes. Cool slightly;stir in 3/4 cup cheese. <br><br><br></div><div>Spread 1/2 cup&nbsp;sauce&nbsp;over&nbsp;bottom&nbsp;of baking dish. Dividing evenly, spoon filling down center of each tortilla, about 1/2 cup mixture for each. Roll up each tortilla; place in baking dish, seam side down. Top with remaining sauce.Cover with foil.&nbsp;</div><div>Bake until bubbly,30 minutes.<br><br></div><div>Uncover; sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake until&nbsp;cheese is melted, about 10 minutes.&nbsp;</div><div>If desired, garnish with avocado and parsley&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\n',6,0,0,0,0,18,8,7,9,14,9,25,'','2014-04-04 09:00:14',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(167,'Tentation Plantain','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Peel plantains, cut in four and put it in a big skillet with butter, add vanilla,cook wine and pour sugar over plantain, cook for 15 minutes rolling the plantain occasionally until tender and brown.<br><br>Serve with <a href=\"http://recipescookbook.org/recipe/white-rice\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">white rice</a> and <a href=\"http://recipescookbook.org/recipe/Havana-Ground-Beef\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">ground beef</a>.<br>\n	\n	',8,0,0,0,0,35,17,7,6,14,9,15,'../files/recipes/temptation plantain.JPG','2014-05-11 22:34:31','',1,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(168,'Roast Beef','<br>\n','Put in blender garlic, onion, black pepper, oregano, bay leave and orange sour, mix&nbsp; and marinate the beef&nbsp; at least 1 hour before cook.<br><br>In a pressure cooker with oil turn golden brown the beef, add wine cook, marinate and&nbsp; water. Close pressure cooker and bring up to full pressure. Reduce heat to stabilize pressure and cook for 15 minutes. Release pressure, remove beef, cut in slices and&nbsp; put in the cooker again.<br><br>Cut potatoes in slices 1/2 inch and put into pressure cooker bring to to boil until&nbsp; the potatoes are tender.<br><br>Serve hot. <br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,9,7,8,3,6,8,100,'../files/recipes/roast meat.JPG','2014-04-20 02:38:53',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(169,'Fish and Veggie','<br>\n','Mash garlic cloves and mix well with salt, lemon juice, oregano and pepper and marinate the fish in it for 1 hour.<br><br><br>Flour the fillets and fry them in heated oil.&nbsp; Or&nbsp; you can grill the marinate fish.<br><br>While&nbsp; peel and cut broccoli and carrot and cook&nbsp; in microwave for 5 minutes, until tender.<br><br>Serve with mashed potatoes or rice.<br><br>\n',7,0,0,1,0,58,7,8,5,4,9,90,'../files/recipes/fish and veggie.JPG','2014-05-22 05:46:06',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(170,'Birds Nest Cookies','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 300 oF. Spread coconut on non-greased cookie sheet. Toast in oven, stirring&nbsp;occasionally, until it turns light golden,about 25 minutes.&nbsp;Remove coconut from cookie sheet and set aside.&nbsp;Increase oven temperature to 350 oF. In a large bowl, add butter and sugar and whisk until light and fluffy, beat in egg and vanilla.&nbsp;In medium bowl, combine flour and salt. Blend into creamed mixture.<div><div><br></div><div>Form dough into 1-1/4 inch ball. Roll heavily into toasted coconut.&nbsp;Place coconut cookies 2\"&nbsp;apart on lightly greased cookie sheets. Make indentation with thumb in center of each cookie.Bake 12 to 14 minutes or until golden brown.&nbsp;Remove&nbsp;cookies&nbsp;and cool completely. Fill&nbsp;indentations with chocolate eggs or other holidays candies&nbsp;</div>\n</div>\n',6,0,0,0,0,23,16,9,9,15,5,25,'','2014-05-08 19:34:45',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(210,'Banana Raisin Bread','<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:WordDocument>\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\n  <w:TrackMoves></w:TrackMoves>\n  <w:TrackFormatting></w:TrackFormatting>\n  <w:PunctuationKerning></w:PunctuationKerning>\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas></w:ValidateAgainstSchemas>\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\n  <w:DoNotPromoteQF></w:DoNotPromoteQF>\n  <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther>\n  <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian>\n  <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript>\n  <w:Compatibility>\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables></w:BreakWrappedTables>\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell></w:Snap