	\n		Make the cake batter according to the directions on the package. bake in a greased 9\" cake pan. Once baked,remove from pan and cool.<br>Cut the cake in half.Arrange the cake on a serving platter,turning the halves so that the rounded sides touch. To shape the wings, cut out a 1\" triangle from each straight side, 2\" from the bottom.<br>Completely frost the cake with the icing. Design a mosaic pattern with candies and then press them into the top of the cake.<br>To make the butterfly\'s antennae, use large candies, as Strawberry Twists.<br>\n	\n	',10,0,0,0,0,7,16,7,9,13,5,70,'','2014-03-30 05:42:07','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(175,'Salsa Rice','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Cook rice according to packagge directions. Stir in salsa, beans, parsley, zest, coriander, salt and cayenne pepper: cook, stirring occsionally, until heated through, about 2 minutes. Transfer to serving bowl.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,7,16,7,6,7,9,10,'../files/recipes/salsa rice.JPG','2014-05-17 14:26:42','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(176,'Havana Ground Beef','<br>\n','In a skillet, put oil, onion, garlic, pepper, beef and pork. Cook on low heat, stirring occasionally. Add all the rest of the ingredients and cook for 15 minutes.\n',6,0,0,1,0,53,7,9,6,6,9,15,'../files/recipes/picadillo a la habanera.jpg','2014-06-05 15:30:53',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(177,'Chicken Salad','<br>\n','Cut chicken and tomatoes into chunks, the olives and onion in slices and chop the parsley. Whisk dressing ingredients: olive oil, red wine vinegar, salt, pepper, oregano and garlic&nbsp; in a serving bowl and add chicken, stir in tomatoes, olives, onion and parsley.<br><br>Arrange in large bowl on a bed of torn romaine lettuce; top with 1 cup crumbled feta cheese.<br><br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,14,13,8,8,10,6,15,'','2014-05-07 14:54:05',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(178,'Spinach and Avocado Salad','<br>\n','In a serving bowl toss together fresh spinach (trimmed) , jicama (peled and cut), orange (peeled and sectioned), cherry tomatoes (halved), and small avocado. Whisk vinaigrette with zest, juice and mint. Just before serving,&nbsp; pour vinaigrette mixture over spinach mixture; toss.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,21,16,7,8,10,9,15,'../files/recipes/Spinach and Avocado Salad.JPG','2014-04-04 01:37:01',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(179,'Beefsteak in Casserole','<br>\n','Marinate the steaks with the sour orange juice,salt,and pepper. Slice onion and cook it in hot oil, add garlic and oregano. When tender, add steaks and fry them well. Add broth and rest of marinade. Cook them slowly, until tender. Server them with the sauce.\n',4,0,0,0,0,26,7,9,6,6,9,20,'../files/recipes/casserole beef.jpg','2014-04-05 11:32:09',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(180,'Margarita Cheesecake','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Coat 8\" springform pan with cooking spray. <br>Combine crumbs with cinnamon; stir in honey and butter until combined. <br>Press onto botton and 1\" up sides of pan; refrigerate until ready to use. <br>In small microwave-safe bowl sprinkle gelatin over orange juice, set aside.<br>In another bowl with mixer at high speed beat Neufchatel and fat free cream cheese until smooth. <br>Reduce speed to low; beat in sugar and sour cream. Increase speed to medium; beat 2 minutes. Reduce speed to low; beat in tequila, lime juice and zest until combined. <br>In microwave&nbsp; heat reserved orange juice mixture on high at 5- second intervals until gelatin dissolves and mixture is pourable. <br>At low speed beat gelatin mixture into cheese mixture in thin steady stream; beat 30 seconds. Pour batter into pan.<br>Refrigerate until set, at least 3 hours or overnight. <br>Garnish with topping and limes slices.<br>\n	\n	',16,0,0,2,0,36,16,7,2,13,6,30,'../files/recipes/DSCN2906.JPG','2014-05-22 05:36:13','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(181,'Fried Rice','<br>\n','Cook <a href=\"http://recipescookbook.org/recipe/white-rice\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">white rice</a> with a little salt, oil and water.&nbsp;Meanwhile make thin tortillas with eggs and salt. Cut tortillas into thin strips, cut ham and chicken into dice.<br><br>In a casserole put oil and fry onion, add cooked rice and saute all, add the tortillas, ham and chicken mix well, add soy sauce, stirring constantly to coat with the sauce and the other ingredients.<br>\n',4,0,0,35,1,89,11,8,6,7,9,60,'../files/recipes/fried rice.jpg','2014-05-18 15:02:46',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(182,'Asparagus','<br>\n','Take out the white part of&nbsp; asparagus. Put them in microwave save pan. cut&nbsp; onion and green pepper in slices, arrange over asparagus with salt, olive oil and water.<br><br>Cook 3 minutes in microwave<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,23,7,7,2,10,9,10,'../files/recipes/asparagus.JPG','2014-06-05 18:46:25',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(183,'Chocolate Truffles','<br>\n','<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\n  <o:RelyOnVML></o:RelyOnVML>\n  <o:AllowPNG></o:AllowPNG>\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:WordDocument>\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\n  <w:TrackMoves></w:TrackMoves>\n  <w:TrackFormatting></w:TrackFormatting>\n  <w:PunctuationKerning></w:PunctuationKerning>\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas></w:ValidateAgainstSchemas>\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\n  <w:DoNotPromoteQF></w:DoNotPromoteQF>\n  <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther>\n  <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian>\n  <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript>\n  <w:Compatibility>\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables></w:BreakWrappedTables>\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell></w:SnapToGridInCell>\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct></w:WrapTextWithPunct>\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules></w:UseAsianBreakRules>\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit></w:DontGrowAutofit>\n   <w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark></w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark>\n   <w:DontVertAlignCellWithSp></w:DontVertAlignCellWithSp>\n   <w:DontBreakConstrainedForcedTables></w:DontBreakConstrainedForcedTables>\n   <