ts with lettuce mix well and serve with dressing.',4,1,1,8,0,56,16,7,8,10,9,10,'../files/recipes/fernand favorite salad.JPG','2014-05-22 05:30:35',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(312,'Ravioli Puttanesca','<br>','Cook ravioli according to package directions. Meanwhile, heat marinada sauce with olives, capers, red pepper and chopped parsley. Drain ravioli; toss with sauce.<div><br></div><div>Serve with grated parmesan cheese and additional parsley.</div>',4,0,0,0,0,54,10,7,6,4,9,20,'','2014-04-02 08:50:11',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(313,'Polka Dot Sorbet Pie','<br>','In food processor, combine crackers and granulated sugar; pulse until coarse crumbs form. Add butter, pulse until combined. Press firmly into 9 inch pie pan; freeze until firm, at least 30 minutes. Alternately scoop sorbets and place in crust. Freeze until firm, at least 6 hour or overnight.<div><br></div><div>Just before serving, beat cream, confectioner sugar and vanilla until soft peaks form.&nbsp;<br><div>Transfer to pastry bag fitted with star tip; pipe or spoon around pie.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Let stand 20 minutes at room temperature before slicing.</div><div><br></div><div><br><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div></div></div>',8,0,0,0,0,32,16,7,8,15,9,380,'','2014-04-21 16:17:48',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(305,'Fried Sesame Chicken','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 400oF Line baking sheet with foil; set rack on top. In bowl, whisk buttermilk with mustard. Add chicken and toss.<div><br></div><div>In shallow bowl, mix remaining ingredients. Add chicken one piece at a time, turning to coat. Place chicken on rack.</div><div><br></div><div>Bake 45 or 50 minutes or until thermometer inserted into thickest part away from bone registers 170oF. Let stand 5 or 10 minutes before serving.</div>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,14,11,8,9,16,6,75,'../files/recipes/DSCN1931.JPG','2014-03-23 23:38:49','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(306,'Spareribs','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Prepare grill for indirect-heat cooking. In small pot, combine &nbsp;garlic, onion, sour orange, black pepper, oregano and salt, rub over both sides of ribs &nbsp;with the half of sauce,&nbsp;<div>Place ribs, meaty side down, on grill. Cover, cook 15 minutes. Turn ribs over. Cover, cook until tender, about 2 hours, brushing with sauce several times during last 30 minutes. Let stand 10 or 15 minutes before cutting into individual servings.</div><div><br></div><div>No grill &nbsp;option:</div><div><br></div><div>Preheat oven to 350oF . Line large jellyroll pan with foil. Place seasoned ribs on pan. Roast until tender, about 2 hours, brushing with sauce several times during last 30 minutes of cooking time.</div>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,10,13,9,5,6,6,155,'../files/recipes/spare ribs.JPG','2014-04-23 07:08:44','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(307,'Snickerdoodles','<br>\n','Heat the oven to 350oF<div><br></div><div>Cream together the shortening and sugar with an electric mixer until light and fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly between each addition.</div><div><br></div><div>Sift together the flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt in a separate bowl. Add to the shortening mixture, beating well. Gather the dough in a ball, wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm, about 30 minutes</div><div><br></div><div>Tear off walnut-size pieces of dough; roll each into a ball. Dust with cinnamon sugar; place on an ungreased baking sheet, spacing about 2 inches apart. Bake until light brown and firm on top, 10 to 15 minutes; the tops will be deeply cracked,and the centers will still be somewhat soft.</div><div><br></div><div>Cool on the baking sheet, 5 minutes; transfer to a cooling rack to finish. Store in an airtight container.</div><div><br></div><div>Note: For cinnamon sugar, mix 1 tablespoon ground cinnamon whit 1/4 cup sugar.</div>\n',12,0,0,0,0,14,13,8,9,12,9,40,'','2014-04-01 01:10:20',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(308,'Almond Macaroon','The Almond macaroon, also called arron is a dessert of a delicious flavor, besides distinguished. Tell the story that this recipes arose in the Duchy of Florence, Italy. But this dessert gave him fame and recognition in another place; according to historians, in 1533, Catherine di&nbsp; Medici brought him to France, country of development to culture, fine arts, and fashion during medieval period.<br><br>The recipe of Almond macaroon was well received among the aristocracy, and the almond macaroon quickly becoming a luxury dessert.<br><br>The almond macaroon is prepared with simple ingredients such as almonds, sugar and egg white, but the secrets itâ€™s unique flavor is how to elaborate and bake the dough. Actually that recipe can be prepared in different colors and flavors, due to the possibilities of the current pastry. The presentation of the recipe is done in pairs, or two cookies joined together by a layer of cream or jam, dusted with confectioner sugar.<br><br>Today the almond macaroon is selling in prestigious patisseries in France, and the French people receives it so well and every year they celebrate its official Holiday in March, 20.<br><br>&nbsp;With this unique flavor, Will you offer somebody this dessert with coffee?<br><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" DefUnhideWhenUsed=\"true\"\n  DefSemiHidden=\"true\" DefQFormat=\"false\" DefPriority=\"99\"\n  LatentStyleCount=\"267\">\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"0\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Normal\"></w:LsdException>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"9\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"heading 1\"></w:LsdException>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"9\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"heading 2\"></w:LsdException>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"9\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"heading 3\"></w:LsdException>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"9\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"heading 