\" Name=\"Bibliography\"></w:LsdException>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"39\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"TOC Heading\"></w:LsdException>\n </w:LatentStyles>\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 10]>\n<style>\n /* Style Definitions */\n table.MsoNormalTable\n	{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\";\n	mso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\n	mso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\n	mso-style-noshow:yes;\n	mso-style-priority:99;\n	mso-style-qformat:yes;\n	mso-style-parent:\"\";\n	mso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\n	mso-para-margin-top:0in;\n	mso-para-margin-right:0in;\n	mso-para-margin-bottom:10.0pt;\n	mso-para-margin-left:0in;\n	line-height:115%;\n	mso-pagination:widow-orphan;\n	font-size:11.0pt;\n	font-family:\"Calibri\",\"sans-serif\";\n	mso-ascii-font-family:Calibri;\n	mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\n	mso-fareast-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\n	mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-fareast;\n	mso-hansi-font-family:Calibri;\n	mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;}\n</style>\n<![endif]-->\n	\n	','	\n		<div>In a large bowl, whisk with electric mixer egg whites until soft peaks do, gradually add 1/3 cup sugar and continue beating until peaks are firm but no dry, set aside. In another bowl combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, add vanilla, milk, oil and egg yolks, and mix it at medium speed for 3 minutes, scraping the sides and bottom frequently. Join the two mixtures well, pour into pan and bake &nbsp;25-30 minutes, or until a tooth pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool completely on wire rack. When the cake is cool, with a sharp knife, mark a circle of one centimeter deep and with a spoon remove the mass of the cake. Make a syrup with 3 tbsp sugar and 1 tbsp water and let boil until is light consistency and hot pour over the edge cake. Make a vanilla pudding as directed on package, and pour in the circle you did in the cake.</div><div><br></div><div>For another version: You can use chocolate or your favorite flavor pudding.</div>\n	\n	',10,0,0,0,0,39,7,9,9,13,9,50,'../files/recipes/vanilla volcano.JPG','2014-05-22 09:51:42','',0,0,1,0,0,0,'2013-12-25 13:00:02'),(281,'Rum Pudding','<br>','Line a waxed&nbsp; paper-lined deep pan with split ladyfingers.<br><br>Mix eggs yolks and sugar and beat until light. Add rum. Fold egg yolks into whites, and whipped cream into this. Fold in marshmallows and nuts. Add nutmeg and pour into the pan. Chill or freeze, as you like.<br><br><br>We used a 9 x 5 inch loaf pan and had enough extra filling to make a second pudding. To do so, you would need another dozen ladyfingers.<br>',8,0,0,0,0,11,13,9,8,13,9,30,'','2014-06-01 21:06:00',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(282,'Vanilla Chocolate Cupcakes','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF. Line 18 muffin cups&nbsp; with cupcake liners. On medium&nbsp; high speed, beat 1 1/4 cups sugar and spread until fluffy, 2 minutes. On low speed, beat in egg whites. Beat in baking mix, milk and 1 tsp vanilla until just smooth. Divide among liners. <br><br>Bake 15 or until pick inserted comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Transfer from pans to racks; cool completely.<br><br>In small pot, whisk remaining sugar with cocoa and 3 tbs. water, over medium-high heat, bring to boil, stirring.Over low heat, cook stirring, until thickened, 7-8 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in sour cream, corn syrup, remaining vanilla, then chocolate.<br><br>Refrigerate 1 hour. On medium high speed, beat chocolate mixture until thick, 1 - 2 minutes.<br><br>Spread over cupcakes. Decorate with jimmies.<br>\n',18,0,0,1,0,28,16,9,9,15,9,25,'../files/recipes/vanilla chocolote cupcake.JPG','2014-05-22 05:25:53',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(283,'Chicken Fried Rice','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Cook rice, reserve. Meanwhile, in large nonstick skillet, heat 1 tbs oil over medium high heat; add eggs. Cook stirring, until set; remove from skillet.<br><br>In same skillet, heat 1 tbs&nbsp; oil over medium-high heat. Add vegetables; cook, stirring, until softened, bout 2 minutes. Add chicken, teriyaki sauce and reserved rice and eggs. Cook stirring, until heated through. Sprinkle with scallions.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,13,11,8,6,7,9,35,'../files/recipes/chicken fried rice.JPG','2014-05-18 08:31:19','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(284,'Coconut Cream Pie','<br>\n','In large bowl, whisk together pudding mixes, coconut milk and extract until smooth and thickened, about 2 minutes. Gradually fold in 2 cups whipped topping until combined. Spread evenly in crust. Refrigerate until set, at least 2 hours. Spread with remaining whipped topping.<br><br>If desired, sprinkle with toasted coconut.<br>\n',12,0,0,0,0,10,13,8,8,13,5,15,'../files/recipes/coconout cream pie.JPG','2014-04-05 12:09:52',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(285,'Crepes','The Crepes are torts as old as the European civilization. Some people have claimed the idea of how to make crepes aroused in the region of Brittany, to Western France, but&nbsp; this recipe is also present in the ancient roman cookbook, where Apicius, the roman cooker, prepared it in a hot iron surface and served its with honey and pepper.<br><br>If the basis of feeding in Europe was the wheat, is easy to imagine that every people prepared theses torts made from flour, milk and eggs in a similar way, and transmitted this throughout many generations.<br><br>Krampouezh in Brittany, palaÄinka in the Czech Republic, Slovenia and Croatia, palatschinken in Austria, palacsinta in Hungary, filloas in Galicia, crepes in Spain and so on. The secret of how to make crepes have been present in religious and popular festivals.<br><br>We know these recipes can be found in the French royal cookbook. King Edward VII of France, where from his table came the famous recipe: Crepes Suzette. The different ways to make crepes fusion cultures, traditions and launched this recipe to the stardom. <br>','In bowl combine flour, sugar and salt. In another bowl, beat eggs; beat in milk.<div>Beat milk mixture into flour mixture until thin smooth batter forms.</div><div><br></div><div>Coat medium nonstick skillet with cooking spray; heat over medium-high heat. Spoon 3 tbs. batter into skillet and swirl pan so that batter thinly covers bottom. .Crepe will &nbsp; be very thin.Cook, turning once, until lightly browned on both sides, about 1 minute per side.</div><div><br></div><div>Continue making crepes until batter is used up.</div><div><br></div><div>Top with favorite filling and roll up to serve.</div>\n',4,0,0,0,0,33,13,8,6,15,9,25,'','2014-04-21 03:24:27',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(286,'Pumpkin Mousse','<br>','In bowl, whisk together pudding mix, milk, cinnamon and salt until smooth.&nbsp;<div>add pumpkin; whisk until light and fluffy. Fold in whipped topping.</div><div><br></div><div>Chill until set. about 1 hour. To serve, place 1 tbsp fudge topping in bottom of each serving glass. Top each with about 1/2 cup pumpkin mixture.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>If desired, garnish with additional whipped topping, fudge topping and ginger.</div>',6,0,0,0,0,13,16,9,8,13,9,70,'','2014-03-16 11:39:28',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(287,'Mozzarella Pasta','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Cook pasta according to package directions.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>Mean while, chopped tomatoes and shallots, halved the mozzarella balls and olives and sliced basil leaves, and then combine it in a large serving bowl. Add oil, vinegar and salt. Toss well to mix.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Drain pasta; stir into tomato mixture. Garnish with basil spring.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,13,13,8,8,4,5,20,'../files/recipes/mozarella pasta.JPG','2014-03-17 04:18:32','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(288,'Roast Chicken With Mango','<br>','Preheat oven to 350oF<div><br></div><div>Combine first 5 ingredients. Place chicken in roasting pan and rub with spice mixture.</div><div><br></div><div>Roast chicken until meat thermometer inserted into thickest part of thigh way from bone register 180oF, about 2 hours. Sprinkle with 1 tsp. cilantro and zest.Let stand 10 minutes before carving.</div><div><br></div><div>Meanwhile, toss mango slices with scallion, lime juice and remaining 2 tsp. cilantro.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Serve chicken with mangos</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>',6,0,0,0,0,11,13,8,9,16,9,150,'','2014-05-05 10:45:05',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(289,'Green Potato Salad','<br>\n','In medium pot, combine potatoes quartered with enough salted water to cover; &nbsp;bring to a boil. Cook until just tender, 8 or 10 minutes. Drain; rinse under cold water to cool.<div><br></div><div>Meanwhile, in large serving bowl, whisk together oil, vinegar, mustard, salt and pepper.Add potatoes, scallions, basil and parsley; toss to coat.</div>\n',6,0,0,0,0,12,16,7,6,10,9,30,'../files/recipes/parsley potato salad.JPG','2014-06-05 13:52:41',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(290,'Pasta Primavera','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Cook pasta according to package directions, adding frozen vegetables &nbsp;during last 5 minutes of cooking time. Drain pasta &nbsp;mixture well, reserving 1/2 cup cooking water.In same pot, melt cream cheese over low heat. Add pasta mixture, chicken, peas, thyme,salt. pepper and reserved pasta water.<div><br></div><div>Stir until cream cheese is melted and mixture is heated through, about 5 minutes.</div><div><br></div><div>Serve immediately.</div>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,9,13,7,6,4,6,20,'../files/recipes/rottini primavera.JPG','2014-03-05 12:49:46','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(291,'Lemony Chicken','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 375oF<div><br></div><div>Mix 1 tbs.oregano, 1/2 tsp. salt and 1/2 tsp. pepper , sprinkle over chicken. Coat large roasting pan with cooking spray; place over 2 burners set on medium heat. When hot, add chicken;cook turning once, until browned, about 5 minutes per side. Remove chicken from pan. In large bowl toss potatoes, &nbsp;peppers cut into long pieces and lemon quartered, seeded with garlic sliced, remaining 2 tsp oregano, 1/2 tsp salt and 1/2 tsp pepper. Add to roasting pan; cook stirring, until browned.</div><div><br></div><div>Return chicken to pan. Carefully cover with foil. Place in oven and cook until chicken is no longer pink near bones and vegetables are tender, about 40 minutes.</div>\n',6,0,0,0,0,21,16,8,9,16,9,70,'','2014-05-22 04:56:09',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(292,'Beans Salad','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Chop onion, green &nbsp;pepper and celery in small pieces.<div><br></div><div>Open all the cans and drain in a colander.</div><div><br></div><div>Mix all ingredients in a big bowl and toss well, cover and refrigerate.</div>\n	\n	',10,0,0,0,0,7,13,7,8,10,6,60,'../files/recipes/beans salad.JPG','2014-06-05 18:47:16','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(293,'Seafood Salad','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Chop green, yellow and red peppers, jalapeno slices, cucumber without seed, garlic, red onion and cilantrillo. Cut in half tomatoes and devained shrimps, , cubed all seafood meat but scallops.<div><br></div><div>Wash it and then put in a big salad bowl all this ingredients.</div><div><br></div><div>Make a dressing with olive oil, salt, vinegar, lemon and sour orange. Pour over all ingredients into bowl and toss well.</div><div><br></div><div>Cover and refrigerate at least &nbsp;a hour.</div><div><br></div><div>Make &nbsp;the salad the day before so it get more flavor.</div>\n	\n	',10,0,0,2,0,45,7,8,8,9,6,120,'../files/recipes/seafood salad.JPG','2014-05-21 01:02:56','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(294,'Imperial Rice','<div>I started writing this story thinking in my cousin, her husband and their kids since Imperial Rice is their favorite dish ever from the Cuban cuisine; especially if it is prepared by my mother, who created this cookbook.</div><div><br></div><div>Looking forward to understand better the origins of Imperial Rice, I did a little Web research to find there is little information about their history, although it is a very popular dish. The only certain data I obtained was, many people locate this recipeâ€™s birth in some point in Eastern Cuba. Frustrated, I tried again harder consulting further bibliography, until I was pleased enough.</div><div><br></div><div>The Imperial Rice is a very practical dish in the Caribbean, notorious for its versatility, and adaptability to any circumstance. It it is not a typical dish, but it is a very popular, nutritious and affordable recipe. The Imperial Rice recipe constantly varies depending the ingredients reachable the culture of the zone. This plate is often served as a main dish and in America we used to accompanied it with salad, boiled vegetables or French fries. Some people prefer the use of Cheese, other uses only mayo; there is a great debate around the correct way Imperial Rice is made, but everything depends of the point of view taken, all them are delightful.</div><div><br></div><div>How to make Imperial Rice is a bit laborious but simple. There is not need to be a Chef to accomplish the task with merits. With a minimal care success is guarantied, and a sigh of excitement in the eyes of your loved ones will be always present. No matter the occasion, the portentous, delightful and Caribbean Imperial Rice it is always welcomed.&nbsp;</div>\n','Cook the chicken in 3 cups of water until tender. Take out chicken and set aside the broth. When the chicken is cold shredded and marinade with salt and lemon.<div><br></div><div>With the broth, salt and bijol (yellow food coloring) cook the rice as always.</div><div><br></div><div>Coarsely chop onion, green pepper and garlic saute in a skillet for 2 minutes add tomatoes sauce, black pepper, oregano, cook 1 minutes, combine with chicken and cooking wine, cook until dry.</div><div><br></div><div>To serving, pour half of rice in a 9 x 13 inch pan or bundt coated with cooking spray and press tightly, cover with mayonnaise pour chicken on top and press again, then the cheese, and cover with remaining rice press tightly again so when you invert it in a serving plate won fall apart.</div><div><br></div><div>Guarnish with olives and pimientos slices.</div>\n',6,0,0,15,2,2561,7,8,6,7,9,60,'../files/recipes/imperial rice.JPG','2014-06-07 22:59:06','',0,0,0,1,0,0,'2014-01-01 13:00:02'),(296,'Decadent Date Bars','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 325oF. Lightly coat 11 x 7 inch glass baking dish with cooking spray.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>Mix flour, baking powder and salt; reserve. In medium bowl, mix egg substitute, sugar and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture until combined. Mix in chopped small pieces dates and 3 tbs.mini dark chocolate chunks. Pour into baking dish. Sprinkle evenly with coconut, then remaining 1 tbs. chocolate.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Bake 24 minutes or until golden and toothpick inserted into center comes out sticky, but not wet. Cool. Cut into bars.</div>\n',16,0,0,0,0,9,16,8,9,12,9,60,'','2014-05-21 20:20:34',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(297,'Apricot Glazed Pork Roast','','	\n		Preheat oven to 350oF &nbsp;In small microwave safe bowl, microwave apricot preserves on high in 30 seconds intervals until melted. Stir in vinegar and reserve.<div><br></div><div>In separate small bowl, combine oil, crush fennel seeds, garlic powder, salt and paprika. Rub over pork; place in roasting pan. Roast until meat thermometer inserted into thickest part register &nbsp;145oF, about 55 or60 minutes, brushing with apricot glaze during last 10 minutes of cooking time.</div><div><br></div><div>Let pork stand 10 minutes before slicing.</div>\n	\n	',8,0,0,0,0,18,13,8,9,6,8,80,'../files/recipes/Apricot Glazed Pork Roast.JPG','2014-05-16 06:07:51','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(298,'Broccoli Almandine','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Bring large pot of water to boil. Add broccoli, cook until just tender, 3 minutes. Drain well in colander, then pat dry with paper towels.<div><br></div><div>Meanwhile, heat large dry skillet over medium high heat. Add almonds; cook, stirring occasionally, until lightly browned, 2 or 3 minutes. Remove from skillet; reserve.</div><div><br></div><div>In same skillet, melt butter over medium high heat. Add thinly sliced garlic Greek seasoning and salt;cook, stirring until garlic is just starting to brown.</div><div><br></div><div>Add broccoli; cook, stirring, until heated through about 1 minute. Remove from heat. Drizzle with honey and toss with grated lemon zest.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Transfer to serving bowl; sprinkle wih reserved almonds.</div>\n	\n	',6,0,0,1,0,20,13,7,6,17,10,15,'../files/recipes/brocoly armandini.JPG','2014-04-06 13:20:29','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(299,'Roasted Potato','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF. In large bowl combine oil, butter, paprika, onion powder, salt and chili powder.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>Cut potatoes lengthwise into 1 inch wedges and add, toss until coated in oil mixture. Arrange in single layer on jelly-roll pan. Roast 30 minutes.</div><div><br></div><div>Increase oven temperature to 450oF. Roast until potatoes are cooked through and lightly browned, about 15 minutes.</div>\n',6,0,0,0,0,10,13,7,9,17,9,60,'','2014-04-03 18:39:12',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(300,'Vacation Burger','<br>\n','For the pineapple sauce, mix peeled, cored and diced pineapple with diced green pepper, diced onion and chopped cilantro. Add 1 tbsp. lime juice and salt to taste. Toss mixture. Set aside.<div><br></div><div>Mix ground beef, 1/4 tsp salt, 1/4 tsp. black pepper and 1/4 tsp. onion power thoroughly and form mixture into 4 equal oblong patties (shaped &nbsp;for the garlic toast bun). &nbsp;Set aside.</div><div><br></div><div>Heat grill to a medium temperature. Grill burger patties on each side, until desired doneness (the internal temperature reaches 145oF for a medium burger) Meanwhile, toast or bake garlic toast according to package directions.</div><div><br></div><div>To assemble burger, layer the garlic toast with lettuce leaves, 1 burger patty, 1 slice of Pepper Jack cheese, 1/4 of the pineapple sauce, 1/4 of the avocado slices and top whit garlic toast.</div>\n',4,0,0,0,0,14,13,8,5,6,6,35,'','2014-03-22 08:39:42',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(301,'Spicy Grilled Potatoes','<br>\n','Prepare grill for indirect heat cooking. Place each potato scrubbed and dried on piece of foil. On an angle, cut 4 slits in each potato, 3/4 of the way through. Mix butter, seasoning, garlic powder and paprika; stir in Parmesan. Dividing mixture evenly, spoon over potatoes; wrap in foil.<div><br></div><div>Place on grill over indirect heat. Cover, cook until tender, about 1 hour. Unwrap potatoes; drizzle with any butter mixture in foil. Sprinkle with parsley.</div><div><br></div><div>No grill option:</div><div>Peheat oven to 400oF. Bake wrapped potatoes 1 hour.</div>\n',6,0,0,0,0,16,13,8,5,17,5,70,'','2014-04-30 22:29:01',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(302,'Beef with Chimichurri Sauce','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		in blender , process the 5 first ingredients with 1/4 tsp. salt until smooth. Rub the beef with pepper. Spread 1/4 cup sauce over roast; let stand 1 hour. Reserve remaining sauce.<div><br></div><div>Prepare grill for direct-and indirect-heat cooking. Sprinkle beef with remaining 1/2 tsp salt; place on grill over direct heat. Grill, turning to mark sides, 7 or 8 minutes. Transfer to indirect heat. Cover, grill until meat thermometer inserted into thickest part of beef registers 145oF for medium-rare, 1 hour. Taste to done.</div><div><br></div><div>Let stand 10 minutes before slicing. Serve with reserve sauce.</div><div><br></div><div>No grill option:</div><div><br></div><div>Preheat oven to 400oF. Cook roast on rack in &nbsp;roasting pan 50 minutes.&nbsp;</div><div>Taste to done.</div>\n	\n	',8,0,0,0,0,19,13,8,5,6,6,120,'../files/recipes/beef with chimichurri.JPG','2014-05-17 01:17:04','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(303,'Mango Mousse Cake','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Cut each shortcake rolls into 7 slices and line side of 8 inch springform pan with single layer of cake slices; cover bottom with remaining slices.<br><div><br></div><div>In blender, puree jarred mango slices drained until smooth. Transfer to bowl; stir &nbsp;in 1 cup nectar and food coloring. In microwave-safe bowl, sprinkle gelatin over remaining 1/2 cup nectar; stir to combine.Microwave mixture on High until melted, 30 seconds. Stir into pureed mango mixture. Refrigerate until thickened, 20 or 30 minutes.</div><div><br></div><div>In large bowl, on medium-high speed, beat cream and sugar until stiff peaks form; refrigerate 1 cup. Fold remaining whipped cream into mango mixture; spread in pan.&nbsp;</div><div>Refrigerate until firm, about 4 hours.</div><div><br></div><div>Run knife between side of pan and cake; remove side of pan. Top with mango slices; &nbsp;brush with jelly. Transfer reserved whipped cream to pastry bag fitted with star tip. Pipe around edge of cake. If desired, garnish with mint.</div><div><br></div><div><br></div><div><br></div>\n	\n	',12,0,0,2,1,106,13,9,2,13,5,300,'../files/recipes/mangoe moosse.JPG','2014-06-05 06:46:01','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(188,'Cuban Dressing','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\n  <o:RelyOnVML></o:RelyOnVML>\n  <o:AllowPNG></o:AllowPNG>\n </o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:WordDocument>\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\n  <w:TrackMoves></w:TrackMoves>\n  <w:TrackFormatting></w:TrackFormatting>\n  <w:PunctuationKerning></w:PunctuationKerning>\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas></w:ValidateAgainstSchemas>\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\n  <w:DoNotPromoteQF></w:DoNotPromoteQF>\n  <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther>\n  <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian>\n  <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript>\n  <w:Compatibility>\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables></w:BreakWrappedTables>\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell></w:SnapToGridInCell>\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct></w:WrapTextWithPunct>\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules></w:UseAsianBreakRules>\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit></w:DontGrowAutofit>\n   <w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark></w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark>\n   <w: