ok in boiling water for one hour or in pressure cooker for 20 minutes. Remove from water, take of the tamale and open. Serve on a plate with saute onions on top. Enjoy.</div>\n',6,0,0,3,3,185,7,9,6,14,9,60,'../files/recipes/tamales.JPG','2014-06-06 08:26:50',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(340,'Yogurt Potato Salad','<br>\n','Peeled, cut&nbsp; in cube and wash potatoes, cook for 10 minutes or until tender. In large bowl, combine yogurt, mustard and horseradish. Add remaining ingredients; toss to mix well.<br><br>Refrigerate to chill or serve.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,17,16,8,8,10,9,10,'../files/recipes/yogurt potato salad.JPG','2014-04-27 17:41:22',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(341,'Asian Chicken Salad','<br>','Combine sour cream, hoisin sauce,salt,chili paste, chicken, celery and onion; mix well.<br>Lay the washed and dried lettuce leaves on a platter.<br>Top each with 1/4 cup chicken salad. Top with a heaping tablespoon of cottage cheese. Sprinkle with chopped peanuts. Fold up lettuce cups to eat.<br>',4,0,0,0,0,25,11,8,6,16,9,10,'','2014-03-16 07:19:02',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(342,'Toffee Bars','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF. Ungreased or foil-lined 13 x 9 inch pan.<br><br>Separate the yolk from 1 large egg and place yolk in large bowl. Into the bowl with the yolk, stir butter, brown sugar and vanilla, with wooden spoon until well mixed. Stir in flour and salt. Press dough into prepared pan.<br><br>Bake 25 or 30 minutes or until very light brown (crust will be soft).<br><br>Sprinkle milk chocolate chips over the crust. Let stand about 5 minutes or until chocolate has softened. Spread chocolate evenly over bars. Sprinkle with chopped nuts.<br><br>Place pan on rack and let stand 30 minutes.<br>\n',20,0,0,0,0,13,13,9,9,15,9,40,'../files/recipes/tofee bars.JPG','2014-05-14 16:41:15',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(343,'Pork stir Fry','<br>\n','In nonstick skillet brown thinly sliced pork tenderloin; remove, in same skillet cook vegetables, chopped garlic and ginger, in olive oil until crisp-tender. Bring to a boil; cook 1 minute. <br><br>Add pork, lime juice and cilantro; heat.<br><br>Serve over cooked noodles or white rice,<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,16,13,8,6,6,9,30,'../files/recipes/pork stir fry.JPG','2014-03-23 20:20:31',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(344,'Fruit Cake','<br>\n','Preheat oven&nbsp; 350oF and coat bundt pan with cooking spray, set aside.<br><br>Sift flour, baking powder and salt, in a medium bowl beat&nbsp; butter until creamy add sugar gradually, then eggs, milk and vanilla, mix well.<br><br>Add&nbsp; fruit and flour&nbsp; without beating, mix with gentle rolling motion. Pour into pan and bake for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan for 10 minutes on wire rack; remove from pan, invert onto serving plate.<br><br>In small bowl, combine apricot and orange juice, blend well. Spoon over warm cake and cool.<br><br>You can make it in two 8 inch layer cake pan.<br><br><br>\n',12,0,1,0,0,15,13,9,9,13,9,60,'../files/recipes/fruit cake - slide.JPG','2014-05-30 14:58:30',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(345,'Confetti Salad','<br>\n','Cook potatoes in water with salt and 2 tablespoons lemon juice until tender, drain. Cook eggs for 8 minutes and quartered, diced pimiento and green pepper, sliced onion.<br><br>In large serving&nbsp; bowl, combine hot potatoes and remaining ingredients. Toss gently. Refrigerate to chill<br><br><br><br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,16,13,8,6,10,9,20,'../files/recipes/Confetti salad.JPG','2014-05-28 18:56:13',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(346,'Tricolor Salad','<br>\n','Coat 6 cups mold with cooking spray. In bowl pour 1 cup boiling water over strawberry gelatin mix; stir until completely dissolved. Add 1/3 cup cold water and strawberries. Pour into mold. Refrigerate until set but no firm, about 1 1/2 hours. <br><br>In microwave-safe bowl sprinkle unflavored gelatin over 2 tbs. water; let stand until softened, about 1 minute. Microwave on High in 5 seconds intervals until liquified, about 15 seconds.<br><br>In medium bowl at medium high speed beat cream cheese,&nbsp; at room temperature, sour cream and sugar until smooth. Reduce speed to low; beat in unflavored gelatin until combined. Pour&nbsp; over strawberry mixture in mold; refrigerate until set but not firm, about 1 hour.<br><br>Meanwhile, in bowl pour remaining boiling water over blue gelatin mix; stir until completely dissolved, 3-4 minutes. Add remaining cold water. Let&nbsp; blue mixture stand on counter until room temperature, about 30 minutes. While cream cheese layer is setting. Stir in blueberries. Pour over cream cheese mixture in mold. <br>refrigerate until firm, 2 - 3 hours.<br><br>Just before serving run knife around sides to loosen. Quickly dip bottom of mold into hot water; place serving platter over mold and invert to release. <br><br>Can be made one day ahead, leave in mold until ready to serve.<br>\n',16,0,0,4,0,71,13,9,8,15,6,330,'../files/recipes/tricolor salad.JPG','2014-05-16 00:51:18',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(347,'Chick Pea Porridge','<br>\n','Soak chick peas in 3 cups of cold water&nbsp; for 2 hours, drain wash and put in a pot with 4 cups of cold water, chorizo (spanish sausage), salted pork and beef chopped onion and garlic cover and cook in medium heat for 3 hours or until tender (in a pressure cooker cook for 25 minutes and reduce water to 3 cups) taste the broth and add salt if is necessary. <br><br>Peeled, wash and cut in four potatoes and pumpkin add to pot and cook until tender, about 15 minutes.<br><br>Put some chick peas in a plate, mash then a little and put back in the pot and boil until thick.<br><br>You can use beef skirt or other beef.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,252,17,8,6,14,9,445,'../files/recipes/Chick peas Porridge.JPG','2014-06-05 11:14:02',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(348,'Stuffed Potatoes','The Papa Rellena (Stuffed potatoes)&nbsp; is a meal of modern times, is the combination of tuber found in Peru by the Spanish at the time of the conquest, and the traditional patty very popular in that country.<br><br>How to understand the reason for this mix? Which led to unite ingredients so dissimilar cultures?<br><br>In the period of the conquest, between the late XV and XVI century, the travel by ship from Spain to the New Continent, took between 3 and 4 months, to the provision of food and other products to the Americas was very delayed, and secondly wheat, abundant in Europe was not known in America, where only grow corn, potatoes and cassava, aboriginal basic diet.<br><br>Moreover, the conquest of Peru and the territories of South America are characterized by great violence and in the midst of these wars, worsened the supply of products, so as the new solution is created mashed potatoes stuffed with seasoned ground meat, then frying as a patty.<br><br>The top plate of primitive, given primarily to eat lower-class people, was gradually gaining fame and consideration to become part of the diet of the rich class, whom already in 1554 sent to Spain&nbsp; the potatoes as a curiosity.<br><br><br>\n','In a pot combine potatoes, peeled and quartered with water and salt. Cover and boil at moderate heat until potatoes are tender. Drain and immediately mash.<br><br>Cover palm of hand with cornstarch and spread over hand one part of the mash potatoes, spoon the center with 1 spoonful of <a target=\"_blank\" title=\"\" href=\"http://recipescookbook.org/recipe/How-to-make-Havana-Ground-Beef\">picadillo (Havana Ground Beef)</a>&nbsp; and bring mash potatoes over to cover filling.<br><br>Proceed with remaining mixture until 12 balls are ready. Wrap them in beaten egg and breadcrumbs and deepfry&nbsp; in oil&nbsp; until golden brown<br>\n',4,0,0,1,0,48,7,8,6,14,9,40,'../files/recipes/papas rellenas.JPG','2014-05-21 02:20:25','',1,1,1,0,0,0,'2014-01-08 13:00:02'),(349,'Pork Chops With Wine','<br>\n','Dip the chops into the lemon juice and rub generously with salt and pepper. Set aside for an hour in the refrigerator.<br><br>Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet, brown the chops in the butter or margarine on both sides. Pour the wine over the chops and simmer until chops are tender. Turn the chops occasionally.<br><br>Serve with wine sauce poured over the chops.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,20,10,8,6,14,7,30,'../files/recipes/pork chops with wine.JPG','2014-04-03 15:30:00',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(350,'Hot salad','<br>\n','Drain well in a colander the corn and green beans, cut tomatoes and grated the cheese.<br><br>In a salad plate mix all ingredients less cheese.<br><br>Pour grated cheese over salad, and put them in microwave 30 seconds or until cheese is melted<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,18,7,7,2,10,9,15,'../files/recipes/the hot salad.jpg','2014-05-26 15:45:19',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(351,'Summer Salad','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Cook pasta according to package directions, add broccoli during last 4 minutes of cooking time, drain well in colander.<br><br>In salad bowl mix elbow pasta with broccoli, ham and walnut.<br><br>Set to cool, before serving pour over dressing and toss.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,2,0,32,7,8,6,4,9,25,'../files/recipes/summer salad.JPG','2014-05-20 20:25:31','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(352,'Vegetables Salad','<br>\n','Peel, cut and wash all vegetables and cook with water and salt until tender.<br><br>Meanwhile make a dressing in a skillet with olive oil saute crushed garlic and sliced onion, add vinegar.<br><br>Put drained vegetables in a salad plate and pour the dressing over them, toss well.<br><br>You can made it with frozen of them vegetables according to package directions.<br>\n',6,0,0,1,0,45,7,7,2,10,9,30,'../files/recipes/vegetables salad.JPG','2014-06-04 18:58:17',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(353,'Cheese Cream Soup','<br>\n','In a large saucepan, over medium heat, melt butter and saute onion, gradually add flour in this mix and saute. add milk little by little and stir slowly to remove any lumps. Cook whisking constantly until thickened, (Do not boil). Add cheese and stir to it melted.<br>\n',4,0,0,2,0,27,13,9,6,19,9,10,'../files/recipes/Cream Cheese Soup