 let&nbsp;&nbsp; boil&nbsp;for 5&nbsp;minutes.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;\">Drain; add&nbsp;the sugar&nbsp;and\nbutter cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.</span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;\"><br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial,sans-serif;\">serve hot.<br></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; \"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; \"><br><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; \"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif; \" lang=\"ES\">.</span><span style=\"font-size:10.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";mso-fareast-font-family:=\"\" \"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#888888;mso-ansi-language:es\"=\"\" lang=\"ES\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\n',4,0,0,0,0,16,7,7,6,17,9,20,'../files/recipes/Glazed carrots.jpg','2014-05-18 03:03:03',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(201,'Tuna Salad','<br>\n','Cook elbow pasta following package directions. Meanwhile chop onion and drain the tuna can.<br><br>Drain the pasta and combine with all ingredients stirring well.<br><br>Refrigerate for one hour, serve whith soda crackers.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,9,7,9,8,10,6,12,'../files/recipes/tuna salad.jpeg','2014-04-25 06:59:35',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(202,'Potatoes in White Sauce','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt;\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt;\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#333333\"=\"\">Cut the\npotatoes&nbsp;and onions&nbsp;into rings.</span