font size=\"3\">Mashed&nbsp;potatoes and mix with&nbsp;the cream of&nbsp;</font>cheeses<font size=\"3\">. &nbsp;</font></font></p>\n\n\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; \"><span arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#333333\"=\"\"><font face=\"arial\">Add the&nbsp;yolks one\nby one and lastly add the <o:p></o:p>stirrings whites&nbsp;with\nthe baking powder. Wrap the mixture gently.<o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; \"><span arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#333333\"=\"\"><font face=\"arial\">Put into&nbsp;a greased pan&nbsp;and bake&nbsp;until golden. Server hot</font><font size=\"3\"><o:p></o:p></font></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0.0001pt; background-image: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; background-color: rgb(245, 245, 245); background-position: initial initial; background-repeat: initial initial; \"><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt;font-family:\" arial\",\"sans-serif\";=\"\" mso-fareast-font-family:\"times=\"\" new=\"\" roman\";color:#333333\"=\"\">&nbsp;</span></p>\n',4,0,0,0,0,27,7,7,6,14,9,25,'../files/recipes/Potato and cheese souffle.jpg','2014-05-15 08:04:55',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(205,'Friend Coconut Cake','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF&nbsp; and&nbsp; 3 greased and floured 9\" layer pans.<br><br>Blend cake mix, pudding mix, water, eggs and oil in large mixer bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer 4 minutes. Stir in coconut and walnuts. Pour into greased pans. Bake for 35 minutes. Cool in pans for 15 minutes; remove and cool on rack. <br><br>Fill&nbsp; and frost with coconut-cream cheese frosting.<br>\n',12,0,0,0,0,11,7,9,9,13,6,60,'../files/recipes/creamy coconout pie.JPG','2014-05-22 00:16:02',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(206,'Coconut and Cream Cheese Frosting','<br>\n','Melt 2 tablespoons butter in skillet, add 1/4 cup coconut; stir constantly over low heat until golden brown. Spread coconut on absorbent paper to cool. <br><br>Cream 2 tablespoons butter with cream cheese. Add milk and sugar alternately, beating well. Add vanilla; stir in 1 3/4 cups of the coconut.<br><br>Spread on top and sides of cake layers. Sprinkle with remaining coconut.<br>\n',0,0,0,0,0,11,13,9,8,14,9,20,'','2014-03-16 02:29:01',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(207,'Red Beans Soup','<br>\n','Soak beans in water for an hour. Cut pork into medium size pieces and saute to release the fat it can have, In the pressure cooker, cook the beans for 20 minutes or until tender with water soaking, pork without the fat, and chorizo.<br><br>Crush garlic, chop onion, green pepper, cumin, oregano, black pepper and saute all in reserved fat pork. When the beans are tender add the saute, tomato sauce, potatoes and squash peeled and washed cut into quarters.<br><br>Bring to boil for 15 minutes, until the potatoes and squash are tender and slightly thickened broth.<br><br><br><br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,13,7,9,3,14,9,45,'../files/recipes/red beans soup.JPG','2014-03-17 20:10:07',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(209,'Cuban Plantain Tostones','<br>\n','Peel plantain and cut them into 1\" thick and put in the skillet with cold&nbsp; oil. Cook until they begin to golden.&nbsp;Remove of oil and place on absorbent paper. Fold other paper over slices pound flat with the palm of the hand, Dip in salted water and cook for a second time in hot oil until golden. Serve hot.<br>\n',4,0,0,1,0,205,7,9,6,14,9,20,'../files/recipes/tostones.JPG','2014-06-06 05:00:40',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(211,'Pineapple Sundae','<br>\n','Twist crown from pineapple. Cut pineapple lengthwise in quarters. Cut fruit from shell. Core and cut pineapple into chunks. Divide among eight 1 -cup souffle or dessert bowls.<br><br>In blender, mix milk and dry pudding, 40 seconds (or beat together until blended). Transfer to a bowl and chill 10 minutes. Spoon evenly over pineapple. Top with nuts and coconut.<br>\n',820,0,0,0,0,31,13,7,8,13,9,20,'','2014-05-21 19:14:53',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(212,'Tamale Casserole','<br>\n','Cut meat into medium pieces and marinate with garlic and lemon, saute the meat&nbsp;&nbsp; . and add enough oil to make a sauce with onion, green pepper, tomato sauce and cook wine, and cook. <br><br>Mix the corn with water. drain and add with meat and sauce add salt and black pepper to taste, cook for about 1 hour stirring occasionally to prevent sticking.<br><br>Serve hot<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,21,7,8,6,14,9,70,'','2014-05-16 19:36:21',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(213,'Potato Tambor','<br>\n','Peel potatoes and cook them with salt until tender, make a mash potatoes with butter.<br><br>Make a <a href=\"Havana-Ground-Beef\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">Havana Ground Beef</a>&nbsp;recipe as it appear in this recipe book.<br><br>Coat 13\" x 9\" pan with cooking spray and put in the bottom of pan a half of mashed potatoes; pour over it all picadillo and cover with remaining mashed potatoes.<br><br>Sprinkle with cheddar cheese and bake 20 minutes or until sheese is malted.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,117,7,8,6,14,9,50,'../files/recipes/potato tambor.jpg','2014-05-21 22:35:48',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(214,'Hamburger and Salad','<br>\n','In a blender mix onion, garlic, lemon, salt and pepper. In a medium bowl mix all ingredients.<br><br>Make 4 balls and a crush with your hand to make a hamburgers. Marinate for an hour before, cook in a grill or in a skillet.<br><br>Serve in bread with lettuce, carrot,&nbsp; tomatoes and mustard.<br><br>\n',4,0,1,0,0,11,7,8,5,6,6,25,'../files/recipes/mirta hamburguers.jpg','2014-03-16 09:48:59',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(217,'Fried Malanga','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Peel and grate the malanga and mix with others ingredients.<br><br>Fry by tablespoons in medium hot oil until golden.<br>\n	\n	',5,0,0,0,0,429,7,7,6,17,9,8,'../files/recipes/fried malanga.JPG','2014-06-06 08:16:39','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(218,'Magic Coconut Cake','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350 oF and coat 3 pans 9\" with cooking spray.<br><br>Separate the white eggs from the yolks. Sift the flour.&nbsp; In a big bowl with electric mixer beat the egg whites until stiff, gradually adding sugar and yolks one by one and then dry ingredients alternately with water. Wrapping it around gently without stirring.<br><br>Pour the mixture into pans. Bake 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan or wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pans and cool completely on wire rack.<br><br>Make a <a href=\"http://recipescookbook.org/recipe/How-to-make-Coconut-Pudding\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">Coconut Pudding</a> recipe as it appear in this recipe book.<br><br>Spread pudding between layers, top and sides of cake. Sprinkle top with coconut flake and cocoa powder unsweetened.<br>\n',12,0,0,0,0,178,7,9,9,13,6,45,'../files/recipes/magi coconout cake.jpg','2014-05-20 19:06:51',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(216,'Rice Pudding','<br>\n','Wash rice and cook with water, and&nbsp; cinnamon stick until tender and with a little water, add milks and salt. Stirring occasionally until thick.<br><br>Pour into 8 dish bowls or dessert plate and sprinkle with ground cinnamon.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,26,7,8,6,13,9,45,'../files/recipes/rice pudding.jpg','2014-05-22 00:07:04','',0,0,1,0,0,0,NULL),(221,'Coconut Pudding','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In a small bowl, beat egg whites and set aside. In a large bowl. <br>whisk 1 cup of milk and cornstarch until completely smooth. In a large heavy saucepan, combine remaining milk, sugar and salt. Mix well. Bring to a boil over high heat, whisking constantly. Remove pan from heat,<br><br>Gradually whisk 1 cup of hot mixture into the egg whites. Pour mixture back into pan. Cook over medium low heat for 2 minutes, whisking constantly. do not boil. Remove pan from heat. Pour into serving dishes. Cool to room temperature.<br><br><br><br><br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,11,7,9,6,13,9,20,'../files/recipes/cocconout puddin.JPG','2014-03-15 20:28:41','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(220,'Almond Muffins','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 375oF and line 24 muffins pans with paper liners.<br><br>Sift flour, salt and baking powder together. Cream butter, add sugar;&nbsp; beat until light and fluffy, Beat in eggs one at a time, add&nbsp; flour mixture alternately with milk; beat well after each addition. Stir in almond extract and almond slices. Put into prepared pans,<br><br>Bake about 20 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. <br>cool into pan on wire racks 10 minutes and remove from pans. Cool completely on wire rack.<br>\n',24,0,0,1,0,44,7,9,9,15,9,35,'../files/recipes/mufflin.jpg','2014-06-05 18:46:37',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(222,'Plantain Fufu','	\n		<b id=\"internal-source-marker_0.13422077801078558\" style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; \"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; \"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; \">The word fufÃº gets to us through the Ghana cook in Africa. During the pre-columbian period the Ashanti ethnic group prepared a food by boiling yams and cassava. When these vegetables are ground together, the food acquired a white color, named fufuo</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; \">.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; \"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; \">But, when the Latin people tell fufÃº, they refer to the meal made with plantain. The plantains grown in Meridional Asia, but they arrived to Africa in thirteen century and then to America around 1516, from The Canarias.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; \"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; \"><br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; \"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; \">At the same time the banana reaches the Americas, the first boatloads of slaves were coming. The story tells at the time of British occupation in Cuba the slaves only received for meal boiled and mashed plantain. The ration was distributed between slaves while screaming the voice: </span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; \">food, food!</span><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; \">, and since the slaves understood fu fu, this term was plated in the history forever.</span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; \"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; \"><br></span></p><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"text-align: justify; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; \"><span style=\"font-size: 16px; font-family: Arial; background-color: transparent; font-weight: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap; \">The plantain fufÃº is well known in Cuba by many different names. In Havana we used to call it fufÃº, machuquillo or matajÃ­baro; in the East of Cuba is called mofongo or mangÃº. In some places of Caribbean is also called Mogo.</span></p></b>\n	\n	','	\n		Cut plantains in 3 pieces, put in the pot with water and salt cover and let boil until tender. <br><br>Meanwhile, cut pork chop into small pieces and remove the fat, Saute bits of fat and then the pork, remove them of skillet and set aside.<br><br>Drain plantains, remove the peel and heart, mash it with a fork. <br><br>Saute garlic in skillet with fat until golden brown, add the plantains, pork chops and pork rinds stir well. <br><br>Serve hot<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,2,0,873,7,8,6,14,9,35,'../files/recipes/plantain fufu.JPG','2014-06-05 15:30:11','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-01-29 13:00:03'),(223,'Strawberry Jam','<br>\n','Combine water, lemon and sugar let boil 5 minutes in medium-low heat. Add strawberries and let it boil, stir frequently until thickened.<br><br>Pour in serving bowl.<br>\n',15,0,0,0,0,9,13,7,6,13,9,25,'../files/recipes/strawberry jam.jpg','2014-04-08 20:31:36',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(224,'Chicken Sandwich Spread','<br>\n','In a processor food grind a chicken.<br><br>Cut olive in four. In a medium bowl with a fork crush cream cheese, add olive, chicken, sweet relish and mayonnaise, mix well.<br><br>Serve with cracker or&nbsp; make little sandwich for the party.<br>\n',10,0,1,0,0,75,7,9,8,5,8,12,'../files/recipes/pasta de bocadito.jpg','2014-05-29 12:15:35',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(225,'Roast Chicken','<br>\n','Marinate chicken with crushed garlic, chopped onion, black pepper, oregano, salt and sour orange for an hour or more.<br><br>Brown chicken in the pot with oil, add marinate and cooking wine, let it simmer until tender and sauce has been made.<br><br>Serve hot.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,16,7,8,6,16,8,60,'../files/recipes/roast chicken.jpg','2014-05-08 16:56:37',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(227,'Stewed Meat','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Marinate the steaks with sour orange juice salt and pepper. for an hour or more.<br><br>Peel and wash potatoes, cut into ring of 1 centimeter wide and put them in a casserole.<br><br>Slice onion and cook it in hot oil; add garlic and oregano. When tender, add steaks and fry them well, and put into potatoes casserole.&nbsp; Add cooking wine, rest of marinade and water. Cook them slowly, until tender. <br><br>Serve them with the sauce over rice and salad<br>\n	\n	',5,0,0,0,0,10,7,8,6,6,8,35,'../files/recipes/stewed meat.JPG','2014-04-10 00:38:53','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(230,'Strawberry Delight Cake','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF and coat&nbsp; 3 pans 9\" with cooking spray.<br><br>Sift flour, add baking powder and salt, sift again. In a medium bowl beat butter until creamy add sugar gradually, then eggs, milk and vanilla, mix well.<br><br>Add flour without beating, mix with gentle rolling motion. Pour into pans.<br><br>Bake 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes, remove from pans. Cool completely on wire rack.<br><br>Spread strawberry jam between layers.<br><br>Make 7 minutes frosting and spread on top and sides of cake. <br><br>Garnish with strawberries.<br>\n',12,0,0,0,0,14,16,9,9,13,8,45,'../files/recipes/strawberry delight cake.jpg','2014-03-30 03:57:24',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(232,'Vegetarian Congri Rice','	\n		<div>Born in Latin America, the mixture of rice and beans is a suigeneris spectacle to the site and the palate. The story says that slaves, brought from Africa five centuries ago, who did not have enough resources to eat, cooked &nbsp;beans and rice together in a clay pot under the sun.</div><div><br></div><div>We do not known exactly the place of its origin, but with small variations in its ingredients and/or its seasoning, rice and beans have become a typical dish of Latin America, making it a tradition in the Latin kitchen.</div><div><br></div><div>Each country named it differently; CongrÃ­ in Cuba, Moros in Dominican, Calentado in Colombia and Peru, Casamiento in Honduras and El Salvador, Casados in Guatemala, &nbsp;Gallo Pinto in Nicaragua and Pinto in Costa Rica. &nbsp;It is interesting how the different names arose.</div><div><br></div><div>Some in Central America, called it Gallo Pinto, because of having colors similar to a rooster with red feathers; but Nitza Villapol, quoting Don Fernando Ortizâ€™s book, tells about the name evolving from Creole, \"where the red beans are told Congo and rice to be told rizâ€. Others in Colonial Cuba called it\" Volunteers and Firefightersâ€, because the volunteers were always dressed in white as rice and the firefighters were the black people wearing shirts with red necks.</div><div><br></div><div>Now, the more interesting name of this food become â€œMoros y Cristianosâ€ (Moors and Christians); its name is so far at reality in which lived they potential creators, because it refers to the story of the Spanish conquest &nbsp;in the year 1492 , when the Catholic Kings threw aside the Moors in southern Spain where they had been established for more than eight centuries.</div><div><br></div><div>The color of the cooked rice with beans is similar to the dark color of the skin of the Moors, and this detail was quickly identified for the natives, who just so named their food.</div><div><br></div><div>Beyond gimmicks and names, rich in history, we offer CongrÃ­, a symbol of Cuban identity, to delight your palate with the great flavor of the Caribbean.</div>\n	\n	','	\n		Wash bean and soak them in water for an hour. Cook beans in the same soaking water in pressure cooker for 15 minutes or until tender, In a skillet with 4 tbsp of oil saute onion, garlic and pepper. Put beans with water, rice and salt in the rice cooker add the sauce from the skillet and mix.<br><br>When the rice is done wait 15 minutes, uncover and&nbsp;stir&nbsp;from the bottom.&nbsp;When served, stir again.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,1,0,0,216,7,8,3,14,9,40,'../files/recipes/cuban congri.JPG','2014-06-02 21:22:42','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-02-05 13:00:02'),(419,'St. Patrick Cake','	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 350oF, and coat 2 round 91/2 inch pan with cooking spray.<br><br>Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour batter into pans and bake for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean,cool in pan on wire racks 10 minutes, remove from pan; cool completely. Place cake layers top sides up, back in the clean pans; prick each layer with utility fork at 1/2 inch intervals. Pour 2 cup of the boiling water over lime gelatin in bowl; stir until gelatin is dissolved. Spoon over two layers and refrigerate 3 or 4 hours.<br><br>Meanwhile make a frosting, beat pudding mix and milk with a whisk for 2 minutes, stir in cool whip and add 4 drops of green color food.<br><br>Dip 1 layer in pan into warm water 10 seconds; invert on plate, gently shaking to loosen. Remove pan; spread layer with 1 cup of the frosting. Remove remaining layer from pan as above; invert on first layer. Remove pan;frost with remaining topping. Garnish with lollipop or as you wish. Refrigerate.<br>\n	\n	',12,0,0,0,0,13,7,9,9,13,10,120,'../files/recipes/st patricks cake.JPG','2014-04-30 20:09:56','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2013-08-21 17:53:01'),(233,'Spanish Omelet','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		In a 10\" Teflon frying pan,combine olive oil, onions finely chopped,&nbsp; and saute over low heat, stirring occasionally. Strain in a colander. Reserve onions and pour oil back into the frying pan. Add potatoes peeled and cubed and 1/4 salt. Mix cover and cook over low heat until tender. Remove potatoes and reserve.<br><br>Beat eggs and&nbsp; 3/4 tsp salt thoroughly, and mix with the reserved onios and potatoes. Turn heat to medium; add egg mixture so the oil in the frying pan browns the eggs rapidly. Immediately, reduce heat to low and cook until upper part is dry. Occasionally. move the frying pan back and forth and release borders.<br><br>When dry, put plate over and turn tortilla, slip again into frying pan and cook for 10 minutes on other side.<br>\n	\n	',8,0,0,1,0,43,17,8,6,14,9,40,'../files/recipes/Spanish omelet.JPG','2014-05-15 07:50:48','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2013-08-21 15:14:23'),(234,'Moros y Cristianos','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Wash beans and soak them in water for an hour. Cook beans in the same soaking water in pressure cooker for 15 minutes or until tender.<span style=\"font-style: italic;\"><br><br>In a skillet saute pork chop chopped in the little pieces, remove it, and if necessary&nbsp; add oil until 4 tablespoon of fat in it. saute onion, garlic, oregano, black pepper and green pepper.<br><br><br>Put beans with water, rice and salt in the rice cooker, add the sauce from the skillet and cook.<br><br>When the rice is done wait 15 minutes, uncover and stir from bottom.<br><br>When you serve stir in the fried pork chop and stir again from below to mix.<br></span>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,68,7,8,3,7,9,45,'../files/recipes/moros y cristianos.JPG','2014-06-07 22:54:00','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(235,'Mango Cake','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 325oF. Coat a bundt pan with cooking spray<br><br>Mix 2 cups flour with baking powder, set aside. In a large bowl beat cream cheese, butter, sugar and vanilla, add eggs one at a time, beating well each time you add another.Gradually beat in flour on low speed until well blended. Pour 1/3 of this mixture into a mold.<br><br>Peel and diced the mango and mix with the rest flour, incorporate it into the remaining batter and pour inside the mold.<br><br>Bake for 60 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pan, cool completely on wire rack.<br><br>Sprinkle powder sugar just before serving.<br>\n	\n	',16,0,0,0,0,45,13,9,9,13,9,85,'../files/recipes/Mango Cake.JPG','2014-05-10 18:01:37','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(236,'Tropical Salad','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Peeled, cut in chunks a mango, seedless grapes, halved and chicken large shreds.<br><br>Whisk mayonnaise, yogurt, salt and 1/3 cup chopped fresh mint in a serving bowl, add chicken, stir in mango, pineapple and grapes.<br><br>Top with pecans and narrow strips of fresh mint.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,14,7,8,8,10,9,20,'../files/recipes/tropical salad.JPG','2014-04-25 08:53:39','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(238,'Asparagus Salad','<br>\n','Bring about 1/2 inch water to boil in large skillet. Add asparagus; cover. Simmer 3 to 4 min. or until asparagus is crisp-tender; drain. Rinse asparagus with cool water; drain well on paper towels.<br><br>Meanwhile, mix mustard and lemon juice in small bowl. Gradually add oil, whisking constantly until well blended and thickened.<br><br>Place asparagus on plate; top with mustard sauce, cheese and lemon zest.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,17,13,8,6,17,9,15,'../files/recipes/asparagus salad.JPG','2014-03-22 06:00:54',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(239,'Cheese Stuffed Shells','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF.&nbsp; Coat 13\" x 9\" pan with cooking spray.<br><br>Bring to a boil shells in 5 cups water with salt to taste&nbsp; until tender.<br><br>In medium bowl combine eggs, ricotta cheese, mozzarella cheese and 3/4 cup parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.<br><br>Spoon about 2 tbsp mixture into each shell. Pour in baking dish, top with sauce, and sprinkle with remaining parmesan.<br><br>Bake for 30 minutes<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,14,10,9,9,4,9,50,'','2014-05-29 01:26:55',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(240,'Asparagus and Garlic','<br>\n','Trim bottom ends of asparagus. Heat oil in a pan and fry the bread until it is golden in color. Place in food processor. Saute garlic in the oil until it is golden and place in processor as well. Then saute the asparagus in this same oil for about 3 minutes. Add water, cover, and cook until asparagus is just tender.<br><br>While asparagus cooks beat the garlic and bread in the food processor. Slowly add vinegar and a couple tablespoon of the cooking fluid from the asparagus. Pour the mixture over the asparagus and salt to taste. Cook 5 minutes more or until asparagus is tender.<br><br>Sprinkle with parsley and serve.<br><br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,10,13,7,6,17,9,10,'../files/recipes/asparagus with garlic.JPG','2014-03-26 21:41:59',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(241,'Tortellini and Ham','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF&nbsp; and coat with cooking spray 9\" x 13\" pan.<br><br>Cook tortellini according to package directions. Add frozen broccoli during the last minute of cooking time. Drain.<br><br>Combine butter, basil, black pepper, garlic powder, mayonnaise, cream cheese and half and half in a large bowl. Mix well.<br><br>Fold in parmesan cheese, tortellini, broccoli and ham and spoon into a greased pan.<br><br>Bake for 30 minutes.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,12,10,8,9,4,8,60,'','2014-04-22 10:46:19',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(242,'Cool Salad','<br>\n','In&nbsp; a casserole cook pasta as directed on package, drain and cool.<br><br>Peel, core and&nbsp; diced apple, cut onion into small pieces, olive in four. Drain the tuna and put in a bowl, tear up with a fork.<br><br>Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, cover with clear wrap and chill.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,14,7,9,8,10,9,20,'../files/recipes/cold salad.jpg','2014-02-02 07:30:14',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(243,'Ham Steaks','<br>\n','Mix sugar and mustard and spread it on both sides of the steak.<br><br>Put it in a skillet or on a hot griddle. Cook it for about 10 minutes or until is melted sugar, and&nbsp; golden pineapple rings also with some of the same sugar that the ham looses<br>\n',2,0,0,0,0,13,13,8,9,6,8,15,'','2014-05-08 22:39:30',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(245,'Chicken Soup','<br>\n','In a pressure cooker with water put the chicken to boil , cook for 10 minutes.Discard&nbsp; the bones from&nbsp; the chicken and put back the boneless chicken meat to the pressure cooker.<br><br>Peel, dice and wash all ingredients, put it to&nbsp; boil in the&nbsp; cooker with salt,&nbsp; onion&nbsp; and garlic.<br><br>Close cooker, and bring up to full pressure on high heat. reduce heat and cook for 15 minutes. Remove cooker from heat, allow to cool naturally, open cooker.<br><br>Put the cooker back to the heat without pressure&nbsp; and pour inside angel hair capellini and cook until tender.<br><br><br><br><br>\n',6,0,0,1,0,28,7,8,3,14,9,60,'../files/recipes/Chicken Soup.JPG','2014-05-21 22:30:38','',1,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(246,'Country Fried Steak','<br>\n','Crush the steak, marinate with crushed garlic, onion rings, salt and lemon juice, cover it , store in the refrigerator for at least an hour.<br><br>Before you cook the steaks, beat&nbsp; white eggs with a dash of salt, add yolk eggs and stir.<br><br>Drain the steaks and cover them in beaten eggs and breadcrumbs twice.<br><br>Fry in hot oil until golden brown.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,11,7,8,6,6,9,90,'../files/recipes/breaded steak.JPG','2014-04-03 21:21:12',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(247,'Ropa Vieja (Shredded Beef)','<div>Do you know the similarity between food and clothes?</div><div><br></div><div>The story tells, a poor man waiting for his family for dinner, and not get money to buy the odd food to serve, out of his closet all her clothes, as old as great was his poverty, and began to cook with all the love he felt for his family. At the end of the stew clothing became a wonderful meat.</div><div><br></div><div>This legend gives name to the famous dish \"Ropa Vieja\" which was originally a dish made of leftovers, it was used to cook pork, chicken, beef that had been the previous day, adding to it evolving chickpeas and spices like oregano , thyme, bay leaf and perfumed with white wine.</div><div><br></div><div>A native of the Canary Islands, the portion of land, which drove the sailors who sailed to the New World, is not difficult to guess how to become part of the Latin tradition, for thousands of canaries were established in America looking for new horizons life, and contributed to the formation and development of the customs of these peoples</div><div><br></div><div>The plate is therefore in Latin cuisine, transformed to the new way of making the fledgling company, a plate of shredded beef cooked in tomato sauce.</div><div>There remains the initial question, what is the similarity? Simple... a work of infinite love.</div>\n','Cook the meat in water until tender, put aside the meat and make a soup with broth.<br><br>Rip the meat into thin strands , cut onion into thin rings and pepper into strips, crush the garlic and saute in medium hot oil with onion, pepper and tomato sauce, add remaining ingredients and let cook covered over low heat about 15 minutes, stir occasionally to prevent sticking.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,34,7,8,6,6,9,60,'../files/recipes/ropa vieja.JPG','2014-05-20 03:30:55',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-02-12 13:00:03'),(248,'Chicken Divan','<br>\n','Boil chicken, skin and debone it. Cook frozen broccoli (maybe in microwave).<br><br>While chicken and broccoli are cooking slice&nbsp; up bunch of fresh mushrooms. Place chicken in 13\"&nbsp; x 9\" pan, then mushrooms, then broccoli. <br><br>In a separate bowl mix mayonaise, soup and lemon juice together. Pour this mixture over the chicken, mushrooms and broccoli.<br><br>Pour grated cheddar cheese over all of this stuff. Melt butter in the micro and add bread crumbs to it.&nbsp; Place the butter crumb stuff on top of the cheddar cheese.<br><br>Bake at 350oF for 30 minutes or until bubbly.<br><br><br><br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,16,13,8,9,16,8,50,'../files/recipes/Chiken Divan.JPG','2014-05-26 09:00:38',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(249,'Salt of Chives','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 350oF <br><br>Cut chives with the scissors and mix with salt.<br><br>Bake the mixture to dry the leaves and combine the flavors.<br><br>Store in an airtight jar.<br><br>Make your own salt&nbsp; of chives to add all kinds of dishes.<br>\n',0,0,0,0,0,12,7,7,9,14,9,20,'','2014-03-22 14:08:59',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(250,'Cottage Cheese and Chives','<br>\n','Mix cottage cheese with mustard. Peel the shallot, chop finelly and combine with cottage cheese mixture.<br><br>Wash and dry the leaves of chive and cut very fine with scissors. <br>add 2/3 of the chive to the mixture and season with salt and pepper to taste. Mix well.<br><br>Add the remaining chives.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,37,13,8,8,14,9,15,'','2014-05-19 06:03:31',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(251,'Almond Chicken','Almonds are originated in West Asia, North Africa and the Mediterranean. The huge geographical area where this seed grown, in addition to their exquisite flavor was direct consequence of their fast spreading. Quickly, almond was used to feed men and animals.<br><br>Since ancient times, almonds have been used in cookbooks, being tasted alike by kings and commoners, and their use has taken world-class after the processes of conquest and fusion of cultures. An example of this is chicken with almonds, originating in China and brought to the Americas by their creators.<br><br>The story tells, at time of construction the pacific Railroad, in 1800 year; many Chinese were brought to work in that construction and once to it finish, its worked didnâ€™t leave at Canada ; they established there and dedicated to open smalls â€œcafÃ©â€ in this country.<br><br>For they was very difficulty found the real ingredients for they native dishes, so the question was immediate, How to do the chicken with almonds, for example? The inventiveness and desire to progress led to victory: they replaced many of their original recipes ingredients for which existed and adapted to new conditions of life assimilation the Canadian customs. However the achievements the Chinese food prevail becoming in a novelty for the Canadian community.<br><br>\n','<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:WordDocument>\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\n  <w:TrackMoves></w:TrackMoves>\n  <w:TrackFormatting></w:TrackFormatting>\n  <w:PunctuationKerning></w:Punctua