:en-us;mso-fareast-language:en-us;mso-bidi-language:ar-sa\"=\"\">Cut the dried jerky into four pieces and soak it the previous night. The next morning drain it.<br><br>In a large saucepan place the soaked jerked beef, cut chicken into two parts, simmer about an hour. Add the skirt and the mass of chopped pork, and simmer another hour or so.<br><br>While the meat is cooking make a sauce with two tablespoons oil, onion, garlic, pepper, tomato sauce and salt to taste. Peel, and cut ears of corn, white malanga, green&nbsp; plantain, yucca, sweet&nbsp; potato, half way ripe plantain, when the meats are tender add it in the same order they appear in the recipe, each time you add&nbsp; plantain pour lemon juice to check them so that the broth is not dark. Add the stir-fry, salt and stir well.<br>Ground corn mixed with a teaspoon of salt, two tablespoons of milk, two tablespoons of oil and saute the garlic in it. Take the dough and form small balls. <br>When meats are almost soft add half way ripe plantain and put the balls on the food in the broth. Cover and simmer, do not stir until cooked corn balls.<br><br>To thicken the broth crush two or three pieces of root in a little broth and add it to the broth.<br><br>Can also soften meats and viands toughest pressure cooker and saving time and effort.<br><br>You can use beef skirt or other beef.<br><br style=\"mso-special-character:line-break\">\n</span><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" DefUnhideWhenUsed=\"true\"\n  DefSemiHidden=\"true\" DefQFormat=\"false\" DefPriority=\"99\"\n  LatentStyleCount=\"267\">\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"0\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"Normal\"></w:LsdException>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"9\" SemiHidden=\"false\"\n   UnhideWhenUsed=\"false\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"heading 1\"></w:LsdException>\n  <w:LsdException Locked=\"false\" Priority=\"9\" QFormat=\"true\" Name=\"heading 2\"><