to ice water. When cold, drain and transfer to plate, coat with 1 tbsp. canola oil. Reserve.<br><br><br>Cut chicken into 1/2\" each strip. Cut scallions into 1\" pieces,minced peeled fresh ginger, minced garlic and cut peppers into 1\" pieces.<br><br><br>Heat wok or skillet over high heat. Add 4 tbs. canola oil; swirl to coat pan. When hot, add chicken; stir-fry until cooked through, about 6 minutes. Transfer chicken to plate.<br><br>Add remaining 2 tbsp.canola oil to wok; swirl and when hot, add garlic, ginger and scallions. Stir fry until soft. Add soy sauce; cook, stirring up bits from bottom of pan. Add honey and lime juice; simmer until reduced by one-quarter, Return chicken with any juice in plate to wok; add peppers, then noodles. Cook, stirring, until hot, about 2 minutes.<br><br>Serve drizzled with sesame oil.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,13,11,8,6,4,9,45,'../files/recipes/chicken lo mein.JPG','2014-06-06 00:58:58','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(267,'Vinegared Shrimp','<br>','Preheat oven to 375oF<br><br>Prick potatoes several times with a fork; wrap&nbsp; in foil. Bake until cooked through, 1 -1 1/2 hours.<br><br>Meanwhile, in bowl, combine vinegars, sugar and soy sauce; until sugar is dissolved. reserve.<br><br>Heat large saute pan over medium-high heat. Add 1 tbsp oil. Add shrimp; saute stirring, until shrimp turn pink. Transfer to bowl; reserve.<br><br>Add remaining 1 tbsp oil to pan. When hot, add thinly sliced shallots, minced garlic and minced peeled fresh ginger. Saute until soft,&nbsp; about 2 minutes. Add soy sauce mixture; simmer, stirring up browned bits from bottom of pan, until mixture is reduced by half, Add edamame, tomato and shrimp. Simmer until shrimp are cooked. Whisk in butter and season with salt and pepper.<br><br>Trim ends from potatoes;cut in half lengthwise. Divide potatoes among four plates; top with shrimp and sauce.<br>.<br>',4,0,0,0,0,14,13,8,9,9,9,135,'','2014-05-19 20:53:44',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(268,'Cuban Chicken and Rice','<br>\n','Cut chicken into pieces and marinate with crushed garlic and sour orange.In a casserole heat oil and brown the chicken, add onion and green pepper chopped, tomato sauce, salt, pepper, bay leaf and saffron to color, cook wine and chicken broth.Cook&nbsp; until chicken is half cooked, wash the rice and add. Simmer until the grain is open and soft. <br><br>Stir the rice at the bottom and add the green peas and stir again.<br><br>Garnish with red pepper<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,40,7,8,6,16,9,60,'../files/recipes/cuban chicken rice.JPG','2014-05-15 06:37:04',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(269,'Chocolate berry cake','<br>\n','Coat bottom of&nbsp; two pan 8 inch&nbsp; and set aside. Preheat oven to 350oF.<br><br>Sift the flour, add melted butter and half of the sour cream.Beat for 1 minute at the lowest speed of electric mixer. Stir in remaining sour cream, 1/2 cup chocolate and yolks, mix for another minute. Add the egg white beaten with sugar, wrapping the dough gently. Pour into pans and bake for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pan. Cool completely on wire rack.<br><br>Put the berries jam between layers of cake, set aside. Whip the cream milk gradually adding the sugar and remaining cocoa powder until having a thick consistency, cover the cake with the cream and&nbsp; garnish with different berries.<br><br>Always keep in the refrigerator to prevent the cream decompose.<br>\n',12,0,1,0,0,29,13,9,9,13,8,60,'../files/recipes/chocolate berry cake.jpg','2014-05-16 19:22:51',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(270,'Fried Pork Chops','<br>\n','Combine all ingredients and pour over pork chops, put it in a refrigerator for at least&nbsp; an hour.<div><br>In a pressure cooker put the pork chops, marinade, cook wine and water, close the cooker, bring to full pressure on high heat. reduce heat and cook for 10 minutes. Remove cooker from heat, allow to cool naturally, open cooker.<br><br>In a skillet with oil saute the pork chops until golden brown.<br>\n</div>',4,0,0,0,0,19,7,8,6,6,8,30,'../files/recipes/fried pork chops.jpg','2014-04-16 02:34:19',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(271,'Special Chicken Rice','<br>\n','Make a broth with chicken, remove chicken from broth and cool. Chop up the chicken, cut the onion, green pepper and garlic into small pieces. <br><br>In a skillet, with 2 tbs of oil saute 2 tbs of onion, pepper and garlic, add black pepper.<br><br>In a casserole put this sauce, salt, chicken, rice and broth. Let it cook over high heat until it boils, then over medium heat about 30 minutes, or until done. Stir from the bottom.<br><br>In a skillet with 3 tbsp of oil, saute remaining onion, add&nbsp; drained mushrooms and continue keep frying to combine flavors about 3 minutes. Incorporate into the finished rice and stir well to bring them together.<br>\n',8,0,1,0,0,14,7,8,6,16,7,70,'../files/recipes/chicken, rice and mushrooms.JPG','2014-03-27 04:39:42',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(272,'Meatballs','<br>\n','Cut really small garlic, onion and green pepper. Combine meat, 2 tbsp each onion and green pepper, milk salt, black pepper and breadcrumbs, mold into a medium balls. Roll in flour and fry in hot oil until golden brown. Remove meatballs from oil and set aside.<br><br>Prepare the following sauce: saute in 1/4 cup oil, garlic, onion and green pepper, add remaining ingredients and stir well.<br><br>Place meatballs in sauce and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.<br>\n',8,0,0,0,0,17,13,8,6,6,9,45,'../files/recipes/meatball.jpg','2014-03-31 16:15:22',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(273,'Pasta with Meatballs','<br>\n','Make&nbsp;<a href=\"http://recipescookbook.org/recipe/How-to-make-Meatballs\" title=\"\" target=\"_blank\">Meatballs</a> recipe as it appear in this recipe book.&nbsp;Meanwhile, cook the pasta as directed on package, drain in a colander and&nbsp; return to casserole, mix it with corn.&nbsp;When the Meatballs are ready, combine with the pasta and sprinkle cheese over it. Enjoy<br><br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,11,10,8,6,4,9,45,'../files/recipes/pasta and meatball.JPG','2014-05-18 06:29:37',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(275,'Devil Eggs','<br>\n','Boil eggs, let them cool and cut in half, carefully remove the yolks and mash them.<br><br>In food processor cut ham, onion and garlic, add the yolks and mix with mayonnaise and salt.<br><br>Fill the eggs with this mixture and chill before serving. Garnish with bit red pepper or whatever you want.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,15,7,8,6,14,9,30,'../files/recipes/devil egs.JPG','2014-04-22 06:23:59',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(276,'White Rice','<div>The presence of rice in the food of so many countries of the world is extremely interesting. Its popularity is reflected in the popular Latin notion \"si no hay arroz servido, no se ha comido\" (if there is no rice served, the meal is incomplete); and although eating rice on a daily basis may appear to be a custom belonging to more of a peasant lifestyle, the widespread consumption of rice indicates that it indeed holds a prominent role in the culinary arts.</div><div><br></div><div>Rice has been cultivated almost as long as the age of man, its cultivation having started as early as 8200-7800 BC. &nbsp;Rice quickly gained prominence in China and southern Asia, and was brought to Europe via Mesopotamia where it was even used by King Dario as currency for trade. Not much later, the Arab nation introduced rice to Spain, from which it would later travel to the Americas in the sixteenth century.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Rice today is prepared in many different ways. Due to European and Asiatic migration, the fact is that over the generations rice has become ingrained in the roots of peoples worldwide. It now serves as the basis of thousands of recipes. Even today with all the decadent options available, who is not attracted by the scent of freshly cooked rice?</div>\n','Wash the rice. In a pressure cooker with 1 ounce of oil fry the rice for 3 minutes, add water and salt and stir well. Close cooker and bring to full pressure on high heat. Reduce heat and cook for 2 minutes. Remove cooker from heat. Allow to cool naturally&nbsp; Open cooker, stir from bottom.&nbsp;Serve hot.<br>\n',4,0,0,1,0,65,13,7,3,7,9,10,'../files/recipes/white rice.jpg','2014-05-21 07:01:00',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-03-05 13:00:02'),(280,'Hummus','<br>\n','Drain the chickpeas. Mix 2 tbsp of the liquid extracted to the chickpeas with all ingredients in the bowl of a food processor and blend them until the hummus is coarsely pureed. Pour them in a bowl with a capacity of two cups. Serve with pita chips, crackers or tortilla chips.\n',0,0,0,0,0,15,13,7,8,3,6,10,'','2014-03-28 14:54:21',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(317,'Pasta Shrimp  Salad','<br>\n','Prepare pasta as directed on package, drain.<div><br></div><div>In skillet mix dressing and soy sauce cook at medium high heat, add shrimp, cook stirring until are pink, about 10 minutes.</div><div><br></div><div>In a salad bowl mix pasta with diced and seeded cucumber, chopped cilantro and green pepper, peanut, cheese and shrimp &nbsp;toss well.</div><div><br></div><div>May serve hot or cold.</div>\n',20,0,0,0,0,13,13,8,6,10,6,6,'../files/recipes/shrimp salad.JPG','2014-05-18 06:46:13',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(318,'Merengues','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 275oF<div><br></div><div>In a bowl &nbsp;with electric mixer in medium speed beat white eggs until firm, add sugar gradually and beat for 20 minutes.</div><div><br></div><div>In 2 cookies sheets, place by spoonful the mixed, and bake 40 minutes.</div><div><br></div><div>Put off the oven, let stand the merengues 2 hours at least in the oven. Do not open the door.</div><div><br></div><div>I make at night and set in oven over night.</div>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,13,13,9,9,12,9,140,'../files/recipes/merenguitos.JPG','2014-05-13 03:20:07','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(319,'Milk Balls','<br>\n','&nbsp;In a medium bowl beat eggs add milk and form small balls.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>In a casserole mix water, sugar and cinnamon and bring to boil for 3 minutes, then fry the balls in the syrup until golden.</div><div><br></div><div>Serve with syrup.</div>\n',4,0,1,0,0,6,7,8,6,13,9,15,'','2014-04-04 06:10:19',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(320,'Corn Fritters','<br>\n','Sift flour,baking powder. salt and sugar; set aside. Combine eggs, milk and butter and mix well. Fold egg mixture into dry ingredients. Add corn last.<div><br></div><div>Drop by tablespoon into hot oil.&nbsp;</div><div>deep &nbsp;fry until golden brown.</div><div><br></div><div>Sprinkle with powered sugar. Serve warm.<br><div><br></div></div>\n',4,0,0,0,0,15,7,8,6,14,9,20,'../files/recipes/sweet corn fritter.JPG','2014-05-06 04:13:52',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(321,'Italian Pesto Chicken','<br>','Heat oil in large skillet on medium heat. Add chicken and garlic; cook and stir 4 or 5 minutes. Stir in peppers; cook 3 to 4 minutes or until chicken is done, stirring frequently.<br>Stir in pesto and juice from 1 lemon half; top with cheese. Cover, cook on low heat until cheese is melted.<br>Spoon over pasta.<br>Serve with remaining lemon half, cut into wedges.<br>',4,0,0,0,0,19,10,9,6,16,9,20,'','2014-03-24 03:28:41',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(322,'Freiso','Eating Freiso for breakfast is wonderful; everybody in our family likes this delicate plate. The way this recipe is cooked has been in the family recipes for over 70 years. My great-grandmother Lola brought it from Spain, when she immigrates to Cuba, my grandmother specialized in them, especially to give us the pleasure and my mom followed this tradition.<br><br>The Freiso is a variant of French crepes or Crepas as call it in Spain; the different consist in the singular way of prepare the pasta and the mode of fry it in hot oil, the result is a smooth and fine tort, you eat adding powdered sugar.<br><br>The way to do Freiso keeps going from generation to generation. In this moment my children learn prepare it while having fun .This to help our family not to miss the secret of our ancestors.<br>\n','Beat all ingredients in a blender.<div><br></div><div>In a 8 inch nonstick skillet pour a1/8 tsp. vegetable oil, pour 1/4 cup batter into center of skillet, lift and turn pan to cover bottom, cook until lightly browned, turn and brown the other side, remove and sprinkle with sugar.</div><div><br></div><div>Repeat with remaining batter. Stack in top or the other, roll up and enjoy.</div>\n',4,0,1,0,0,28,17,8,6,13,9,25,'','2014-05-01 17:45:49',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(324,'Chick Pea Casserole','<br>\n','Wash chick peas and soak in 3 cups water for 2 hours. Drain and put in a casserole with 5 cups water, beef cutted in chunks, ham and chorizo; cook in medium heat for 2 hours or until all are tender. (In a pressure cooker, cook for 25 minutes.)<div><br></div><div>Drain in colander, in the broth cook potatoes and cabbage (cut in four).</div><div><br></div><div>In a skillet with olive oil saute chopped onion add chick peas, beef, dice ham and chorizo sliced, add potatoes and cabbage from the broth and cook for 10 minutes stirring to mix the flavor.</div><div><br></div><div>To make a soup add noodles to the broth cook for 5 minutes<br><br>You can use beef skirt or other beef.<br><div><br></div><div><br></div></div>\n',6,0,0,0,0,19,17,8,6,14,9,240,'../files/recipes/Chick Pea Casserolle.JPG','2014-05-16 21:21:33',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(325,'Pesto Genovese','<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:WordDocument>\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\n  <w:TrackMoves></w:TrackMoves>\n  <w:TrackFormatting></w:TrackFormatting>\n  <w:PunctuationKerning></w:PunctuationKerning>\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas></w:ValidateAgainstSchemas>\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\n  <w:DoNotPromoteQF></w:DoNotPromoteQF>\n  <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther>\n  <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian>\n  <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE