 pan for 5 minutes and remove to a wire rack. Serve warm.<br>',6,0,0,0,0,48,16,7,9,12,9,95,'','2014-06-04 17:35:26',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(357,'Cake Sandwich','	\n		Sandwich\'s name becomes part of the food history when the English aristocrat John Montagu, IV Count of Sandwich, in 1762, during a card game that lasted 24 hours, asked his cook to prepare meat between two slices of bread to satisfy your hunger without dirtying your fingers.<br><br>However, the origins of this recipe, dating back to ancient times when the Jewish sage, Hillel, the Elder, wrapped lamb and bitter herbs between two pieces of&nbsp; old-fashioned soft matzah, flat unleavened&nbsp; bread during the Passover.<br><br>The immediate precursors of the plate can be placed in the taverns of the Netherlands during the sixteenth century, where they prepared meats hanging from the roof beams with butter and bread for travelers and residents.<br><br>At times of industrial capitalism, the popularity of the recipe was on the rise, as the working class need a functional food, i.e., fast, easy to carry and inexpensive to allow him to renew forces while working; the sandwich, which possessed these characteristics, it became one of the favorite dishes of people, coming from a little part of the food worldwide.<br><br>Over time various types have appeared sandwich, even some who eat with silverware, as the recipe that we present today: The Sandwich cake, which made the modern Cuban cuisine, a book compiled by Nitza Villapol, is not certainly a unique variant as preparing sandwich, which for its exquisite taste beautiful presentation and easy preparation, has gained support in different regions of the country.<br><br><br>\n	\n	','	\n		<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:WordDocument>\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\n  <w:TrackMoves></w:TrackMoves>\n  <w:TrackFormatting></w:TrackFormatting>\n  <w:PunctuationKerning></w:PunctuationKerning>\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas></w:ValidateAgainstSchemas>\n  <w: