i.JPG','2014-03-23 01:30:13',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(360,'Beef Wraps','<br>','Cook the ground beef and garlic in a large skillet over medium heat until the beef is well browned, stirring often to separate meat. Pour off any fat.<br>Stir the broth in the skillet and cook until the mixture is hot and bubbling.<br>&nbsp;Place 1 lettuce leaf onto each tortilla. Spoon about 1/2 cup beef mixture down the center of each tortilla. Top each with 2 slices of tomatoes and 2 slices of onion.<br>wrap tortilla around the filling.<br>',4,0,0,0,0,7,8,9,6,6,9,25,'','2014-05-02 04:43:43',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(361,'Parmesan Crusted Chicken','<br>\n','Preheat oven to 425 oF.<br>In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise and cheese. On baking sheet, arrange chicken. Evenly top with mayonnaise mixture, then sprinkle with bread crumbs.<br>bake 20 minutes or until the chicken is thoroughly cooked.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,20,16,9,9,6,9,30,'../files/recipes/Parmesan Crusted Chicken.JPG','2014-06-04 17:00:47',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(363,'Beef and Potatoes','<br>\n','Cut up beef in regular pieces and wash. Mix minced garlic, sliced onion, salt, oregano, black pepper and lemon juice and rub beef with this mix. <br><br>Place casserole with oil over medium heat and saute the beef, add the marinade and others ingredients except olives, raisin, capers and pared and quartered potatoes. <br><br>Stir, cover and cook in low heat. Stir 2 or 3 times.<br><br>When beef is almost tender, add remaining ingredients. Remove from heat when potatoes are tender.<br><br>Serve with white rice.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>serve with white rice<br>\n',4,0,0,1,0,31,7,8,6,6,9,60,'../files/recipes/beef and potatoes.JPG','2014-04-26 11:28:30',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(364,'Lemon Rice','<div>The lemon rice is a simple recipe, with an excellent taste and is very easy to prepare, itâ€™s good to eat in the summer months, when the heat takes away your appetite.</div><div><br></div><div>In its preparation mode, the recipe includes two important ingredients, garlic and parsley; they give a pleasant flavor and aroma to recipe. The use of garlic is important in the recipe because it helps in the digestion process, influencing therefore the health of diners. If you prepare the Lemon Rice with integral or parboiled rice, you wonâ€™t gain weight easily.</div><div><br></div><div>How to make Lemon Rice is not hard because you can use the rice cooker, and have a minimal demand of your time. There might be a doubt, by prejudice diners, that the garlic bad breath when its consumed; to eliminate the bad odor, you can eliminate it by not eating the green tail, or the heart of garlic clove; others persons recommend drinking water with half a teaspoon of clay; but the most simple of all, itâ€™s included in this recipe, &nbsp;mix parsley with garlic and sure you &nbsp;will not feel the effect of garlic on the breath.</div>\n','<div>Cook the rice in a rice cooker with water and salt until it is slightly al dente.</div><div>Meanwhile, crush the garlic to reduce it to a pure, add parsley, lemon juice and cold oil.</div><div><br></div><div>When the rice is al dente, add this mixture, and cook the rice.</div><div>When the rice is done wait 15 minutes, uncover and stir from the bottom.</div><div><br></div><div>Serve hot.</div>\n',6,0,0,3,0,48,13,7,6,7,9,15,'../files/recipes/lemon rice.JPG','2014-05-21 06:00:28',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-03-26 12:00:02'),(365,'Brigadeiros (Chocolate Fudge Truffles)','	\n		<div>The Brigadeiro is a Brazilian chocolate bonbon created in 40â€™s of the XX century. The story tells, that Brigadier Eduardo Gomez; ran for presidency of the country between 1946 and 1950 with the slogan ... \"vote for the Brigadier, who is handsome and singleâ€, that, made him very popular among women, who voted for the first time in Brazil, during these elections.</div><div><br></div><div>The Brazilian Brigadeiros was created for a group of ladies who supported his campaign; and itâ€™s was baptized in Brigadier honor, I donâ€™t know if it was because of his love for the chocolate and nuts or for the political openness of the women right to vote.</div><div><br></div><div>Coincidentally in these years was introduced in Brazil, quintessential producer of cocoa, condensed milk, and the mixture of these ingredients, led the creation of this simple, but delicious dessert; which even was created only in the last century, has the traditionalism the country of origin.</div><div><br></div><div>To prepare the Brigadeiro, is necessary to be extremely careful, because the cooker has to find the smooth, sticky texture, so that itâ€™s solid outside and inside the chocolate melts in your mouth. In its preparation you can add egg yolks as a thickener, and another flavors, but the original recipe does not take them. Itâ€™s usually rolled into balls and covered in granulated chocolate or coconut, but it can also be consumed unrolled as a topping or filling for cakes and another pastries.</div><div><br></div><div>The brigadeiros, delight of children and adults, is a must presence birthdays and weddings, and prepared in small balls covered in granulated chocolate, can be served as an accompaniment of tea or coffee.</div>\n	\n	','	\n		Pour the condensed milk into your heaviest pot. Stir in the cocoa powder and the salt. <br>Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat. Keep the mixture barely at a boil to prevent burning and sticking.<div><br>Cook for 10-15 minutes, stirring, until mixture becomes very thick and shiny and starts to pull away from the bottom and sides of the pan.&nbsp;Remove from heat and stir in the butter.&nbsp;Chill in the refrigerator for 20 to 30 minutes. With buttered hands, roll the mixture into 1 inch balls.<br>\n	\n	</div>\n	\n	',10,0,0,1,0,43,13,9,6,13,8,30,'../files/recipes/brigadeiros2.JPG','2014-05-10 09:37:08','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-04-02 12:00:02'),(366,'Pineapple Flan','<br>\n','In a mold, metal bowl or pot, place 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tablespoons water then mix it well. Cook this in medium heat on your stove until the sugar turns amber and caramelize to a soft stage. Swirl the caramel around the mold totally covering the interior. Set aside.&nbsp; <br><br>In a blender mix together pineapple, milk, gelatine and 2 cups hot boiled&nbsp; water until combine.<br><br>Pour into mold and refrigerate 2 hours. <br><br>To serve, run small knife around edge of pan. Invert serving plate over pan. Shake gently to release. <br><br>Enjoy this one is a lot easy.<br>\n',8,0,0,2,0,128,7,9,8,13,7,10,'../files/recipes/pinaple flan.JPG','2014-06-05 09:18:59',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(367,'Fried Sweet potatoes or Cuban Boniato.','<br>\n','Peel and wash sweet potatoes or boniato and cut into chunks. Deep fry in oil at medium low heat, until crisp and golden.<br><br>Remove and drain on paper towels. Serve hot.<br><br>\n',4,0,0,2,0,873,7,7,6,17,9,20,'../files/recipes/fried sweet potato.JPG','2014-06-08 20:17:14',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(368,'Stuffed Steak','<br>\n','Marinate steak&nbsp; with salt, garlic, black pepper and lemon for at least&nbsp; an hour.<br><br>Cut onion and green pepper in 1 inch pieces. In a steak place one slice of ham, onion and green pepper, fold over the filling, close off with wooden tooth stick.<br><br>Saute the steaks in casserole, add dry wine, marinate and water cook them slowly, until tender and have sauce.<br><br>Serve with the sauce over white rice.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,13,7,8,6,6,8,100,'../files/recipes/filled steack.JPG','2014-05-14 17:01:07',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(369,'Potato and Cheese Soup','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Peel and wash potatoes and onion and cook with water and salt until tender. Mix the mixture smooth in a blender or mash it through a sieve.<br><br>Return soup to pan, add milk and pepper and bring to boil, stirring constantly. Add cheese and stir till cheese melts.<br><br>Serve immediately. Garnish if desired.<br>\n	\n	',10,0,0,0,0,9,13,8,6,19,9,45,'../files/recipes/potato and cheese soup.JPG','2014-04-19 04:23:11','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(370,'Mummy Hot Dog','	\n		The Halloween party is magical, it is a day of celebration, is a special day for the young and old, and even that in these times has lost the significance that originated it, it is still held as a tradition within the culture of the American, English and Irish people.<br><br>The Halloween party begins in the kitchen, is a singular moment in it for the preparation of dishes gives way sophisticated and simple snacks are leaving the imagination of chefs and cooks.<br><br>Mummy hot dogs, the recipe that we present today, already famous in the American kitchen is a very simple dish to prepare to adorn our table according to the festival and also is an energizing food, you can give to children before eating candy.<br><br>Mummy hot dog is a classic recipe for the holidays, it is advisable to prepare with pork sausage and beef for greater color contrast or low fat sausages to make them healthier, always accompanied by cheese which will help improve the coating of sausage confectioner upon the mummy.<br><br>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 375oF.<br>Unroll dough and separate into 4 rectangles. Cut each rectangle lengthwise into 10 strips.<br><br>Place a rectangle of cheese on each hot dog, and roll four strips of dough around to resemble bandages, stretching a bit to cover the entire hot dog. A half inch of one end of each hot dog, separate the strips a little, leaving room for the face. In a baking dish, ungreased, place them with the cheese side down. Spray them with a little cooking spray.<br><br>Bake 15 minutes or until dough is lightly browned. Make eyes with mustard.<br>You can serve them plain or with tomato sauce<br><br>\n	\n	',5,0,0,0,0,21,16,9,9,6,4,30,'../files/recipes/mummies hot dog.JPG','2014-05-18 02:46:27','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-04-09 12:00:03'),(371,'Ghosts in the Cementery','Letâ€™s celebrate Halloween, a magic party full of joy and imagination. Although it is Halloween and the stories of horror rule, everyone will disguise themselves and go in the search of candy or just to make a joke.<br><br>The date of Halloween has a broad cultural base from the time when the Celts celebrated the harvest, and gathered and prepared for the harsh winter that was coming.<br><br>Today, is more than just a party, is a magical time in the kitchen where you will test the creativity of chefs and assistants, is the moment in which the imagination begins to roll in the kitchen to recreate the most exciting designs.<br><br>Graves in the cemetery belongs to such creation. In this sweet made of cookies and chocolate, join the originality and flavor to delight the palate of young and old. It\'s a recipe made from simple ingredients that takes very little cooking time, and that allows you to decorate your table and entertain guests.<br><br><br>\n','Crush chocolate cookies with a rolling pin or food processor. <br><br>Pour milk into a large bowl, add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk for 2 minutes or until well blended. Let it stand for 5 minutes. Gently stir in 3 cups of cool whip and half of crushed cookies.<br><br>Pour in a dish of 13 x 9 inches, sprinkle with remaining crushed cookies. Refrigerate for an hour,<br><br>To decorate can be made with cookies and frosting for tombstones; immersing stand slightly in the dessert, or you can also introduce a wooden stick, can be with marshmallow ghosts and pumpkins, candy corn, etc..<br><br>Refrigerate until ready to serve.<br><br>\n',10,0,0,2,0,39,16,9,8,13,4,120,'../files/recipes/ghosts in the cemetery.JPG','2014-05-21 19:00:27',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-04-16 12:00:01'),(372,'Green Beans Almandine','	\n		<br>\n	\n	','	\n		Cut green beans and cook, drain. Meanwhile, cook slivered almonds in butter over low heat, stirring occasionally, till golden. Remove from heat; add lemon juice.<br><br>Pour over beans,<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,17,13,7,6,17,3,20,'../files/recipes/grean beans almondine.JPG','2014-05-28 18:05:37','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(373,'Marinated Yucca','<br>\n','In a pan boil&nbsp; 3 cups water with salt, when it is hot add yucca and cook until tender, about 1 hour,(in a pressure cooker reduce water at 2 cups and cook for 20 minutes). Meanwhile, cut the bacon in little pieces and saute in a skillet with 2 tablespoon oil until crispy, take bacon out of the skillet. In the same oil saute crushed garlic and onion slices.<br><br>When the yucca is done, drain and put it in a serving plate. Put over it lemon juice and the marinade. Sprinkle with crispy bacon.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,95,7,7,3,17,9,30,'../files/recipes/yuca with dressing.JPG','2014-05-30 03:12:18',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(375,'Chicken Onion Pimiento','<br>\n','Mix crushed garlic, chopped 1/2&nbsp; onion,lemon juice and salt, add chicken and marinate for at least an hour.<br><br>In a big skillet, at medium heat, saute the chicken with oil, until it turns brown on all sides. Add marinade, wine, green pepper, onion slices and water, cook until tender,<br><br><div>Put chicken in a serving plate, raise the heat to high and boil marinade for minute, and pour it over chicken, garnish with pimientos.<br><br><br>\n</div>\n',4,0,0,0,0,8,7,8,6,16,9,90,'../files/recipes/pollo.JPG','2014-06-04 14:32:25',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(376,'Regular Salad','<br>\n','Peel the cucumber, carrots and avocado, cut the bad parts, and wash all vegetables.<br>Remove seeds while holding a halved cucumber, scrape down the middle of cucumber to scoops out seeds, and cut. Cut tomatoes,radish and carrots in slices, lettuce and avocado in chunks.<br><br>In a salad plate, place lettuce, make a ring with tomatoes over lettuce, mix the remaining ingredients and pour inside the ring.<br><br>For the dressing mix olive oil, cider vinegar and crushed garlic, or use other dressing you like.<br>\n',6,0,0,0,0,13,7,7,8,10,9,15,'../files/recipes/regular salad.JPG','2014-01-13 03:18:51',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(384,'Stuffed Chicken','<br>\n','Sprinkle inside chicken&nbsp; garlic and onion powder. Squeeze out sour orange on top of chicken.Refrigerate at least an hour.<br><br>In a skillet with butter saute the onion add ham, raisins and mix well.Spoon the stuffing loosely into neck cavity. Pull skin over stuffing to the back of chicken and secure with a skewer. Tie drumsticks together with chicken string.<br><br>Place chicken breast side up on a rack in a roasting pan, cover with foil to avoid excess browning. Bake at 325oF for 75 minutes approximately.<br>Continue roasting until the thermometer reads 180o.<br><br>Place chicken on a carving board and remove any stuffing and cut in pieces.<br><br>Note: If you want, make a&nbsp; Moros&nbsp; and Cristianos recipe as it appear in this recipe book and fill the chicken with it.<br>\n',4,0,0,0,0,9,7,8,9,16,8,120,'../files/recipes/filled chicken.JPG','2014-04-22 07:33:21',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(378,'Cheese Flan','<br>\n','In a mold, metal bowl or pot, place 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tbsp. water then mix it well.Cook this in medium heat on your stove until the sugar turns amber and caramelizes to a soft stage. Swirl the caramel around the mold totally covering the interior. Set aside.<br><br>In a blender place milk, water, vanilla, eggs and cream cheese, cover and blend for&nbsp; 8 seconds. Pour into prepared pan, cover lightly with foil. Place pan in roasting pan fill roasting pan with warm water to about 1 inch depth.<br><br>Bake at 350oF for 50 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean<br><br>Remove flan from water. Cool on wire rack. Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.<br><br>To serve, run knife around edge of pan. Invert serving plate over pan, turn over, shake gently to release.<br>\n',6,0,0,1,0,38,7,9,9,13,7,60,'../files/recipes/cheese flan.JPG','2014-05-29 23:30:50',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(379,'Tocino del Cielo','	\n		The creation of the dessert Tocino del Cielo is closely related to the Spanish wine industry, because to prepare it, the wine was necessary filtered and clarified by adding beaten egg whites. This process resulted in an extraordinary surplus of egg yolks, and...What to do with them?<br><br>Tells the story that the vintners of Cadiz in the early fourteenth century gave away to convents leftover egg yolks to calm popular hunger, and the nuns were preparing different dishes with them; thus arising this dessert.<br><br>Documented in the history by the nuns of the Convent of the Holy Spirit of Jerez de la Frontera in 1324, the Tocino del Cielo, a recipe&nbsp; made from egg yolk and sugar caramelized has traveled the world becoming one of the most emblematic dessert of Spain.<br><br>\n	\n	','	\n		In a mold, metal bowl or pot, place1/2 cup of sugar and 2 tbsp water then mix it well and cook this in medium heat on your stove until the sugar turns amber and caramelizes to a soft stage.Swirl the caramel around the mold totally covering the interior. Set aside.<br><br>Bring to boil remaining sugar, water and lemon drops, when it starts to boil count 5 minutes, put out the stove and let it cold.<br><br>Wisk yolk and whites eggs until mixed, add vanilla and the cold syrup&nbsp; mix well. Strain the mixture and pour it into the mold.<br><br>Bake at 350oF for 90 minutes.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,136,7,9,9,13,7,90,'../files/recipes/tocino del cielo - slide.JPG','2014-05-29 23:58:08','',1,1,0,1,1,0,'2014-04-23 12:00:02'),(381,'Roast turkey','<br>','Place into a food processor sour orange, garlic, vinegar, salt, onion, black pepper, oregano and ground bay leave, cover and process until blended, set aside.<br><br>A day before Thanksgiving:<br><br>Wash turkey and dry with towel paper. With finger carefully loosen skin from the turkey breast; rub 1/3 cup of the mix reserved inside and outside the turkey pull skin to the back of turkey and macerate over night.<br><br>Thanksgiving Day:<br><br>In the morning Preheat oven at 325oF Rub turkey with 1/3 cup butter and 1/3 cup marinade. Place breast side down on a rack in a roasting pan and cover with aluminum foil. <br><br>Bake for 3 or 4 hour, basting with remaining marinade and butter every half an hour, turn over turkey and bake again, until a thermometer reads 180oF.<br><br>Before the last hour in the oven, put out the foil to lightly brown it. Cover turkey and let stand for 20 minutes before cut in portions.<br><br>For dressing drain the juices of the roasting pan in a colander and pour it in a gravy boat.<br><br>',16,0,0,0,0,8,7,8,9,6,3,300,'','2014-02-23 04:30:38',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(382,'Filled Turkey','<br>\n','In a skillet with oil, chopped onion, crushed garlic, beef, pork and ham, cook in medium heat stirring until no pink. Add cooking wine,chicken broth salt, black pepper.<br><br>Cut in little pieces apple and pecan add stirring to mix, cook for 30 minutes.<br><br>If you desired filled the turkey or place the stuffed in a serving plate.<br>\n',16,0,1,0,0,11,7,8,6,6,3,40,'../files/recipes/filled turkey.JPG','2014-04-22 10:19:20',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(383,'Pumpkin Layer Cheesecake','	\n		<div>The Pumpkin Cheesecake is a great tasting dish, prepared with sugar, cheese, pumpkin and aromatic spices, which combines in itself with two very traditional dishes in the American food, the New York style cheesecake and pumpkin pie, is one of the dishes typical of October festivities, when families gather to celebrate and give thanks to God for their achievements.</div><div><br></div><div>The pumpkin cheesecake is one of the favorite dishes of American families, who also prepare the recipe in its original form, or natural variants made with chocolate, coffee and pecan praline that add a nice flavor to this dessert.</div><div><br></div><div>This recipe also can be prepared in a healthier way, if you minimize the amount of sugar and accentuate the flavor of the species, which would allow a lower calorie intake, if you do not enjoy the sweet taste of pumpkin.</div>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 350oF<br><br><br>with an electric mixer in medium speed beat cream cheese &nbsp;sugar and vanilla until smooth, gradually add eggs to combine well.<br><br>Combine a cup of this mixture with pumpkin puree, nutmeg and cinnamon.<br><br>Spoon the cream cheese mixture into crust and spoon the pumpkin mixture over the other mixture into crust.<br><br>Bake 40 minutes. Refrigerate for 4 hours or overnight.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,1,0,0,13,7,8,9,13,3,60,'../files/recipes/pumpkin cheesecake.JPG','2014-05-08 17:56:29','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-04-30 12:00:02'),(385,'Strawberry Cake','<br>\n','Preheat oven 350oFand coat 2 pans 9 inch with cooking spray. Set aside.<br><br>Prepare cake mix following package directions, and pour into pans. Bake for 30 minutes or until a wooden&nbsp; pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes; remove from pans. Coll completely on wire rack.<br><br>Place a cake layer on platter, spread with 1/2 cup of jam, place the other layer over it.<br><br>To make a frosting beat cream cheese and 1/2 cup of jam and 2 drops red food color at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating until blended. <br><br>Spread the frosting on top and sides of cake and decorate with strawberries.<br>\n',12,0,1,0,0,16,7,9,9,14,8,50,'../files/recipes/strowberry cake - slide.JPG','2014-05-27 00:00:29',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(386,'Pina Colada Cheesecake','<br>\n','In nonstick skillet over medium heat cook coconut, stirring, until lightly browned, 3 or 4 minutes; remove. Coat 8\" springform pan with cooking spray. Combine crumbs with 1/2 cup reserved coconut; stir in butter. Press onto bottom and 1\" up side of pan. <br><br>In microwave safe bowl sprinkle gelatin over 1/4 cup pineapple juice. In another bowl at high speed beat cream cheese at room temperature until smooth. Reduce speed to medium; beat in sugar then sour cream. Reduce speed to low. Add cream of coconut, rum and 1/3 cup pineapple juice; beat until combine. In microwave heat reserved gelatin mixture on high in 5 second intervals until gelatin dissolves. At low speed beat gelatin mixture into cheese mixture until combined.<br><br>Pour batter into pan. Refrigerate until set, 4 hours. To serve run knife around edge of cheesecake to loosen; remove side of pan. Garnish with remaining coconut.<br><br>\n',20,0,0,0,0,39,13,9,8,13,5,30,'../files/recipes/pinaple flan - slide.JPG','2014-05-16 06:17:43',NULL,0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(387,'Christmas Rainbow Cake','<div>Christmas is relative to the birth of Jesus and celebrated with joy by Christian people for over two millennia. Christmas symbolizes hope, harmony and happiness. Many cultures consider Christmas the most important festivity of the whole year; and their people start preparing for the celebration by the end of November. Houses and public places are decorated with lights and bell and filled with cheerful music.</div><div><br></div><div>Christmas is time for family unification; it is time to make new plans, to forgive and be forgiven, to turn around our lives and sharing the happiness of a new beginning with each of the people around us. According to each countryâ€™s traditions, in Christmas delightful dishes and desserts are prepared in order to share with family, neighbors and friends in a huge dinner to celebrate the birth of god.</div><div><br></div><div>As tradition is, we sharing the joy of these special days by inviting you to exquisite, Christmas traditional, flavorful dishes. Merry Christmas and a Happy New Year!</div>','	\n		Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour batter into 2 round pans, 9 x 1 1/2 inches (do not use pans with removable bottoms). Bake at 350oF for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove from pans; cool completely.<br><br>Place cake layers top sides up, back in the 2 clean pans; prick each layer with utility fork at 1/2 inch intervals. Pour 1 cup of the boiling water over raspberry gelatine in bowl; stir until gelatine is dissolved and spoon over 1 layer. Repeat with lime flavor gelatine. Refrigerate 3 - 4hours.<br><br>Dip 1 layer in pan into warm water&nbsp; 10 seconds; invert on plate, gently shaking to loosen. Remove pan; spread layer with 1 cup of the cool whip. Remove remaining layer from pan as above; invert on first layer and frost with remaining topping.<br><br>Refrigerate; garnish&nbsp; if desired.<br>\n	\n	',16,0,0,3,0,68,16,9,9,13,12,300,'../files/recipes/christmas cake.JPG','2014-06-03 18:38:25','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-05-07 12:00:02'),(389,'Diplomatic Flan','	\n	','	\n		<!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\n <w:WordDocument>\n  <w:View>Normal</w:View>\n  <w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\n  <w:TrackMoves></w:TrackMoves>\n  <w:TrackFormatting></w:TrackFormatting>\n  <w:PunctuationKerning></w:PunctuationKerning>\n  <w:ValidateAgainstSchemas></w:ValidateAgainstSchemas>\n  <w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\n  <w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\n  <w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\n  <w:DoNotPromoteQF></w:DoNotPromoteQF>\n  <w:LidThemeOther>EN-US</w:LidThemeOther>\n  <w:LidThemeAsian>X-NONE</w:LidThemeAsian>\n  <w:LidThemeComplexScript>X-NONE</w:LidThemeComplexScript>\n  <w:Compatibility>\n   <w:BreakWrappedTables></w:BreakWrappedTables>\n   <w:SnapToGridInCell></w:SnapToGridInCell>\n   <w:WrapTextWithPunct></w:WrapTextWithPunct>\n   <w:UseAsianBreakRules></w:UseAsianBreakRules>\n   <w:DontGrowAutofit></w:DontGrowAutofit>\n   <w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark></w:SplitPgBreakAndParaMark>\n   <w:DontVertAlignCellWithSp></w:DontVertAlignCellWithSp>\n   <w:DontBreakConstrainedForcedTables></w:DontBreakConstrainedForcedTables>\n   <w:DontVertAlignInTxbx></w:DontVertAlignInTxbx>\n   <w:Word11KerningPairs></w:Word11KerningPairs>\n   <w:CachedColBalance></w:CachedColBalance>\n  </w:Compatibility>\n  <m:mathPr>\n   <m:mathFont m:val=\"Cambria Math\"></m:mathFont>\n   <m:brkBin m:val=\"before\"></m:brkBin>\n   <m:brkBinSub m:val=\"--\"></m:brkBinSub>\n   <m:smallFrac m:val=\"off\"></m:smallFrac>\n   <m:dispDef></m:dis