ong meringue. Set aside.<br><br>Preheat oven to 350oF and coat 2 round 8\" or 9\" pan with cooking spray.<br><br>In another bowl mix flour, 1 cup of sugar, baking power and salt, add vanilla, milk oil and egg yolks, mix in medium speed for 3 minutes and transfer the mix to the meringues bowl and join very well.<br><br>Pour into pans and bake for 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted into centers comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes, remove from pan and cool completely on wire rack.<br><br>Cut ears and bow tie from one cake.<br><br>Arrange whole cake layer on large serving plate, with two ears positioned&nbsp; at top and bow tie placed under the face. Brush off any excess crumbs; set aside.<br><br>Frost entire cake.&nbsp; Sprinkle with coconut. Arrange thin licorice strips for whiskers and smile, gumdrops for eyes and nose and jelly beans for bow tie decorations.<br>\n	\n	',12,0,0,0,0,5,13,9,9,13,5,70,'../files/recipes/easter cake.JPG','2014-02-06 05:36:02','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(421,'Pie Cupcake','	\n	','In medium bowl with electric mixer prepare cupcakes mix as directed on package and pour into 24 cupcakes foil liners pan.<br><br>Tint frosting&nbsp; with 3 or 4 drops of food coloring and cocoa powder to make light brown for pie crust. Spread some of frosting on top of each cupcake, leaving 1/4\" of cupcake edge exposed.<br><br>For filling, arrange about 25 like colored candies close together on top of cupcake, repeat with remaining cupcakes and&nbsp; like colored candies.<br><br>Spoon remaining light brown frosting into zip top plastic bag, press out excess air and seal. Snip small (1/8\") corner from bag. For lattice crust, pipe 4 or 5 lines across top of cupcakes, about 1/2\" apart. Pipe 4 or 5 more lines, on the diagonal. Pipe beaded edge around top of cupcake. Repeat with remaining cupcakes and frosting.<br><br>For perfectly portioned cupcakes I use an ice cream scoop to divide the batter among the liners.<br>	\n	',24,0,0,0,0,15,13,9,9,12,6,60,'{$picture}','2014-05-07 20:45:10','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(422,'Spaghetti in Hot Dog','	\n	','	\n		Cut each hot dog into 3 pieces, carefully as it can break, insert about 5 spaghetti in a pieces, cook the pasta according to the package directions and drain.<br><br>Meanwhile , make a sauce in the pan with butter, chopped onion and garlic, ground oregano and black pepper, parsley and basil, stirring for 1 minute, add the tomatoes puree and stir until desired consistency.<br><br>Mix gently spaghetti and sauce before serving.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,80,7,9,6,4,4,25,'../files/recipes/Spaghetti in Hot Dog.JPG','2014-06-06 09:23:33','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(423,'Tunnel Cake','	\n	','	\n		In medium bowl, with an electric mixer prepare the cake mix as directed on package.<br><br>When cool place the cake on a platter. Cut a horizontal slice 3/4 inch of the cake top and set aside.<br><br>With a small knife cut a pipe 1 inch deep in the center of cake, being careful not to cross it. Remove sides and save the clipping to eat as a snack.<br><br>Mix the boiling water with the gelatin in a&nbsp; bowl for 2 minutes or until dissolved. <br>add&nbsp; water 1/2 cup of ice up to 3/4 cup and mix until the gelatin is dissolved completely.Remove 1/2 cup gelatin and place it in a separate medium bowl. Add whipped cream, mix it with a wire whisk until well blended. Refrigerate 10-15 minutes or until thick enough to spread.<br><br>Refrigerate, meanwhile, the other part of the gelatin from 5 -10 minutes or until thickened. Add 3/4 cup of the fruit and mix, put with a spoon in the hollow of the cake, put back the top of the cake, and cover it with the mixture of gelatin and reserved whipped cream.<br><br>Decorate the top with the remaining fruit.<br>\n	\n	',12,0,0,0,0,9,13,9,9,13,8,50,'../files/recipes/tunnel cake.JPG','2014-05-28 17:25:49','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(393,'Corn Cake','	\n	','Preheat oven to 350oF&nbsp; and coat 9\" pan with cooking spray. Set aside.<br><br>In a medium bowl mix all ingredients with an electric mixer and pour into pan.<br><br>Bake for 25 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire racks 10 minutes, remove from pan. Cool completely on wire rack.<br>	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,9,7,9,9,14,9,40,'../files/recipes/corn panetela.JPG','2014-04-18 11:18:22','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(394,'BuÃ±uelos de Yuca','	\n	','	\n		Peel yucca and cook it in water with salt until tender. Put out the string and mashed yucca. Add whisked egg, cinnamon or aniseed. Knead with flour until it doesn\'t stick to your fingers and you can make a number 8 shape.<br><br>Fry in hot oil until golden.&nbsp;Serve with syrup.<br>\n	\n	',12,0,0,3,0,283,7,7,8,13,9,60,'../files/recipes/bunnuelos.JPG','2014-06-05 01:03:16','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(424,'Mexican Rice','	\n	','	\n		Wash the rice. In a rice cooker with oil fry the onion and ham for 2 minutes, add tomato sauce stir, add rice, water, salt and cook .<br><br>When the rice is done wait 15 minutes, uncover add drained peas and carrot and stir from the bottom.<br><br>Serve hot.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,2,0,29,8,8,6,7,6,20,'../files/recipes/mexican rice.JPG','2014-06-08 19:36:56','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(425,'Broccoli saute','	\n	','In large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium high heat. Add onion and garlic; cook stirring occasionally, until softened, about 5 minutes.<br><br>Add 1/2 cup water, mustard, paprika and salt; stir until blended. Add broccoli; reduce heat to medium. Cover skillet, cook, stirring occasionally, until broccoli in just tender. <br><br>If necessary, remove lid during last minutes of cooking to allow any liquid to evaporate.<br><br><br>	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,13,16,7,6,17,10,25,'{$picture}','2014-04-25 18:21:02','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(426,'Potatoe Skins','	\n	','Scrub potatoes; pierce with a fork. Place on paper towels. Microwave on High 16 minutes.<br><br>In large skillet over medium heat cook bacon until crisp, about 5 minutes.Position rack 6 inches from oven top and heat broiler.Line a baking sheet with nonstick foil.Slice potatoes in half lengthwise; scoop out flesh, leaving about 1/4 inch edge, reserving flesh for another use.&nbsp; Place skins, cut side down, on sheet; coat with nonstick cooking spray. Broil 4 minutes.<br><br>Remove potato skins from oven. Flip over (cut side up). Season with salt and pepper. Sprinkle each with 2 tablespoons of the cheese and 1 slice bacon, crumbled. Top bacon with an additional 2 tablespoons cheese per skin.<br><br>Return to broiler; broil 3 minutes, until cheese melts. Top with scallions and serve with sour cream.<br>	\n	',5,0,0,0,0,8,16,8,9,17,9,38,'{$picture}','2014-03-02 15:35:01','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(427,'Refreshing Chicken Salad','	\n	','	\n		Place boneless, skinless chicken in large saucepan and cover with water. Cover pan and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer until chicken is done, about 15 minutes.Remove chicken from water, place on a cutting board and let cool.<br><br>Cut cooled chicken into bite size pieces. Place in large bowl and sprinkle with seasoning salt.Add grapes cut in half, pineapple tidbits drained,celery thinly sliced and mayonnaise. Stir gently to combine. Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.<br><br>To serve, stir well and sprinkle walnuts over the top.<br>\n	\n	',8,0,0,0,0,9,13,8,6,10,6,27,'[[]] ERROR: INFINITE LOOP DETECTED ON RECURSIVE REPLACEMENT $picture','2014-01-01 06:41:11','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(428,'Mochaccino Cake','	\n	','Preheat oven to 350oF. Coat 2&nbsp; (9\" cake pans) with cooking spray.<br><br>Stir 1 tbs. coffee granules into 1/4 cup hot water until dissolved; stir in syrup. Reserve.<br><br>On low speed, beat cake mix, 1 cup water, eggs, oil and 4 tbs. coffee granules until just blended, 30 seconds. On medium beat 2 minutes. Divide between pans. Bake 25 or 30 minutes until pick inserted into centers comes out clean. Using fork, poke holes into cake layers while still hot. Brush tops with reserved syrup mixture; cool completely in pans.<br><br>Blend remaining coffee granules and hot water; cool. On medium speed, beat butter until fluffy, 2 minutes. Add chocolate; beat until smooth. On low, gradually beat in confectioners sugar, then reserved coffee mixture until blended. On medium high, beat until fluffy, 2 minutes. Place one cake layer on serving plate. Spread with 1 cup frosting. Top with remaining cake layer. Spread top and side with remaining frosting. Sprinkle with jimmies.<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>	\n	',16,0,0,0,0,19,16,9,9,13,7,120,'{$picture}','2014-05-29 01:27:33','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(429,'Steak Pizzaiola','	\n	','	\n		The night before, season steaks with salt, rub with 1 clove garlic and 1 tbs oil. Place in baking dish, cover and refrigerate overnight. Let meat come to room temperature in the morning.<br><br>Heat 3 tbs. oil in wide deep saute pan over medium, high heat, add thickly sliced mushrooms and pinch of salt; cook stirring until mushrooms are seared and begin to give up their juices. Add thinly sliced lengthwise onion, red and yellow pepper cut into 1/2\" thick slices and pinch of salt. Cook stirring until peppers are lightly caramelized, about 4 or 5 minutes. Reduce heat; stir in another clove garlic. Cook and stir until peppers are tender.<br><br>Add wine, turn heat to high and bring to boil. Boil and reduce wine until syrup, 2 minutes. Add tomatoes with juice and crushed by hand , cook stirring until thick and flavorful, about 5 minutes. Remove from heat; stir in remaining garlic, chopped oregano and parsley leaves. Season with salt and pepper. Cover to keep warm.<br><br>Heat wide deep, heavy saute pan over high heat. Add 1 tbs. oil and butter. When butter melts and foams, add steaks without crowding, in batches if necessary; cook until browned on one side, turn over, brown on other side. Cook until desired doneness.<br><br>Serve steaks with sauce.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,6,10,8,6,6,7,70,'../files/recipes/steak pizzaiola.JPG','2014-04-30 15:55:07','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(430,'Fettuccine Alfredo','	\n	','	\n		Chop onion, red pepper, garlic and beacon and set aside. Cook pasta following package directions.<br><br>In a big skillet saute beacon about 2 minutes, add onion, pepper and garlic, saute until medium brown. Add a half of chicken bouillon cube crush with your hand and sprinkle over it, ground cumin and butter, cook until begin boil add shrimp and when it don\'t boil add cornstarch mixed with milk. Cook until desired thick.<br><br>Drain the pasta&nbsp; and mix it with the sauce.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,12,10,8,6,4,9,25,'../files/recipes/Fettuccine Alfredo.JPG','2014-04-08 11:04:50','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(431,'Delicious Pumpkin','	\n	','	\n		Peel, put out seeds and cut the pumpkin in 2 inch slices, wash and cook pumpkin in water with salt until tender and drain.<br><br>Meanwhile, chop onion and garlic. In a skillet with oil saute onion and garlic until translucent.<br><br>Put the pumpkin in a salad plate and pour over the dressing.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,8,7,7,6,17,3,20,'../files/recipes/pumpking.JPG','2014-04-25 11:46:25','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(432,'Vegetables Lazagna','	\n	','	\n		Cook pasta following package directions. Drain, rinse with cool water. <br><br>Meanwhile, prepare sauce. In a skillet whit oil saute onion and garlic over low heat about 3 minutes, add tomatoes, broken up with fork; tomato paste oregano, basil and sugar. Stir well; add vegetables to sauce. Cook over low heat until thick.<br><br>Lightly grease 13 x 9 inch baking dish, ladle approximately 3/4 cup sauce into pan.&nbsp; Top with noodles. Dot with 1/2 the ricotta and 1/2&nbsp; the mozzarella. Add layer of sauce and noodles and remaining ricotta and mozzarella. Top with more sauce; add remaining noodles. Top with remaining sauce; sprinkle with parmesan cheese.<br><br>Baked&nbsp; at 350oF&nbsp; for 30 minutes<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,9,10,7,9,4,9,50,'../files/recipes/lazanna ede vegetales.JPG','2014-05-12 23:06:14','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(433,'Chow Mein','	\n	','	\n		Heat oil in a wok or pan and stir fry the sliced celery and&nbsp; cut in eighth onion over high heat 2 or 3 minutes, separating the onion layers. Add soy sauce, sugar and broth; bring to a boil. Add the bean sprouts and shredded cooked chicken and stir to combine.<br><br>Dissolve cornstarch in water and add gradually to sauce. Simmer gently until it thickens.<br><br>Serve over chow mein noodles.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,6,11,8,6,14,9,20,'../files/recipes/chow mein.JPG','2014-02-01 19:28:41','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(436,'Fajitas','	\n	','	\n		Cut chicken into strips 3\" long by 2\" wide, also the green peppers into strips, onion in thin slices and crush the garlic, set aside.<br><br>In a large skillet, at medium temperature cook chicken about 5 minutes stirring, add onion, garlic and chopped peppers above. Stir constantly until the chicken is cooked.<br><br>Serve with tortillas.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,6,8,8,6,16,6,30,'../files/recipes/chicken fajita.JPG','2014-06-08 19:36:36','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(435,'Blue Cake','	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven at 350oF. Coat 2 pans 9\" each with cooking spray.<br><br>In medium bowl, with electric mixer prepare cake mix as directed on package and pour into pans.<br><br>Bake for 30 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes, remove from pan, cool completely on wire rack.<br><br>Spread blueberry jam between layers. Mix cool whip and blueberry jam&nbsp; and coat&nbsp;&nbsp; top and side of cool cake.<br><br>Garnish with blueberry. <br>\n	\n	',12,0,0,0,0,8,7,9,9,13,9,50,'../files/recipes/blue cake.JPG','2014-04-30 14:45:15','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(438,'Refried Beans','	\n	','	\n		Cook the beans in 3 cups water until tender, cut the onion and green pepper into small pieces and crush garlic. <br><br>In a casserole with 2 tbs. oil saute 1/2 cup of onion, green pepper and garlic until soft, add oregano, black pepper, bay leaf and cumin, saute for 1 minute and add the beans and leave stirring and mashing, adding slowly the cheese until it is pasty.<br><br>Serve hot with additional onion and cheese for people who like with more cheese and onion.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,6,8,9,9,14,6,50,'../files/recipes/frijoles refritos.JPG','2014-04-04 07:03:40','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(439,'Creamy Macaroni','	\n	','	\n		Prepare elbow macaroni according to package directions. Drain.<br><br>Meanwhile, in big skillet over medium heat, heat soup milk, mustard and pepper to boiling. Add vegetables; return to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover; simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring accasionally.<br><br>Stir in ham, cheese and macaroni. Heat through. Sprinkle with additional chesse if desired.<br><br>You can use 16 oz. package frozen broccoli, cauliflower and red pepper for fresh vegetables.<br>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,10,16,8,6,4,9,30,'../files/recipes/creamy macaroni.JPG','2014-04-20 21:02:29','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(440,'Chicken Garden','	\n	','	\n		Cut green pepper in thin strips, carrot and zucchini in 3 inch julienne strips.<br><br>An hour before sprinkle with rosemary, salt and pepper to taste. In skillet brown chicken in oil. Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil. Cover and cook 3 minutes over medium heat. Uncover and cook over medium high heat&nbsp; until thickened.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,9,16,8,6,16,5,30,'../files/recipes/chicken garden saute.JPG','2014-03-16 13:09:00','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(441,'Patriotic Cake','	\n		<p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\" id=\"docs-internal-guid-1691c851-e16f-0414-bf7f-6827692b455c\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\">Memorial\n Day is a United States federal holiday, which occurs every once a year \non the final Monday of May. Memorial Day originated in order to remember\n the Union and the Confederate soldiers who died in on the civil war. In\n present day, Memorial Day is used to remember all of the men and women \nwho have died while they were serving for the United States Armed \nForces.</span></p><br><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\"></span><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\"></span><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:#ffffff;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\">By\n the early 20th century, Memorial Day was an occasion for more general \nexpressions of memory, as people visited the graves of their deceased \nrelatives in church cemeteries, whether they had served in the military \nor not. It also became a long weekend increasingly devoted to shopping, \nfamily gatherings, fireworks, trips to the beach, and national media \nevents.</span></p><br><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\"></span><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\"></span><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:#fffffd;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\">While\n Waterloo N.Y. was officially declared the birthplace of Memorial Day by\n President Lyndon Johnson on May 1966, it is still difficult to define \nthe origins of the day. It is more likely that it had many separate \nstarts; many towns planned or spontaneous gathering of people to honor \nthe war dead in the 1860\'s tapped into the general human need to honor \nour dead, each contributed honorably to the growing movement that \nculminated in Gen Logan giving his official proclamation in 1868.</span></p><br><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\"></span><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"line-height:1.15;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:#fffffd;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\">Memorial\n Day was officially proclaimed on 5 May, 1868 by General John Logan, \nnational commander of the Grand Army of the Republic and was first \nobserved on 30 May 1868. When flowers were placed on the Union and \nConfederate soldiersâ€™ graves at Arlington National Cemetery. The very \nfirst state to officially recognize this holiday was New York in the \nyear 1873, and by the 1890s, it was recognized by all of the northern \nstates. The South, however, did not take this celebration, and honored \ntheir dead on separate days until after World War I.</span><span style=\"font-size:16px;font-family:Arial;color:#000000;background-color:transparent;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;font-variant:normal;text-decoration:none;vertical-align:baseline;\"></span></p>\n	\n	','	\n		Coat two 9\" pan with cooking spray, set aside.<br><br>Preheat oven&nbsp; to 350oF.<br><br>In medium bowl, with an electric mixer prepare cake mix as directed on package and pour into coated pans, bake until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire racks 10 minutes, remove from pan, cool completely on wire rack.<br><br>Meanwhile beat cream cheese and butter at medium speed with an electric mixer until creamy. Gradually add sugar and salt, beating until blended. Stir in vanilla.<br><br>Spread cream frosting between layers and&nbsp; on top&nbsp; and sides of cake.<br><br>Garnish with decorative accessories according to occasion.<br>\n	\n	',16,0,0,0,0,24,16,9,9,13,13,120,'../files/recipes/patriotic cake.jpg','2014-05-21 01:03:17','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-05-14 12:00:02'),(442,'Pumpkin Custards','	\n	','	\n		Mix sugar, cinnamon, and salt in small bowl. Beat egg in large bowl. Stir in pumpkin and sugar-spice mixture. gradually stir in evaporated milk. Put into eight custards cup and place it on baking sheet.<br>Bake for 50 minutes. Cool on wire rack for two hours. Serve immediately or refrigerate<br>\n	\n	',8,0,0,0,0,12,16,7,9,13,3,55,'[[]] ERROR: INFINITE LOOP DETECTED ON RECURSIVE REPLACEMENT $picture','2014-05-27 06:41:02','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(443,'Cellphone Cake','	\n		<div><div>Father\'s Day is a celebration honoring fathers and celebrating fatherhood, paternal bonds, and the influence of fathers in society. Many countries celebrate this holiday on the third Sunday of June, however, it is also celebrated widely on other dates. Father\'s Day was originally created to complement Motherâ€™s Day, a celebration that honors mothers and motherhood.</div><div><br></div><div>In recent years, retailers have adapted to the holiday by promoting greeting cards and gifts that are traditionally masculine such as electronics and tools. Schools and other children\'s programs commonly have activities to make Father\'s Day gifts.</div><div><br></div><div>Father\'s Day is accompanied by a smaller total number of phone calls, greeting cards and gifts than Mother\'s Day. It is speculated that this is due to the greater number of households with a mother than households with a father, to the greater role of mothers in housework, and to historical advantage â€“ Mother\'s Day began in 1870 and became official in 1914 while Father\'s Day became official in 1972.</div></div>\n	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 350oF. Butter and flour 13 x 9 inch baking pan.<br><br>In microwave melt chocolate chips to make 1 1/3 cups, and cool.<br><br>Prepare cake mix according to package directions with 1 cup water, eggs and sour cream. Pour into pan and bake 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan; cool completely on rack. <br><br>On medium-high speed, beat butter until smooth. Beat in chocolate; gradually beat in sugar until fluffy. Frost and decorate cake following steps.<br><br>1. Using toothpicks, mark a 6\" x 4 1/2\" rectangle in top of cake for cellphone screen.Spread remainder of cake with chocolate frosting.<br><br>2. Pipe white decorating icing into rectangle. Using small spatula, smoothly spread icing to fill in area. Let stand until&nbsp; dry, about&nbsp; 5 minutes.<br><br>Using marker, write numbers and letters on M&amp;M; place on cake. Separate 2 Pull-n-Peel bundles into double strands. Using black icing, write message on cellphone screen. Cut 2 1?2\" long piece from remaining Pull-n-Peel. Attach to top edge of cake for antenna.<br>\n	\n	',12,0,0,8,0,75,16,9,9,13,15,130,'../files/recipes/Dropbox.jpg','2014-05-21 20:06:13','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-05-21 12:00:03'),(444,'Surprise Cupcake','	\n		Fourth of July is a federal holiday celebrating the adoption of the Declaration of Independence, on July 4, 1776, when the United States of America reached its freedom from the Kingdom of Great Britain.<br><br>The legal separation of the Thirteen Colonies from Great Britain occurred on July 2, 1776, during the American Resolution. When the Second Continental Congress voted to approve a resolution of independence that had been proposed in June by Richard Henry Lee of Virginia.<br><br>From 1776 until today, July 4th has been celebrated as the birth of American\'s independence, with typical festivities ranging from fireworks, parades and concerts to more casual gatherings with families and friends, and barbecues.<br><br>\n	\n	','	\n		Cupcakes<br><br>Preheat oven to 350oF. Line 18 muffin cups with cupcake liners. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Divide batter evenly among cupcake liners. Place desired \"surprise\" such as brownie, donuts, cookie or Butterfingers in center of top each cupcake. Slightly press into batter. Bake 20-25 minutes. Cool in pans 10 minutes. Remove from pans; cool on racks.<br><br>Frosting<br><br>On medium speed, beat butter until light and fluffy, about 2 minutes. Beat in Fluff until blended, about 1 minute. On low, beat in confectioners\' sugar and vanilla. Beat on medium-high until fluffy. Frost cupcakes, decorate as desired<br>\n	\n	',18,0,0,2,0,35,16,7,9,13,13,45,'../files/recipes/surprise cupcakes.JPG','2014-05-28 12:00:01','',0,0,0,0,0,0,'2014-05-28 12:00:01'),(445,'Frozen Strawberry Green Tea','	\n	','In blender, mix crushed ice,cold-brewed green tea, frozen strawberries and honey until smooth. If desired add additional honey to taste.<br>Garnish with sliced strawberry, lemon sliced and mint sprig<br>	\n	',2,0,0,0,0,13,16,7,8,14,9,10,'{$picture}','2014-04-30 14:21:44','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(446,'Lemon Bundt Cake','	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 325oF. Grease and flour a 10 inch bundt pan.<br><br>In a large bowl, combine cake mix and pudding mix, then stir in the oil. Beat in the eggs, one at a time, then stir in the lemon lime soda.<br><br>Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake for 35 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br><br>Allow to cool 15 minutes in pan before inverting onto cooling rack to cool complete<br><br>Sprinkle powder sugar before serving.<br>\n	\n	',16,0,0,0,0,3,16,9,9,13,6,50,'','2014-04-30 22:38:16','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(447,'Mango Tea Beverage','	\n	','	\n		In blender, mix crushed ice, green or white tea, mango and lemon juice until smooth. If desired garnish with mango and lime slices\n	\n	',2,0,0,0,0,15,16,7,8,11,9,15,'','2014-05-22 01:43:07','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(448,'Cheese Rice','	\n	','Cut the cheese into not very wide rectangular strips, cut green chilies like cheese and make sandwiches with 2 slices of cheese and a chili. Set aside.<br><br>Turn oven to 350oF and grease a 13\" x 9\" mold with cooking spray.<br><br>In a saucepan saute the onion, garlic and chopped jalapeno, add the washed rice, salt and chicken broth, boil over medium heat until dry, stirring constantly.<br><br>Pour in a greased mold the half of the rice, put it cheese sandwiches on top and cover with the remaining rice. Carefully pour the whipping cream over rice.<br><br>Bake 45 minutes, let stand 10 minutes and enjoy our delicious rice.<br>	\n	',6,0,0,2,0,23,13,8,9,7,15,60,'{$picture}','2014-05-21 05:00:42','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(449,'Italian Sausages','	\n	','	\n		In a pan with water and salt cook the sausages until almost all the water consumed. Meanwhile, cut in slices the green pepper and onion, set aside.<br><br>Prick the sausages with a fork several times to loosen the fat. Let them brown in the fat, stirring occasionally. Once golden, take them out and cut into diagonal slices, when removing the sausages saute onion and pepper in the fat, add the sausages and stir saute for 2 minutes to blend the flavors.<br>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,15,10,9,6,6,6,25,'','2014-03-16 13:28:44','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(450,'Raspberry Tart','	\n	','Heat dry skillet over medium heat. Add almonds; cook, stirring until lightly browned and fragrant, 2 or 3 minutes. Remove from skillet; cool. Reserve 1 tbs. almonds; chop remaining. Place spongecake shell on serving plate. Spread 1/2 cup preserves over bottom of shell. In bowl dilute remaining preserves with hot&nbsp; water to make a syrupy consistency. Spread, mixture on outside of the shell. Holding shell on the palm of one hand, press chopped almonds onto the outside of shell with the other hand.<br><br>Using small ice cream scoop fill shell with scoops of sorbet. Freeze cake until just before serving. <br><br>When ready to serve, transfer topping to pastry bag fitted with large star tip, pipe whipped topping in lattice over sorbet. Garnish with reserved almonds.<br><br>	\n	',12,0,0,0,0,15,16,7,8,15,9,25,'{$picture}','2014-05-09 18:45:49','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(470,'Chocolate Peanut butter Parfaits','	\n	','Stir 3 tablespoons milk into peanut butter in medium bowl until smooth. Gently stir in whipped topping.<div><br></div><div>Pour 2 cups milk into medium bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Alternately spoon whipped topping mixture and pudding into 6 parfait glasses.</div><div><br></div><div>Refrigerate until ready to serve. Sprinkle with peanuts.</div>',6,0,0,0,0,12,16,8,8,13,9,10,'{$picture}','2014-04-22 04:16:38','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(451,'Pineapple Fluff','	\n	','Gently fold&nbsp; together drained pineapple, whipped topping&nbsp; and gelatin powder in a medium bowl. <br>Spoon mixture into four small dessert cups and each with an equal amount of raspberries<br>	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,9,16,7,8,13,9,10,'{$picture}','2014-06-04 02:36:24','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(452,'Cabbage Ribbons','	\n	','&nbsp;Cut cabbage into thin strips.<br>In a large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon light margarine&nbsp; over medium heat. Add cabbage and saute until cabbage softens to desired texture (about 3 minutes for very soft consistency, less for firmer). makes&nbsp; about 2 cups cooked cabbage. Sprinkle with black pepper and&nbsp; apple vinegar if desired. Served warm.<br>',4,0,0,0,0,6,16,7,6,17,9,5,'{$picture}','2014-03-02 05:25:45','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(453,'Chicken with Rice','	\n	','Cut chicken into pieces; cover with garlic, onions, salt, black pepper, vinegar and lime juice. Let stand to season. Remove chicken and fry in hot oil until brown. Then, to the fried chicken add the rest of the ingredients and the mixture which first covered the chicken and cook all until tender, add rice, hot water and cook, when the rice is done wait 15 minutes, uncover and stir from bottom.<div><br></div><div>Serve with a can of hot peas.</div>',8,0,0,0,0,11,7,8,6,4,4,60,'{$picture}','2014-05-07 10:59:42','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(454,'Chocolate Cheesecake','	\n	','&nbsp;Position racks in center and lower third of oven. Preheat oven to 500oF. Place roasting pan on lower rack; fill halfway with water. Coat bottom of 9\" x 23/4\" heart shaped or 9\" x 3\" round springform pan with cooking spray. Combine crumbs with melted butter; press onto bottom of pan. At high speed beat cream cheese until fluffy, 4 minutes. At medium speed gradually beat in sugar; beat 3 minutes. Beat in eggs and yolks, one at a time, then vanilla. Beat in flour, then melted chocolate; beat 2 minutes.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>Bake on rack above pan of water 8 minutes or until slightly risen and beginning to brown at edge. Reduce oven temperature to 200oF. Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes &nbsp;or until edge is set and center moves slightly when jiggled. Turn off oven; let cheesecake stand in oven 30 minutes.Run knife around edge of cake to loosen. Cool completely on rack.</div><div><br></div><div>Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight. Remove side from pan. Arrange strawberry slices over cake, overlapping slices slightly. In microwave heat jam on high in 5 second intervals until melted. With pastry brush gently brush jam over berries.</div><div><br></div>',20,0,0,0,0,26,13,9,9,13,11,225,'{$picture}','2014-05-12 19:10:12','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(455,'Tiramisu Layer Cake','	\n	','Preheat oven to 350oF Coat 2 (9\") round cake pans with cooking spray.<div><br></div><div>At low speed beat cake mix, eggs, sour cream and 1 cup water until combined. At medium high speed beat until light, 2 minutes. Divide batter between pans. Bake 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted into centers comes out clean. Cool 5 minutes. Remove from pans; cool on racks.</div><div><br></div><div>Horizontally cut each layer in half. Combine 1/4 cup water and 1 tsp. espresso powder; brush over layers. Stir remaining espresso into Marsala; mix with cheese and 1/4 cup sugar. At medium high speed beat cream, vanilla and remaining sugar until stiff. Fold 1/2 cup whipped cream into cheese mixture.</div><div><br></div><div>Place 1 cake layer on platter; spread with 1/3 of cheese mixture. Repeat with 2 cake layers and cheese mixture. Top with remaining layer.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Transfer 3/4 cup whipped cream to pastry bag fitted with large star tip. Spread cake with remaining whipped cream. Pipe rosettes onto cake. Garnish with cocoa powder and espresso beans, if desired.</div>',16,0,0,0,0,23,16,9,9,13,6,30,'{$picture}','2014-06-05 18:38:12','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(456,'Eggnog Cake','	\n	','<div>&nbsp; Preheat oven to 350oF. Coat 2 (8\") round cake pans with cooking spray. Whisk together flour, baking powder, soda, 1/2 tsp. nutmeg and salt; reserve. In large bowl whisk together brown sugar, egg substitute, sour cream and oil until smooth. Stir in flour mixture, then 3/4 cup milk, 2 tbs. rum and 2 tsp.vanilla until smooth. Divide between pans. Bake 22 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted into centers comes out clean.</div><div><br></div><div>Cool in pans 10 minutes. Transfer to rack; brush with remaining rum. Cool completely. On medium high speed beat topping mix with remaining milk and vanilla until thickened and fluffy 3 - 4 minutes. Place &nbsp;one cake layer on serving plate; spread with 1 1/4 cups. frosting. Top with remaining layer; frost top and side of cake. Sprinkle with nutmeg and garnish if desired.</div>',12,0,0,0,0,10,13,9,9,13,12,150,'{$picture}','2014-02-03 06:58:47','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(458,'Bread Pudding','	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 350oF.<div><br></div><div>Cut bread and soak in milk in a big bowl, set aside.</div><div><br></div><div>In a mold, metal bowl or pot, place 1/2 cup sugar and 2 tbs water, mix it well and cook this in medium heat on your stove until the sugar caramelizes to a soft stage.</div><div><br></div><div>Swirl the caramel around the mold with a capacity of 6 cups totally covering the interior. Set aside.</div><div><br></div><div>Beat eggs and add to bread mixture with sugar, soft butter and dry wine mix with a wood spoon add cinnamon and ground nutmeg , vanilla, almonds an raisins.</div><div><br></div><div>Pour over caramel and cover with aluminum foil , place mold in large pan, half filled with water.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Bake 45 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire rack 15 minutes. Refrigerate</div><div><br></div><div>To serve, run small spatula or knife around edge of pan. Invert serving plate over pan. Shake gently to release.</div>\n	\n	',6,0,0,0,0,13,7,9,9,13,9,70,'../files/recipes/bread pudding.JPG','2014-04-22 05:54:34','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(459,'Scary Cups','	\n	','Beat pudding mix and milk with whisk for 2 minutes, pudding will be soft set in 5 minutes<div><br></div><div>Cut cookies in a little pieces, put 2 tablespoons cookies in each cup, pour over chocolate pudding, put over cookies and chocolate pudding, finish with cookies. Refrigerate</div><div><br></div><div>Garnish with meringue and chocolate chips.</div>',8,0,0,0,0,14,13,8,8,15,4,20,'{$picture}','2014-06-04 16:00:48','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(460,'Corn Pudding','	\n	','Preheat oven to 375oF &nbsp;Coat 13 x 9 inches pan with cooking spray, set aside.<div><br></div><div><br></div><div>&nbsp;In a medium bowl mix together eggs, beat cream sweet corn, corn and pimiento drained, corn muffin mix and ranch dressing. Pour into pan and bake 30 minutes.</div><div><br></div><div>Meanwhile, combine cheese, green onion and bacon cooked and shredded, pour over baked mixture and bake 15 minutes or until melt.</div>',6,0,0,0,0,17,13,8,9,14,4,45,'{$picture}','2014-05-21 13:28:47','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(461,'Pumpkin Flan','	\n	','In a mold, metal bowl or pot place 1/2 cup of sugar and 2 tbs water mix it well. Cook this in medium heat on your stove until the sugar turns amber and caramelizes to a soft stage.Swirl the caramel around the mold totally covering the interior. Set aside.<div><br></div><div>Peel, cut and wash the pumpkin, cook it in a saucepan until tender; Place in a blender and mix the rest of ingredients. Pour over caramel and cover with aluminum foil. Place mold in large pan, half filled with water.</div><div><br></div><div>Bake at 350oF &nbsp; for 45 minutes or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, cool in pan on wire racks 15 minutes &nbsp;and refrigerate completely.</div><div><br></div><div>To serve run small spatula around edge of pan. Invert serving plate over pan, shake gently to release.</div>',6,0,0,0,0,22,7,8,9,13,3,70,'{$picture}','2014-05-04 19:15:41','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(463,'Barbecue Steak','	\n	','	\n		In a bowl mix together crushed garlic, chopped onion, black &nbsp;pepper, salt, oregano, bay leave and sour orange juice. Rub spice mixture over both sides of steaks and reserve at least an hour refrigerate.<div><br></div><div>Prepare grill for direct heat cooking, Grill steaks, turning once, 3 or 5 minutes for each side for medium rare. Brush some of reserved mixture onto grilled steak.</div>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,10,13,9,5,6,6,120,'../files/recipes/grilled meat.JPG','2014-06-05 22:00:50','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(464,'Filled Steak','	\n	','Marinate steak with crushed garlic and lemon juice, refrigerate it at least an hour.<div><br></div><div>In a bowl mix drained stuffed olives and raisins.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Put in each steak 1 slice ham and 2 tbs. of olive mix, roll up steak and tie up with fine cord.</div><div><br></div><div>In a big skillet with hot oil, saute the filled steak, add chopped onion and green pepper, saute it, add tomato sauce, dry wine, salt and black pepper, cover and cook slowly 30 minutes.</div>',4,0,0,0,0,8,7,9,6,6,8,120,'{$picture}','2014-05-18 04:26:38','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(465,'Chicken Tortellini','	\n	','	\n		Cook tortellini following package directions.<div><br></div><div>Cut tomatoes into halves, &nbsp;dice chicken. Preheat large saute pan on medium heat, place oil in pan, then add chicken and cook until light brown. Stir marinara sauce into chicken, then stir in remaining ingredients and cook thoroughly heated. Drain tortellini and stir into marinara sauce.</div><div><br></div><div>Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.</div>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,5,10,8,6,4,9,40,'../files/recipes/chicken tortellini.JPG','2014-01-22 18:49:01','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(467,'Pineapple cake','	\n	','Heat oven to 350 oF<div>Topping: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 inch metal baking pan on stove top over low heat. Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar. Drain pineapple rings, reserving 1/2 cup juice. Fit rings tightly into bottom of pan, you will need 10 to 12. Save any extra rings for snacking. Tuck a maraschino cherry in center of each ring.</div><div>Cake:In medium-size bowl, whisk flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg. In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar 2 minutes. Add eggs,beat until blended. On low speed, beat in half the flour mixture. Pour in reserved 1/2 cup pineapple juice and the milk; beat until blended. Beat in remaining flour mixture, then vanilla.</div><div>Spread batter into pan. Bake at 350 oF for 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.</div><div>Cool cake in pan on rack 10 minutes.</div><div>Place a baking sheet over cake;carefully invert. If any pineapple or cherry stick to pan, gently replace on cake top.</div><div><br></div>',12,0,0,0,0,20,16,7,9,13,9,60,'{$picture}','2014-05-02 04:30:45','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(468,'Love Letters','	\n	','	\n		Combine chicken, chilies, green onions, cheese, garlic and onion powders and salt in medium size bowl, mix well.<div><br></div><div>Place a wrapper on counter with one corner facing toward you. Put about 1 teaspoon chicken mixture slightly below center of wrapper and fold bottom corner up.Fold sides in, points overlapping. Wet edges ti seal. Fold final corner down, to resemble an envelope. Wet edges slightly to seal. Repeat with remaining chicken and wrappers.</div><div><br></div><div>Deep fry, a few at a time, until golden and crispy around edges.</div><div><br></div><div>Drain on paper towels; serve hot.</div>\n	\n	',15,0,0,0,0,5,16,9,6,12,6,30,'','2014-02-02 07:00:35','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(469,'Mango Jam','	\n	','	\n		Peel and slice the mango, put it in a processor food and beat until smooth, add water and sugar. Put it in the pan and bring to a boil, and leave for 10 minutes while boiling. Stir occasionally until desired consistency.\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,12,7,8,6,13,9,20,'','2014-04-02 02:08:11','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(471,'Ricotta Stuffed Chicken','	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 4250F. Coat baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.<div><br></div><div>Combine ricotta, scallion, 2 tbs. parsley, garlic, 1/4 ts.salt and 1/4 tsp.pepper. Dividing evenly, spoon mixture onto center of each chicken half. Roll up; secure with toothpicks. Combine bread crumbs with remaining parsley, salt and pepper. Lightly beat egg white with 1 tbs. water. Coat chicken rolls with flour then dip into egg white mixture. Coat with crumb mixture.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Bake in pan until juices run clear when meat is pierced with fork, 35 or 40 minutes. Remove toothpicks before serving.</div><div><br></div><div>I filled it with a creamy, part-skim ricotta stuffing, then rolled it in bread crumbs and baked. This recipe makes a scrumptious main dish.</div><div><div><br></div></div>\n	\n	',4,0,0,0,0,12,16,8,9,16,15,60,'','2014-05-05 17:14:40','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(472,'Spinach Casserole','	\n	','Preheat oven to 350oF Greased 1 quart casserole.<div><br></div><div>Beat eggs and flour in bowl until smooth. Stir in chopped spinach thawed, cottage cheese, cheddar cheese and salt; mix well.</div><div><br></div><div>Pour into casserole.</div><div><br></div><div>Bake in oven for 1 hour.<br>	\n	<div><br></div><div><br></div></div>',6,0,0,0,0,8,16,8,9,17,10,70,'{$picture}','2014-05-21 14:07:00','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(473,'Hash Brown Casserole','	\n	','Heat oven to 350 0F &nbsp;and coat 13\" x 9\" x 2\" pan with cooking spray.<div><br></div><div>In a large bowl combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper. Stir in the shredded and thawed potatoes, cheese, chopped onion and green pepper and cooked ham.</div><div><br></div><div>Pour into pan and bake uncovered for 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.</div>',12,0,0,1,0,16,16,8,9,14,9,70,'{$picture}','2014-05-20 19:00:55','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL),(475,'Pineapple Banana Bread','	\n	','	\n		Preheat oven to 350oF. &nbsp;and coat 5 foil mini loaf pans with nonstick cooking spray, set aside.<div><br></div><div>Combine cake mix, dry instant pudding, cinnamon, 1 cup juice from crushed pineapple, eggs and oil in large bowl with mixer 2 minutes, or until blended. Add crushed pineapple, bananas and nuts. mix just until blended. Pour prepared batter into pans. Bake 40 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center of cake comes out clean. Cool completely.</div><div><br></div><div>Combine 2 oz, softened cream cheese with1 tablespoon milk and 1/2 cup powered sugar,&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Drizzle over cooled loaves. Garnish with additional chopped pecans, if desired.</div>\n	\n	',20,0,0,0,0,7,16,9,9,14,9,50,'','2014-04-22 10:30:01','',0,0,0,0,0,0,NULL);
