INSERT  DELAYED INTO `secretsofcooking` VALUES (16,'\nAmong &nbsp;the key ingredients to make a cake, eclair, or similar, eggs, oil, wheat flour and sugar are an indispensable to include. \n\n','Indispensable ingredients on a cake','2014-04-28 12:00:01'),(20,'\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid--a2d1a2b-c7d6-40ac-a86a-3d3eb15fea5f\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; white-space: pre-wrap; font-family: Arial;\">The eggs are agents of growth and they should be used at room temperature; but if the recipe requires separating the yolks from the whites it will be easier to do it right after taking them out from the fridge, while they are still cold. Once split wait until they reach room temperature.</span></p><div><br></div></span> \n\n','How to use eggs when baking','2014-05-05 12:00:02'),(21,'\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid--a2d1a2b-c7db-ffc5-1ac4-b6fea0f67efa\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><font face=\"Arial\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">When the recipe indicates to add whole eggs, add them one by one, donâ€™t add the other ingredients until the others are well joined.\n</span></font></p><div><br></div></span> \n\n','When to add the next ingredient','2014-05-12 12:00:02'),(22,'\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid--a2d1a2b-c7db-8ac3-488c-47634c0e5daa\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><font face=\"Arial\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">Incorporate the egg yolks into the egg whites with a rolling motions.</span></font></p><div><br></div></span> \n\n','How to incorporate egg yolks','2014-05-19 12:00:01'),(32,'\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid--a2d1a2b-c7dc-ed8a-9296-8f271f93f68c\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><font face=\"Arial\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">If you use butter in cakes, it shouldn\'t be salted, and use it as the recipe indicates. You can also use vegetable oil in some cakes.</span></font></p><div><br></div></span> \n\n','What\'s the best kind of butter you should use?','2014-05-26 12:00:02'),(24,'\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid--a2d1a2b-c7dc-4bbe-aad3-af12051b7bb7\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><font face=\"Arial\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px; white-space: pre-wrap;\">There are different kinds of wheat flour. If the wheat flour contains baking powder sifting, skip this ingredient in order to use it.</span></font></p><div><br></div></span> \n\n','How to know if you need baking powder.','2014-06-02 12:00:03'),(26,'\n<span id=\"docs-internal-guid--a2d1a2b-c7dd-aa21-c2df-4bf1d999d2a9\"><p dir=\"ltr\" style=\"margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt;\"><span style=\"line-height: 18px;\">When measuring liquids using measuring cups, place the cups in a flat surface in order to get an accurate measurement.</span></p><div><br></div></span> \n\n','How to measure liquids','2013-08-30 12:00:05'),(27,'\nBrown sugar is measured by compressing it in the cup like shredded coconut, bread crumbs and fruit ground, to avoid the spaces \n\n','How to measure sugar','2013-08-31 12:00:05'),(28,'\nTo reduce a recipe in half, use exactly 50% of all ingredients. If the entire recipe requires to use of an egg or an odd number of them, whisk, measure it by teaspoon,and use half of it. \n\n','How to split a recipe in half','2013-09-01 12:00:02'),(29,'\nTo make half the recipe, cake, etc. select&nbsp; smaller pans in proportion so that amount so that the time and oven temperature are equal. \n\n','What to do when making smaller cakes','2013-09-02 12:00:02'),(30,'\nTo double the recipe using exactly twice all the ingredients and proceed, use two pans of the size that the recipe indicates and watch the time of the oven. \n\n','How to double a recipe','2013-09-03 12:00:03'),(33,'\nReplacing whole milk with skim milk reduces fat. \n\n','How to reduce fat in your diet','2013-09-04 12:00:05'),(34,'\nUsing egg whites means less cholesterol.&nbsp; \n\n','How to lower your cholesterol','2013-09-05 12:00:05'),(35,'\nPears or applesauce add sweetness and moisture to baked goods. Use one quarter of the oil called for, and substitute puree for the rest.<br> \n\n','How to substitute sugars.','2013-09-06 12:00:01'),(36,'\nAlways store apples in the coldest part of the refrigerator. If left at room temperature, they will deteriorate more quickly.<br> \n\n','How to make apples last longer','2013-09-07 12:00:06'),(37,'\nTo prevent discoloration of aluminum&nbsp; pans, line the bottom with a circle of parchment. Coat the paper with vegetable cooking spray. \n\n','How to prevent the discoloration of a pan','2013-09-08 12:00:09'),(38,'\nMake measuring honey easier by spraying the measuring cup with vegetable cooking spray. The honey will not stick to the cup. \n\n','How to measure honey','2013-09-09 12:00:08'),(39,'\nIf you use garlic often, chop several heads of garlic at once. Place the chopped garlic in 1 tablespoon of olive oil in an airtight glass container. Store in the coldest part of the refrigerator for up to 2 weeks. \n\n','A shortcut to using garlic','2013-09-10 12:00:07'),(40,'\nNuts are easier to chop when they are warm. Heat them in the microwave on high for 2 minutes or in an oven set to 325 0F for about 5 minutes. \n\n','How to easily chop nuts','2013-09-11 12:00:03'),(42,'\nIn a supermarket choose dark, green salad. Those are loaded with more vitamins \n\n','Which salad should you choose?','2013-09-12 12:00:03'),(43,'\nYou need some fat in the salad&nbsp; to help your body absorb the vitamins from the veggies. Olive oil and vinegar are healthier.<br> \n\n','A healthy tip for your salad','2013-09-13 12:00:04'),(44,'Like all perishable food, mayonnaise should be&nbsp; kept cool, and not left out on the table for more than 1 hour. \n\n','How to preserve mayonnaise','2013-09-16 20:49:52'),(46,'\nWash fresh vegetables in cold water with 2 - 3 tbs of baking soda to get them extra clean. \n\n','How to clean veggies','2013-09-30 12:00:02'),(47,'\nShine silverware with a mixture of three parts baking soda and one part water. \n\n','How to keep silverware clean','2013-10-07 12:00:02'),(48,'\nIf you are&nbsp; out of baking powder, for every cup of flour in a recipe use 2 teaspoons cream of tartar plus 1 teaspoon of baking soda. Mix together and use immediately \n\n','What to do when you are out of baking powder?','2013-10-14 12:00:05'),(49,'\nIf you are uncertain about the effectiveness of your baking powder, dissolve a little in water, if it bubbles, it is OK. \n\n','How to know you have good baking powder.','2013-10-21 12:00:03'),(50,'\nCookies baked on dark, nonstick cookie sheets are more likely to burn, so keep a close eye on them. Also, burning can occur on sheets with sides, or if a cookie sheet is only half full. \n\n','Keeping an eye on the cookies.','2013-10-28 12:00:02'),(51,'\nEgg whites can be frozen and thawed at room temperature and used in the same way as fresh egg whites. \n\n','Reusing egg whites.','2013-11-04 13:00:07'),(52,'\nIf and egg is stuck to the carton, moisten the cardboard to free it. \n\n','What to do when an egg is stuck.','2013-11-11 13:00:03'),(53,'\nIf a recipe calls for one cup of whole milk and you are out, you can use one cup of skim milk and two tablespoons butter, or 1/2 cup of evaporated milk and 1/2 cup water. \n\n','What to do when out of milk','2013-11-18 13:00:03'),(54,'\nIf a recipe calls for one cup of honey, you can substitute it for 1 1/4 cups sugar and 1/4 cup water. \n\n','Using an alternative','2013-11-25 13:00:02'),(55,'Research shows that chives stimulate the digestion of fats, if consumed regularly, can help reduce cholesterol levels. \n\n','Keeping yourself healthy!','2013-12-02 13:00:03'),(56,'\nDo not heat chives, you will lose the vitamin C and digestive properties. \n\n','Keeping you healthy!','2013-12-09 13:00:02'),(58,'\nTo preserve the essential oils, vitamins and flavor of chives, cut it with a scissors instead of chop or grind. \n\n','How to maintain food.','2013-12-16 13:00:05'),(59,'\nFrozen chives preserves more flavor when it is dry, Cut it with scissors into small pieces and place in a small container with water, then freeze them. Before&nbsp; thaw, drain through a sieve. \n\n','Taking care of food','2013-12-23 13:00:02'),(60,'\nJust a bit of barbecue sauce left? Spread it on &nbsp;a pizza crust; top with shredded cooked chicken and Jack &nbsp;cheese. Bake at 450oF for 10 minutes or until cheese is melted. \n\n','What to do with a bit of bbq sauce.','2013-12-30 13:00:02'),(61,'\nIf you have a dash of horseradish add the spicy stuff to your favorite bottled vinaigrette or &nbsp;ranch salad dressing to punch up the flavor. \n\n','Upgrade your dressing.','2014-01-06 13:00:02'),(62,'\nGot a spoonful of cocktail sauce?Make a quick marinade, combine 1 part sauce to 2 parts vinaigrette, use for steak, ribs or chicken. \n\n','Marinade in 3, 2, 1!','2014-01-13 13:00:02'),(63,'\nIf you have a tad of tartar sauce, stir into mayonnaise with some chopped fresh parsley and use it to give potato salad a tangy twist. \n\n','Upgrading your foods!','2014-01-20 13:00:03'),(64,'\nJust a smidgen of grape jelly? Whisk together 2 parts jelly to 1 part soy sauce. Brush over chicken or pork chops during last 5 - 8 minutes of cooking \n\n','Making a sauce in an instant.','2014-01-27 13:00:03'),(65,'\nNo Greek seasoning on hand? &nbsp;Simply use equal amounts of dried oregano, garlic and onion powders, and an extra pinch of salt. \n\n','What to do when out of Greek seasoning?','2014-02-03 13:00:04'),(66,'\nSimmer blueberries in a pan with orange juice, grated orange zest and sugar, 5 minutes. Serve over sorbet or light ice cream. \n\n','How to make an ice cream syrup.','2014-02-10 13:00:03'),(67,'\nToss berries into chicken salad with walnuts, celery and raspberry vinaigrette. \n\n','How to make a salad colorful','2014-02-17 13:00:05'),(68,'\nThe average ice cream scoops is about 1/4 cup, it will be a cinch to dish out just the right amount of rice or mashed potatoes. \n\n','How to serve the right amount','2014-02-24 13:00:02'),(69,'\nScoop cookie dough batter onto baking sheets for perfectly round cookies, or use your scoop to plate shrimp or egg salad. \n\n','A helpful tip for you','2014-03-03 13:00:03'),(70,'\nCupcakes come out all different sizes? &nbsp;Use a scoop to measure out the batter. Then, when they are cooled, use the scoop again to give each one its own perfectly dome -shaped frosting crown. \n\n','How to make perfect cupcakes','2014-03-10 12:00:03'),(71,'\nGrating the zest from an orange or lemon? First wrap the grater in a few layers of plastic wrap. You will still get the zest, but it won\'t stick to your grater.<br> \n\n','How to grate zest. ','2014-03-17 12:00:06'),(72,'\nWhen boiling smelly vegetables like cauliflower or cabbage, add a torn-up slice of bread to the water. It\'ll absorb odors instantly. \n\n','How to absorb odors.','2014-03-24 12:00:04'),(73,'\nDon\'t have any sweet onions for your salad? Slice a regular one and soak it in cold water for 30 minutes. The pungent acid will seep out, giving it a &nbsp;sweeter flavor. \n\n','How to make sweet onions for a salad.','2014-03-31 12:00:03'),(74,'\nWhen a recipe calls for citrus zest, use the fruit while it\'s still cold from the fridge. It\'ll be firmer and easier to grate. \n\n','How to make a better citrus grate.','2014-04-07 12:00:01'),(75,'\nTo keep kitchen drains flowing smoothly, pour a solution of 1/2 cup salt and 4 cups water down the drain every other week to remove grease and prevent odors. \n\n','How to keep your drain flowing.','2014-04-14 12:00:03'),(76,'\nRemove cooking odors! Pour some whole spices into a saucepan, add water and simmer. \n\n','How to remove cooking odors.','2014-04-21 12:00:02'),(77,'Throw a pinch of baking soda into potatoes while mashing to make them fluffier','how to make fluffy potatoes','2013-09-25 15:23:47'),(78,'The key to whipped cream is keeping everything cold. Always start with cold cream, and chill the bowl and the beater. Start beating slow.<div>When the cream just starts to thicken, that is when you add the sugar. Watch closely as you continue to whip. You don\'t want peaks that stand up. It\'s better that they start droopy, and&nbsp;<i>then </i>wait for them to get firm. It\'s &nbsp;always better to underwhip than to overwhip.</div>','How to make perfect whipped cream','2013-10-16 21:31:20'),(79,'It\'s an easy way to remove the block of bars from the pan after baking. Tear off a large piece of foil, turn the pan upside down, and mold the foil over the pan. Turn the pan right side up and press the foil into place. Using a pastry brush, slather the foil with softened butter.','Lining the pan with buttered foil.','2013-10-16 21:39:57'),(80,'Pay attention to chocolate when you melt it.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>The chocolate has two enemies: heat and liquid,always use slow heat &nbsp;and be sure to keep it away from water,.</div><div>The chocolate should not be stored in the refrigerator.The &nbsp;condensation in the fridge can ruin chocolate. It is best kept in a cool, dark and dry place.</div>','The chocolate.','2013-10-16 22:02:02'),(81,'Watery soup. Stir together a tablespoon each of softener butter and flour, then whisk into simmering soup.<div><br></div><div>Broken cookies. Layer the pieces with whipped cream and fruit in a glass bowl to make a trifle.</div><div><br></div><div>Too sweet sauce. Add a dash of vinegar or lemon juice.</div>','What to do when a good recipe goes bad.','2013-10-16 22:12:20'),(82,'Gently scrape off the charred bits and set the meat aside. Then dice up onions and simmer them in a pan with white wine and chicken broth for a quick sauce.','Burned meat?','2013-10-16 22:41:25');
